title: pistachio salad
directions: In large bowl, put Cool Whip.
Sprinkle instant pudding and add pineapple, marshmallows, nuts and coconut.
Mix well and set in refrigerator to chill.

title: cottage biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in butter and oil.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add egg and cottage cheese.
Knead and form ball.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into 1 1/2 to 2-inch chunks.
In large saucepan, cover potatoes with water; bring to boiling.
Cook over medium heat until tender (20 to 25 minutes).
Drain.
Mash until smooth.
Blend in cream cheese, sour cream, milk, salt, onion salt and pepper.
Spoon into buttered 3-quart casserole.
Refrigerate, covered.

title: peachy keen(serves 1)
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender on medium speed.

title: basil mushrooms
directions: Place mushrooms in a jar.
Mix all other ingredients and add to mushrooms.
Close tightly; toss gently and refrigerate.
Best if served in 2 hours or so.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugar and salt.
Stir in egg, molasses and vinegar. Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients; stir into molasses mixture.
Chill about 2 hours.
On lightly floured surface roll to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutter. Place 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Make eyes and buttons with raisins.
Bake in moderate (375°) oven for about 6 minutes. Cool slightly and remove from sheet. Allow to finish cooling on wire racks.
Store in tightly covered tins.
Keeps well for 3 to 4 weeks.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Generously grease 8-inch cast-iron skillet. In medium bowl, whisk together milk, buttermilk, egg, oil, sugar, baking powder and salt until blended. Add corn meal and flour (which has been mixed). Mix until dry ingredients are moistened. Add red peppers, jalapeno and corn. Pour in skillet. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until light golden brown. Makes 6 servings.

title: homemade mints
directions: Mix all of the ingredients by hand. I use waxed paper and divide into 3 sections. Knead until soft enough to roll into a long thin roll. Cut either with scissors or a sharp knife. Let stay on waxed paper for about an hour, then store in airtight containers in the refrigerator. These will last for quite some time when stored this way.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Stir cocoa and water over heat until smooth.
Stir in sugar and salt until dissolved.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Store in covered jar in refrigerator.

title: picante shrimp dip
directions: Place all ingredients but parsley and chips in food processor. Mix thoroughly, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add parsley and process only as needed to mix evenly.
Serve with Taco Bell brand tortilla chips.
Makes 2 cups or 6 to 8 servings.
Takes 5 minutes.

title: salmon balls
directions: Mix together, except for soup and water.
Form into ball.
Put in loaf cake pan.
Pour soup, diluted with water, over the salmon balls.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecued beef(pulgogi)
directions: Slice beef thinly, cutting across grain and scoring lightly with knife to make more tender.
Cut into bite-sized pieces and marinate beef in the sugar and rice wine.
Mix marinated beef thoroughly with soy sauce, chopped garlic, sesame salt, m.s.g. and sesame oil.
Broil seasoned beef over hot charcoal on a grill or in frypan.
Pulgogi is delicious served with lettuce leaves, sesame leaves, garland chrysanthemum and garlic.
Pulgogi is generally broiled over charcoal on a grill at the table.

title: nina's chicken mull
directions: Take chicken off the bone. Cook onions, celery, peppers and tomatoes in margarine until tender.
Add this mixture and chicken to chicken broth.
Add a few crumbled crackers to thicken slightly.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with saltines, ketchup and sliced onions.

title: meat marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl and hand mix for 1 1/2 minutes.
Marinate your favorite meat approximately 2 hours. Makes 1 cup of marinade.

title: mama's cornmeal mush
directions: Stir cornmeal slowly into boiling water.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Turn burner on low to keep it hot for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with butter, or we ate it with cold milk.

title: microwave chocolate mousse pie
directions: In a 2-quart glass measure with handle, combine chocolate, sweetened condensed milk and vanilla.
Cook on 100% power (High) 2 to 4 minutes, stirring after each minute until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
Cool to room temperature, about 1 1/2 hours.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Chill 4 hours or until set.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: sugarless apple dessert
directions: Combine gelatin, diluted apple juice concentrate, cinnamon and nutmeg in large skillet, stirring well.
Let stand 1 minute. Cook over low heat for 1 minute or until tender.
Stir apples gently and baste with pan juice several times during cooking process.
Add margarine; stir gently until margarine melts. Remove from heat.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Spoon mixture into dessert dishes to serve.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all and refrigerate overnight.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add sour cream, mix together.
Add flour and add soda, salt and flavor.

title: cookies from cake mix
directions: Bake at 350°.
Also, can add chocolate chips to batter.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Melt butter, milk and chocolate.
Mix marshmallows and peanuts.
Add chocolate mix.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan with wax paper on bottom.
Chill and cut.

title: easy cheese bread 1
directions: Combine mix, cheeses, poppy seed and add egg and milk.
Mix just to blend.
Beat vigorously 1 minute. Turn into well-greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle with additional poppy seed, if desired.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool before slicing.

title: blueberry dream whip pie
directions: Prepare both envelopes of Dream Whip as directed on box. Allow cheese to soften and blend with Dream Whip.
Add powdered sugar and mix well.
Stir in lemon juice.
Pour mixture into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Top with blueberry pie filling. Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: sparkling harvest cider
directions: Combine cider, ReaLemon and sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Garnish as desired.
Serve over ice.
Garnish with apple wedges.

title: chocolate nut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips and shortening in microwave until smooth (1 1/2 minutes).
Stir in nuts.
Put into 1-inch paper candy cups. Refrigerate until firm.
Makes 14 to 16 candies.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir.
Cook 4 more minutes on High.
Add next 2 ingredients.
Cook on High for 1 minute.
Mix in the last ingredient.
Pour in greased pan.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs, water, raisins, nuts, and pumpkin. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 3 loaf pans (only fill pans 1/2 full). Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish with graham crackers. Pour prepared pudding on top.
Add Cool Whip; another layer graham crackers.
Top with chocolate frosting.
Chill until firm.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese, and mayonaise together.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles. Brown hamburger. Drain off grease.
Pour Ragu on hamburger and heat.
Use a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

Barely cover bottom of pan with sauce followed by layer of 1/2 noodles, more sauce, 1/2 cottage cheese, 1 package cheese, the rest of the noodles, rest of sauce, rest of cottage cheese and the other package of cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Take off foil and brown cheese on top.

title: picnic potatoes
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Break up frozen hash browns into the butter.
Mix the soup, sour cream, onion, cheese and salt; pour over potatoes.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in well-greased skillet or square cake pan at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: roast
directions: Line roaster with foil.
Add all ingredients.
Tightly close foil around ingredients.
Roast in oven at 350° until done, approximately 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at
350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan; remove from heat.
Add cocoa, sugar, eggs, flour, salt and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Walnuts or pecans can be added, 1/2 cup chopped.

title: quick and easy rolls
directions: Mix yeast and warm water; set aside.
Cream in large bowl the margarine and sugar; add egg and flour.
Add dissolved yeast.
Mix until well mixed.
Keep in large, airtight bowl.
Drop by spoonfuls in muffin tin.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spanish skillet dinner
directions: Brown rice, onion and garlic in oil.
Add turkey; brown, stirring frequently.
Add tomatoes and remaining ingredients. Cover; simmer 30 minutes.
Mix well.
Serves 4.

title: lazy gal cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk in bowl.
Pour mixture into the melted butter dish.
In the center of that, pour the 2 cups fruit.
Do not stir.
Bake at 400° until crust is brown, about 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar. Blend very well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Mix into oil-egg mixture and combine thoroughly. Add apples and nuts.
Mix with spoon, then add vanilla. Bake in tube pan. Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/4 hours. Remove from oven and let cool in pan while preparing glaze.

title: peppermint candy
directions: Chips can be bought at a baker's supply.
Sift out and discard powder from peppermint chips and set chips aside.
Melt white chips in microwave (50% about 5 minutes) or on stove.
Stir every two minutes.
Mix peppermint chips with melted white chips.
Spread thin layer on waxed paper.
Let cool; break into small pieces.

title: mandel bread(an old family recipe)
directions: Mix in order given.
Grease a 4 sided cookie sheet lightly with oil.
With a teaspoon, spoon out 3 long strips lengthwise.
Put any leftover on top.
Put cold water into a glass; with your fingertips pat the top of the strips.
Sprinkle the top with a mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, until golden brown.
When done, remove from oven, cut at an angle and lift off pan.
If you want them crunchier, turn each piece on it's side and return to oven for 6 minutes on each side.
Enjoy!

title: sour cream corn bake
directions: Mix margarine, corn and eggs.
Stir in sour cream.
Sprinkle on muffin mix, beat well.
Bake in 3-quart casserole for 1 hour at 350°.
Can freeze.
Super casserole.

title: tortillas
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Knead until well blended.
Heat griddle. Roll out and place on griddle until browned.
Turn and brown other side.
Continue until desired amount or all gone.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Heat cherries and sugar together.
Add a few drops of red food coloring.
Pour into 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Combine oats, brown sugar, flour and salt; cut in butter.
Add pecans. Sprinkle mixture over cherries.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream and ice cream.

title: apple punch
directions: In large punch bowl, combine apple juice, cranberry cocktail and orange juice.
Stir to dissolve.
Slowly add ginger ale or champagne.
Vertically, thinly slice apple, forming whole apple slices.
Float apple slices on top of punch.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: add some zest to your hamburger helper
directions: Make Hamburger Helper as directed, but add just 1/4 cup extra water to make it juicy.
Line a cake pan with Fritos.
Add the Hamburger Helper.
Spread it over the chips evenly so the juice will cover all the chips, then cover with your favorite cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese has melted.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl.
Make well in center, pour into well the eggs, oil and strawberries with juice. Add nuts and mix until moistened.
Grease and flour 2 regular size loaf pans or 3 medium size.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until sides turn loose.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pans.

title: baked apples
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Dice marshmallows and chop nuts.
Boil water in bottom of a double boiler.
Turn off heat.
Place in top of double boiler 1 pound of milk chocolate.
Stir occasionally until melted.
Line a tray with waxed paper.
Pour in 1/2 of melted chocolate.
Cover with marshmallows and nut meat.
Pour rest of chocolate over this.

title: chicken with poppy seed
directions: Mix sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Melt margarine and mix with crumbs and poppy seed.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: marinated london broil
directions: In a large oblong container (or anything big enough to fit one complete shelf of your refrigerator), place the meat in this large container, making sure there is enough room around the edges for the liquids to saturate the sides thoroughly.
Pour the liquids over the meat.
Cover the container with plastic wrap and place in the refrigerator for 3 to 5 days.
Be sure to turn the meat once
a day, making sure the marinade is spooned over the meat after each turning.
Grill for about 30 to 45 minutes.
The flavor is mouthwatering!
Serve with salad, baked potatoes, rolls and butter.
This is a great dish for special occasions, or for just a family get-together.
Serves:

title: woolworth's cheese cake
directions: Mix the jello with boiling water and juice of one lemon.
Let cool.
In separate bowl mix cream cheese, sugar and juice of one lemon.
Set aside and whip chilled evaporated milk and juice of one lemon until frothy like meringue.
Combine all three mixture. Pour into large dish lined with graham cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and refrigerate.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Boil first four ingredients together, cook 15 to 20 minutes. Bake pie shell, pour ingredients into shell and add fresh strawberries.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix oil, fructose, egg whites and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add walnuts, dates or chocolate chips.
Mix well. Drop by generous spoonfuls on oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Saute garlic cloves, soy sauce, ground ginger and sliced chicken.
Then add broccoli, carrots and water chestnuts.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Mix cornstarch in water.
Add to stir-fry and cook until thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Place chicken in large resealable plastic food storage bag. Combine cornstarch, wine, soy sauce and garlic powder in small bowl, whisk until well blended.
Pour over chicken pieces.
Seal bag, toss to coat.
Marinate in refrigerator 1 hour.
Drain chicken, discard marinade.
Heat oil in wok or large nonstick skillet until hot.
Add onions, stir fry 1 minute.
Add chicken, stir fry 2 minutes or until browned.

title: lemon meringue cake
directions: Using 8-inch round layer cake pans, make and cool cake as directed on the label.
Cook lemon pudding and pie filling as directed for pie filling.
Cool 30 minutes; stir several times. Beat egg whites until frothy; gradually add sugar; beat until stiff, but not dry.
Split each cake layer into 2 thin layers. Stack on cookie sheet or ovenproof plate; spread lemon pudding between layers and on top of cake.
Spread meringue around sides of cake.
Bake at 450° for about 5 minutes, until light brown.
Cool to room temperature before serving.
Store cake in the refrigerator.

title: fruit squares
directions: Mix shortening with beaten egg.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients, using a pastry cutter or forks.
Use 7 x 11-inch or 9-inch square baking dish.
Put in 1/2 of batter (loosely); do not pack.
Use a can of any fruit pie filling (cherry, blueberry, peach, pineapple or apple).
Spread lightly and cover with remaining batter mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: german chocolate candy
directions: Chop German chocolate and melt in double boiler.
Add butterscotch morsels and melt together with German chocolate. Stir until well melted.
Remove from heat and stir in pecans. Drop by teaspoon on long tray lined with waxed paper. Refrigerate.
When firm, put in container and store in refrigerator.

title: rugelach
directions: Bring the cheese and butter to room temperature.
Mix with sugar and flour.
Form into a ball and wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate at least 4 hours before proceeding with recipe.

title: crispy oven potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine melted butter with the next 5 ingredients.
Layer potatoes in baking dish, brushing each layer with butter mixture. Bake for 40 minutes or until tender.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake for 5 minutes.
(Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, if desired.) Serve with pork or sausage.

title: freezer strawberry jam
directions: Mash fruit well.
Add sugar.
Mix and let stand.
Mix juice and pectin; stir into fruit.
Stir 3 minutes. Put into jars quickly.
Cover with tight lids.
After jelly has set for 24 hours.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: jalapeno sausage cornbread
directions: Combine 1 cup cornmeal, milk, eggs, salt, soda, bacon drippings and corn in a bowl; mix and set aside.
Saute sausage until lightly browned; drain thoroughly.
Put remaining cornmeal in a greased 10 1/2-inch iron skillet.
Pour half of cornmeal batter into skillet. Sprinkle evenly with sausage; top with onions, then cheese.
Add peppers evenly on top.
Pour remaining batter over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: low-fat cream cheese pie
directions: Mix until creamy the cottage cheese, cream cheese, sugar and egg.
Add cocoa (optional).
Put all ingredients in a food processor and mix well.
If you want chocolate, mix in the 1/3 cup cocoa.
Pour in a graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: golden cream soup
directions: In a large pan combine potatoes, water, celery, onions, parsley flakes, bouillon cube and seasoning.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Gradually add milk to flour, mixing until well blended.
Add milk mixture to vegetables until thick.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add ham.

title: blueberries and cream cheesecake
directions: Combine 2 1/2 cups blueberries and 1 tablespoon cornstarch in container of electric blender. Blend until smooth. Cook puree in saucepan over medium-high heat about 15 minutes or until slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
Set mixture aside to cool. Reserve 1/2 cup puree for glaze.

title: nippy cole slaw dressing
directions: Combine water, vinegar, sugar, salt and egg in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Cool and pour over your favorite shredded recipe.

title: quick and easy delicious brownies
directions: While heating oven, place sticks of butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan; allow to melt, watching carefully.
Combine all ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; add sugar, flour, cornstarch and cocoa and mix smooth with a small amount of milk.
Add remaining milk.
Place on fire and cook slowly, stirring constantly.

title: jewel slay's scalloped eggplant
directions: Pare eggplant.
Slice and boil in salted water until tender; drain.
Add egg, butter, onion, cheese, garlic powder, milk and bread crumbs.
Place in buttered 1-quart baking dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into greased 9-inch pie plate or 3 cup casserole dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with sliced green onion and chopped tomato if desired.
Serve with assorted chips and crackers. Makes 2 cups.

title: jalapeno chicken wraps
directions: Cut chicken into 2 x 1 1/2-inch strips.
In a large plastic bag, mix garlic and onion powder, pepper, seasoned salt and paprika; add chicken and shake to coat.
Place a chicken and onion strip in each jalapeno half.
Wrap each with a piece of bacon and secure with toothpicks.
Grill, uncovered, over indirect medium heat for 18 to 20 minutes or until chicken juices run clear and bacon is crisp, turning once.

title: sauerbraten (beef)
directions: Sprinkle roast with salt and pepper; place in large deep glass bowl.
Combine vinegar and water in a small saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat; cover with plastic wrap.
Marinate overnight or up to 2 days, turning frequently.

title: granola
directions: Mix the first 6 dry ingredients in a large bowl. Combine and heat vegetable oil, honey and vanilla. Add this to the dry ingredients and mix thoroughly. Spread mixture on cookie sheet(s). Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Cool thoroughly. Add sunflower seeds and the preferred combination of dried fruit/nuts.
Store in airtight container.

title: peanutty stuffed apple wedges
directions: Stir together cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add orange juice, 1 tablespoon at a time, stirring well.
Stir in honey, dried fruit and coconut.
Cut each apple into quarters lengthwise. Core apple and remove ends.
Hollow out wedges to within 1/2-inch of peel.
Reserve pulp.
Combine lemon juice and water; brush over apple.
Chop apple pulp and add to peanut butter mix.
Fill apple wedges with peanut butter mixture.

title: creamy peanut butter cheese pie(hurry-up dessert)
directions: In large bowl, combine cream cheese and peanut butter with electric mixer until smooth.
Add powdered sugar and milk.
Beat until combined.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into pie shell. Sprinkle with peanuts.
Cover and chill in freezer 15 minutes.
Cut into wedges.
Serve with chocolate syrup drizzled over top if desired.
Serves 8.

title: pet milk pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Mix in a 1 1/2 quart bowl, sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in syrup.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in milk, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Bake 50 minutes or until firm.
Cool before serving.

title: trails end chocolate cake
directions: Prepare two 9-inch cake pans by lining bottom with wax paper or parchment paper, grease and flour pan bottoms.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla.
Sift together flour, cocoa, baking soda and baking powder.
Add alternately with ice water to butter mixture.
Blend well.
Pour into pans and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pans 10 minutes before removing.
Cool completely and frost with Peppermint Frosting.

title: boiled crayfish
directions: Select adequate size cooking bag and put all ingredients in except salt and pepper.
Place bag in small amount of water in large pot and cook for 30 minutes.
Increase water to accommodate 10 pounds of crayfish.
Bring water to boil, add crayfish, maintaining boiling point of water.
Crayfish should be cooked in about 7 minutes.

title: better banana pudding
directions: In large skillet or pan, boil first 3 ingredients until syrupy.
Mix rest of ingredients; pour into syrup and cook until thickened.
Cool, then add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
In a large ovenproof dish, put a layer of graham crackers then a layer of pudding over crackers.
Then put a layer of sliced bananas. Repeat layers until all is used.
Cover with meringue made from the 2 egg whites and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Brown at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: homemade cheesecake
directions: Blend ingredients with mixer.
Pour into graham cracker crust and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove and let cool.
Top with any pie filling, topping or Cool Whip.

title: smothered steak
directions: Put steak strips, flour, salt and pepper in crock-pot.
Stir well to coat steak. Add all remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on high 1 hour, then turn to low for 8 hours.
(High for 5 hours.) Serve with rice.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Wrap each piece of bacon around a water chestnut and piece of pineapple.
Secure with a toothpick and marinate overnight in soy sauce.
Line a shallow pan with foil and top with a rack (the foil will save you a pan to scrub and the rack will insure the bacon cooks evenly).
Place bacon rolls on rack and bake in preheated oven at 450° for 10 minutes or until bacon is crisp.

title: mom's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar and 2 eggs.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt; stir into the first mixture.
Roll into balls size of large walnuts.
Place 3 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Flatten gently with fork dipped in flour; crisscross.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until set, but not hard.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: vegetarian omelet
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend.
Grease Silverstone skillet. Preheat and pour in omelet.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Loosen around edges and slide out onto plate.
Turn frypan upside down over plate.
Invert so the uncooked side of omelet is at the bottom of pan.
Cover and fry 10 minutes.
Allow to set for a few minutes.

title: dolly's dandy dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients well; dip wiener in batter and deep fry until golden brown.

title: rotel chili
directions: Combine ground chuck and onions in soup pot.
Cook over medium heat until chuck is browned and onions are tender.
Add chili powder and stir.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Chop fruit.
With nuts and fruits chopped, add raisins, coconut and graham cracker crumbs.
Mix well.
Melt marshmallows in milk.
Cook slowly over low heat.
Pour over nuts and fruits mixture.
Mix well.
Spray a 10-inch tube pan with Pam.
Press firmly in tube pan very tight and refrigerate overnight.
Turn upside-down on plate next day.
May have to set a few minutes but will come out of pan.
Keep refrigerated.
Keep wrapped.

title: spanish hamburger
directions: Cook beef until browned. Drain off grease. Add the onion while cooking. Add the rest of the ingredients and cook until thick and hot. Serves 4 to 8.

title: party nibbles
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large roasting pan; stir well. Combine last 3 ingredients; stir well.
Drizzle over nut mixture. Stir well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Yields about 3 quarts.

title: lazy salad
directions: Mix jello, water, pineapple, cheese, miracle whip and whipping cream or cool whip and chill.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Blend margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs, then slowly add the flour.
Stir in vanilla, maraschino cherries and nuts.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in a 9 or 10-inch tube pan.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef across grain into strips.
Cook and stir beef in margarine in 10-inch skillet over low heat until brown.
Reserve 1/3 cup of broth, stir in remaining broth, catsup, salt and garlic into skillet.
Heat to boiling and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beef is tender, 45 minutes.
Stir in mushrooms and onion. Cover and simmer until onion is tender.
Shake reserved broth and the flour in a tightly covered container.
Gradually stir into beef mixture.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Reduce heat, stir in sour cream and heat through. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: quick chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg well; add a couple of tablespoons of mixture to egg; mix well.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture comes to boil (Will curdle as thickens; just beat until smooth).
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Cool.
When cool, top with Cool Whip. Grate unsweetened chocolate square over top.
Refrigerate.
Enjoy!

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar and beat again.
Add flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat in hot milk and butter.
Bake in loaf pan in moderate oven at 350° until done about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: nibble mix
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
Combine cereal, popcorn and pretzels in a large baking pan.
In small pan, melt margarine.
Slowly pour margarine over cereal mix.
Stir to coat.

title: basic waffle recipe
directions: Sift dry ingredients three times, set aside.
Separate whites from yolks of eggs.
Beat whites until stiff.
Beat yolks in mixing bowl.
Add milk until blended.
Add dry ingredients, beat until smooth.
Add melted shortening and beat until well blended. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Put 4 to 6 tablespoons of batter into waffle maker.
Cook according to waffle maker's instructions.
Makes 5 to 6 waffles.

title: pineapple whip
directions: Place marshmallows and juice in double boiler until marshmallows melt.
Let cool, then whip.
Whip cream or Milnot until stiff.
Add to marshmallow mixture.
Pour into pan or Pyrex and place in refrigerator until set, about 1/2 day.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients.
Add seasoning.
Cook until tender. Add soup, cheese and milk until cheese melts.
Simmer until flavor blends.

title: fancy scalloped corn
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except butter.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: steak sauce
directions: Heat all together and serve over steak.

title: diet fruit salad
directions: Drain peaches and cut in thirds.
Add strawberries to peaches. Add pineapple along with the juice.
Cut bananas into bite-size pieces and add.
Sprinkle Tang over fruit and mix well.
Add dry pudding mix.
Chill before serving.

title: fruit crumble
directions: Combine all ingredients except fruit.
Spread half of mixture in bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cover with fruit and top with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350°
for 40 minutes.
Can be served with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter and oleo by hand. Chill.
Form into small balls. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax.
Dip balls into melted chocolate and set on wax paper to dry. If they stick to wax paper it needs more wax.

title: deep-dish pizza casserole
directions: Prepare shells and cheese.
Brown meat with green peppers and onions in frying pan.
Drain; stir in pizza sauce.
Spoon shells and cheese into 2-quart baking dish.
Top with meat mixture. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strata(very good)
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle bread cubes evenly over bottom.
Sprinkle cooked sausage over crumbs.
Place pepper and onions over sausage.
Mix eggs, milk, cheese, mustard, Worcestershire and paprika.
Pour over sausage.
Sprinkle bacon over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Blend in flour, buttermilk, cocoa, food coloring and vinegar.
Add soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix 2 to 3 minutes with electric mixer, scraping bottom and sides of bowl often.
Pour into 3 well-greased and floured layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: penuche
directions: Boil all ingredients except nuts to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts and beat until thick and creamy.
Pour into greased pan and allow to harden.

title: seafood cakes
directions: Mix tuna, dressing, mustard, vegetables, pimento, seasonings and 1/2 cup of bread crumbs.
Shape mixture in balls.
Roll in remaining 3/4 cup bread crumbs.
Flatten balls into small patties. Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Heat 1/2 cup oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add patties.
Cook 5 minutes each.
Remove and drain on paper towels.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Mix egg whites and water with fork.
Add nuts.
Mix well; let sit for 20 to 30 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients; add nuts. Spread on cookie sheet and bake for 45 minutes at 275°.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.

title: mock caesar salad
directions: Put garlic, soy sauce and lemon juice in a salad bowl and whisk thoroughly.
Add endive and romaine; toss to coat.
Sprinkle with pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Garnish with chopped tomato.

title: stokely's broccoli corn casserole
directions: Completely thaw broccoli.
Mix broccoli with corn, onion, 1/4 cup crushed crackers, egg, 2 tablespoons margarine, salt and pepper.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix together the remaining 2 tablespoons crushed crackers and 1 tablespoon butter. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pearl's chili sauce
directions: Chop up and cook until thick.
Taste as you might want to add more spices or less.

title: rotel potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a bowl, mix Ro-Tel tomatoes, Cheddar cheese soup, mushroom soup, water, onion, salt and pepper. Pour mixture over potatoes in a greased baking dish. Place margarine slice on top and bake for 1 hour or until potatoes are soft.

title: lightning cake
directions: Into a 1/2 pint cup put melted butter, eggs and vanilla.
Fill the remainder of the cup with milk.
Beat wet mixture into dry mixture.
Bake in two layer cake pans, greased and floured, for about 30 minutes in an oven of 350°.
When cool, place jelly between the two layers and sprinkle the top with powdered sugar.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix dry jello and drained pineapple, then fold in the rest of ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: chunky cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Cover; chill several hours.
Form into ball.
Roll in nuts to coat.
Serve with crackers.

title: 5-flavor pound cake
directions: Cream
butter,	oil
and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, beaten until
lemon colored.
Combine flour and baking powder and add to	creamed
mixture
with milk.
Stir in flavorings. Place in greased and floured tube pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: chicken tetraginna
directions: Cook chicken and take meat off bone.
Save broth.
In skillet fry 3 slices bacon which have been cut into pieces; fry until brown.
Add green pepper (cut fine) and onion (cut fine) and saute until tender.
To this add mushrooms, soup, olives, cheese and pimientos.
Cook noodles in chicken broth.
Add all together. Salt and pepper and serve.

title: fiesta potatoes
directions: In 10-inch skillet, combine soup, salsa and milk.
Add potatoes, stirring gently to coat.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
If desired, garnish with cherry tomatoes and fresh chives.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups or 5 servings.

title: cranberry orange relish
directions: Mix jello with boiling water; cool.
Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Mix all ingredients together and chill until solid.

title: char's creamy fudge
directions: Mix butter in 4-quart saucepan.
Add cocoa; stir until smooth. Add sugar, salt, milk and Marshmallow Creme.
Bring mix to a full boil and stir constantly for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool 20 minutes.
Beat with a wooden spoon until mix loses its gloss.
Blend in nuts.
Spread in 9 x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Cool until set.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Store in airtight container.

title: venison breakfast sausage(bulk)
directions: Take a sharp knife
and
stick	holes
in the roast and stuff each hole with
a sliver of garlic.
The holes should be about 1 1/2 to 2-inches apart like a pork roast.
Then rub the roast with lots of salt and pepper.
Flour it generously.
Put in your Dutch oven
with	1/8-inch grease and fry until golden brown on all sides.
Put on the lid and cook very slowly until tender.
No vegetables except potatoes, if you want them.

title: lipton onion soup potatoes
directions: Mix diced potatoes with ingredients.
Pour into a casserole dish, cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: buried cherry cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat margarine 30 seconds, until soft. Add sugar and beat until fluffy. Add egg and vanilla and beat well. Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and powder and salt. Gradually add to egg mixture. Shape into 1-inch balls. Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet. Press center of ball with thumb. Place cherry in center.

title: deluxe butterscotch pudding
directions: Mix all together and pat in Pyrex pan (13 x 9-inches).
Bake 15 minutes at 350° or until slightly browned.

title: sour cream coated pecans
directions: Combine the sugar and sour cream; boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and stir well.
Add pecans; mix until well coated (this hardens fast, so this has to be done quickly).
Spread on wax paper to cool and dry.
Break apart into separate nuts while still warm.

title: raisin apple muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and spices.
Combine apple, butter, egg, raisins, and add dry ingredients.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix (don't overmix).
Place in greased muffin tin.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit for juice; add tapioca to the juice.
Add vanilla pudding and bring all to a boil.
Stir constantly.
Pour over fruit while hot, then cool in refrigerator.
Add 5 to 6 bananas just before serving.

title: awesome chicken enchiladas(these are out of this world vaya can dios.)
directions: Cook chicken; dice chilies and slice olives.
Mix olives, diced chilies, sour cream, soup and 1/2 cheese.
Divide that in half.
To one half, add chicken (remove chicken from bones, tear into small bite size pieces).
Place some mixture on each tortilla; roll. Cover rolls with remaining sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° covered for 15 minutes and 15 minutes uncovered.

title: irish potato cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan and set aside.
Mix baking soda and sour cream.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, sour cream mixture, chocolate, walnuts, raisins and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, salt and ginger.	Add to creamed mixture.
Add mashed potatoes.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites and gently add to batter.
Pour into tube pan and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hr. and 30 minutes or until tester comes out clean.

title: no sugar punch(nutrasweet)
directions: Mix together.
Add large NutraSweet ginger ale before serving.

title: no salt spice
directions: Try it on baked chicken or baked potatoes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix cole slaw mix, onions, sunflower seeds, almonds or pecans and uncooked Ramen noodles.
Set aside.
Mix vegetable oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and noodles seasoning.
Pour this mixture over first mixture and toss.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Use ice cream scoop to drop mixture on cookie sheets, 6 scoops to a sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Flatten cookie before baking.
(Recipe does not call for flour.)

title: cool 'n easy pie
directions: In medium bowl, stir boiling water into gelatin 2 minutes or until dissolved.
In a separate bowl, mix cold water and ice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Stir into gelatin until slightly thickened. Remove any remaining ice.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add color, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt 3 times.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk and alternately, dry ingredients last.
Beat 2 minutes.
Fold in vinegar and soda.
Do not beat.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: five bean bake
directions: Brown meats with chopped onion; drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: baked macaroni and cheese with ham
directions: Cook macaroni according to package.
Melt margarine in saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and cook 1 minute.
Stir in flour.
Remove from heat and stir in dry mustard, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Slowly stir in milk.
Cook over medium low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and it comes to a boil. Add cheese and stir over low heat until cheese is melted and sauce is smooth.
Combine sauce and macaroni.
Add ham chunks.

title: classic potato salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, vinegar, salt, sugar and pepper.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; chill.
Makes 5 cups.

title: creamy tomato soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, soup, milk, sugar and seasonings.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in cream cheese until melted.
Serve immediately.
Can make ahead, reheat and add cheese just before serving.

title: crisp crusted baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces.
Pat dry.
Beat egg and milk in one bowl. In another bowl, mix potato flakes, garlic powder and cheese.
Roll chicken, first in egg mix, then potato flakes mixture.
Melt butter or margarine in shallow baking pan.
Roll chicken pieces in butter and place them, skin side up in pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Mix soup, broth, Bisquick, milk and butter together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350° until top is brown.

title: cheese blintzes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut the crusts off the pieces of bread and roll out very thin.
Cream together the cream cheese, egg yolks and 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread a layer of filling on each piece of bread and roll up like a jelly roll.
Combine melted butter, brown sugar and cinnamon and mix well.
Dip each roll-up into this mixture and line in a baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
These are good warm or at room temperature.
Yield: 44 blintzes.

title: oh henry bars
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Pat dough onto 13 x 9 x 3/4-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. While baking, melt chocolate chips with peanut butter.
Spread on cookies after slightly cooled.

title: crunchy caramel snack mix
directions: Combine Cocoa Puffs, Rice Chex, pretzels and peanuts.
Set aside.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Mix all ingredients until all flour is mixed in.
Let rest 30 minutes.
Brush with butter.
Knead down a few times and let rise until double in bulk.
Divide in 3 parts.
Roll out about 1/4-inch thick.
Brush with butter.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture (about 1 cup of sugar and 2 tablespoons of cinnamon). Divide into three.
Fold over and cut in 1-inch strips with a pizza cutter.
Twist and place in pan.
Brush with butter and let rise.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Ice with powdered sugar.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix together the sugar, milk, cocoa, butter, and peanut butter. Bring to a moving boil for a couple of minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and oats.
Spoon on waxed paper and let cool.

title: glazed baby carrots
directions: Place carrots in boiling water and add sugar.
Cook until tender.
Drain well.
In large skillet, combine the butter, brown sugar and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat until butter melts and ingredients are blended.
When the mixture begins to bubble, add the carrots and stir to coat.
Cook until completely glazed.

title: tv mix
directions: *Cereals of your choice can be substituted.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Blend all ingredients, adding flour and buttermilk.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Check it at 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: spinach-artichoke dip
directions: Cook spinach as directed.
Grate cheese and chop onion fine. Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Serve hot with chips.
Enjoy!

title: annie's spareribs and sauce
directions: Make sauce and let cook down a bit, approximately 1 hour on very low heat.
Bake ribs 1/2 hour plain, drain fat off.
Bake on 350°. Put sauce on and baste every 20 to 30 minutes.
Bake 1 layer about 1 1/2 hours on 350°.

title: john b. getty casserole
directions: Brown onion, meat and pepper.
Add soups, stirring until mixed and warm.
Combine noodles and 1/2 cup cheese.
Put remaining cheese on top; bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pepper muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin cups.
Melt butter in skillet with onion and peppers; cook until tender about 7 minutes, stirring often.
Cool to lukewarm.
Whisk sour cream and eggs in medium bowl.
Stir in cooled onion mixture.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, soda in large bowl.
Make well in center.
Add sour cream mixture, stirring just until blended.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 10 muffins. This is a great smelling complement to hearty soups.

title: holiday raisin carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add oil and eggs. Stir in carrots and remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown meat.
Add spices and onions.
Add soup and tomatoes. Cook spaghetti not quite done.
Mix all together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: lemon bread
directions: Beat together egg, milk, cooking oil and lemon juice.
Add flour, sugar, baking powder, lemon peel and salt.
Turn batter into two greased 6 x 3 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Cool in pans 10 minutes. Remove from pans.
Cool thoroughly.
Wrap and store overnight.

title: ritzy chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, debone and chop into bite size pieces.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Place chicken into bottom of greased casserole dish (13 x 9-inch). Top with soup mixture.
Melt margarine and combine with crushed Ritz crackers.
Add poppy seed for looks.
Top casserole with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes (covered).

title: deluxe mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes.
Whip cream cheese and sour cream.
Add onion salt and garlic salt.
Add hot boiled potatoes 2 at a time and beat in.
Add chives last.
Place in oblong casserole.
Add dollops of margarine and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Excellent with roast beef!)

title: no-fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening.
Mix together the egg, vinegar and water.
Add liquids to dry ingredients.
Divide into 4 balls. Freezes well in balls or rolled pie crusts.

title: italian style pork chops
directions: Wash pork chops and pat dry.
Season with garlic powder and season salt.
Place uncooked rice in the bottom of a 9 x 13 baking pan.
Place pork chops on top of the rice.
Top with sliced yellow onion and sliced green pepper.
Mince garlic and distribute over the top of the onion and green pepper.
Add 2 to 2 1/2 cups of water to pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for about 1 hour. Remove foil from pan and stir in can of stewed tomatoes and bake for 15 to 20 more minutes.

title: wacky no egg chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients, then combine all other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour frosting on warm cake.

title: fried squash blossoms
directions: Stir well except nuts and dates.
Add nuts and dates.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans or 1 greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: mountain man soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown meat in oil; drain.
Add celery, onion and green pepper; saute 5 minutes or until tender.
Stir in broth, tomatoes, potato, carrot, garlic salt, clove and bay leaf.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer uncovered for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Discard clove and bay leaf.
Stir in parsley.

title: miss iva's apricot jello salad
directions: Spray the container you are going to put the jello mixture in.
Mix jello and pineapple together.
Heat and stir to boiling point.
Let cool a little.
Add buttermilk.
Let it begin to congeal.
(I put mine in freezer for about 30 minutes.)
But watch it and don't let it freeze.
Fold in Cool Whip and pecans.
Let it congeal.

title: mock apricot jam
directions: Simmer the zucchini for 10 minutes.
Add sugar, lemon concentrate, crushed pineapple and Jell-O mix.
Cook until sugar is dissolved.
Put in sterilized jars and cover with melted wax.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Recipe can be reduced to half.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Add milk and peanut butter.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Freeze 2 hours before serving.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: * Nabisco mini-bites may be substituted.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Spread peanut butter on crackers as sandwiches, 2 crackers at a time.
Melt the white chocolate in double boiler.
Carefully dip peanut butter sandwiches in white chocolate.
Turn; place on waxed paper to harden.
Makes 65 cookies.

title: rotini pasta salad
directions: Boil rotini noodles until tender.
Rinse with cold water and drain noodles.
In large bowl, mix vegetables, cut up into small pieces.
Add vinegar and oil.
Add Salad Supreme and noodles.
Mix well and refrigerate until cold.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together into large ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: broccoli casserole 1
directions: Prepare broccoli according to package.
Drain and place in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Mix together milk and soup.
Pour over broccoli and cheese.
Bake at 250° for 25 minutes.
Top with onion rings, crumbled.
Bake for 10 more minutes until onion rings are browned.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients; cook for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 50.

title: sweet potato roll
directions: Beat 3 eggs on high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually add sugar; stir in sweet potatoes and lemon juice.
In another bowl stir flour, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg.
Fold into sweet potato mixture.
Spread into well greased jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Turn out on double paper sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll towel and cake together and let cool.
Unroll cake and spread with filling.

title: chocolate ice cream the old-fashioned way
directions: Combine all ingredients in an ice cream maker and mix until solid.
Works great in a hand crank ice cream maker.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: peppy spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and process cheese food, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Chill. Serve with assorted crackers.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: cinnamon apple rings
directions: Mix cucumbers and hydrated lime to water, when dissolved then place rings in lime water, let stand for 24 hours.
Drain rings, wash in cool water then pour cold water over the rinds and let set for 3 hours.
Drain and add vinegar, alum, bottle red food coloring and enough water to slightly cover, heat and simmer for two hours.
Drain and cover with vinegar, water, sugar cinnamon, pkg. of red hots.
Bring to a boil and pour over rings and keep lid on tight and let stand over night.
Drain, reheat syrup and repeat the above for three mornings.
The fourth morning, heat, put in hot jars and seal.

title: french fried onions
directions: Heat deep fat to 380°.
Slice onions and separate into rings. Put remaining ingredients into blender.
Cover and process at whip until smooth.
Dip onion rings into batter and then drop into hot fat.
Fry until golden brown.

title: mexican salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together and top with Fritos.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Grease pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Dice squash and onion in a saucepan and boil until tender. Drain excess water and mash squash and onion mixture.
In a large mixing bowl, mix mushroom soup, 1/2 cup grated cheese, 1/2 cup Ritz crackers, egg and squash and onion mixture.
Pour mixture into a casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Top cheese with remaining Ritz crackers.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: breakfast sausage quiche
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Crumble into baked pie crusts. Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Mix milk with eggs and salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and cream well again.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until slightly brown.
Yield: 70 to 75.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a 2-quart casserole dish. Cover with 3/4 cup buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple cinnamon french toast
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 baking pan with Pam.
Spread pie-sliced apples in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle apples with cinnamon.
Pour syrup over apples; spread if necessary to coat evenly.
Arrange bread slices in one layer over top of apples.
Blend eggs, milk, half and half and vanilla together and pour carefully over bread.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: precious moments lasagna
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Push to one side and saute onion. Drain fat.
Stir in 2 cans of tomato sauce, salt and oregano. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Shred cheeses together (except Ricotta). Spread 1/2 can of remaining tomato sauce in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add layer of uncooked noodles, slightly overlapping. Add half of the meat and sauce mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of cheese mixture.
Repeat with one more layer.
Add remaining noodles.
Cover with remaining tomato sauce, Ricotta and cheese. Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: glazed sweet potatoes with pears
directions: In a 2-quart microwaveproof casserole, combine sweet potatoes, margarine or butter, and 1/4 cup of the orange juice.
Cover and microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Stir mixture; cover and microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes or until crisp and tender. Add pears; cover and microwave on High 2 to 4 minutes or until fruit is tender but holds it's shape.
Stir in the walnuts; cover and let stand.

In a 1 cup glass measure, combine the water, maple syrup, cornstarch, cinnamon and remaining 1/4 cup of orange juice. Stir and microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until the mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Pour over sweet potato and pear mixture and toss gently to coat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick and easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Pour off pan drippings.
Add remaining ingredients with 2 cups of water, mixing well.
Simmer for 1 hour, stirring frequently.

title: creamy cucumber salad dressing
directions: Stir together mayonnaise, sour cream and chives or green onions in a small bowl.
Stir in the chopped cucumber.
Stir in milk to make the dressing the desired consistency.

title: enchiladas
directions: Note:
I use Old El Paso mild enchilada sauce.

title: pig eating cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, beating well.
Bake until done (according to box).
Let cool.

title: triple chocolate cake(sinfully delicious)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in ungreased oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches, with fork, scraping corners frequently, until moistened.
Stir batter vigorously with fork 1 minute. Scrape sides with rubber spatula.
Spread out batter evenly in pan.
Bake until top springs back when touched lightly in center, 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Loosen cake from sides; cut and serve directly from pan.
May serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream. Store remaining cake loosely covered in refrigerator.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Crumble crackers into pie crust.
Bring other ingredients to rolling boil and pour over crackers.
Cover with top crust.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes or until crust is slightly tan.

title: pistachio bread
directions: Mix cinnamon, sugar and walnuts.
Then mix first 6 ingredients and pour into 2 greased loaf pans, alternating with 1/2 dough, 1/2 cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine over low heat.
Mix in dry ingredients.
This will be lumpy.
Add sour cream.
Mash out lumps.
Increase heat; simmer until sauce thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add beans.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle cheese over beans.
Sprinkle crumbled crackers over cheese.
Pour remaining margarine over crackers.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Bring to boil; boil for 1 minute.
Add the 4 remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop onto waxed paper until cool.

title: frosted lemon pie
directions: Line an 8-inch pie pan with wafer crumbs.
Beat egg yolks until thick.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, water, lemon peel and juice. Cook in a double boiler until very thick, about 12 to 15 minutes. Cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add remaining sugar gradually; fold into lemon mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into pie pan lined with crumbs.
Place, unwrapped, in freezer and let harden, at least 5 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bread pieces.
Place in bread container to serve.
(Helps to make a day ahead for vegetables to soften.)

title: taco salad
directions: In a very large bowl, break up lettuce.
Put the potatoes, onion, kidney beans and cheese on top of lettuce.
Pour dressing on top.
Toss well.
Top with nacho chips.
Makes lots!

title: chili sausage supper
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir meat, onion and green pepper until meat is brown and onion is tender; drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes, or until noodles are tender, adding more water if necessary to prevent sticking.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Prepare cookie mix as package directs and spread into a 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake until golden brown (about 10 minutes). Cool completely.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until sugar is dissolved.
Spread over cooled cookies.
Drain fruits and layer over cheese mixture in the order given above.
Chill several hours or overnight for best flavor.
Any fruit combination may be used.

title: pickle picnic salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss pickles, beans, tomatoes, cauliflower and onions, set aside.
In a small bowl, mix dressing and dill weed.
Gently stir into pickle/vegetable mixture and toss to coat well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: fun fillo
directions: *Suggestions:
Can use strawberries, bananas, blueberries, melon, apples, kiwi, papaya, grapes and tangerines.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients except vanilla until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon chicken(serves 6)
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add Ricotta, sour cream and 1/2 grated cheese.
Simmer on low, stirring occasionally.
Add seasonings.
After 30 minutes, add remaining grated cheese and 1/3 cup of milk (if too thick).

title: ranch style chicken
directions: Mix Bisquick, salt, pepper and paprika together in a paper sack; set aside.
Cut up fryer and dip in 1/2 cup diluted canned milk (1/2 water and 1/2 milk).
Place in sack with Bisquick mixture; shake until coated.
Melt shortening in a rectangular pan in oven.
Add chicken, skin side down.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 425°.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken, cut into cubes and place in 8 x 8-inch dish. Combine sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Crush Ritz crackers.
Pour in melted margarine and poppy seed.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake until lightly brown in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexico-tequila salad
directions: Shake reserved pineapple syrup, 1/4 cup lime juice, the sugar, tequila, oil and 1/4 teaspoon salt in a tightly covered container. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: roll out cookies
directions: Sift flour and salt on wax paper.
Beat butter, sugar, almond extract, egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture.
Shape into 2 balls.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill at least two hours.
Roll out to desired shape.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool, then add icing.
Decorate, if desired.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water; add 1 cup hot water and 7-Up.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and bananas after partially set.
Chill until firm.

title: banana pudding
directions: Make pudding as directed
on
package.
Fold
in
Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Layer this mixture with bananas and vanilla wafers.

title: spicy shrimp(crock-pot)
directions: In crock-pot, melt butter, then add spices. Add shrimp last. Simmer on low for 25 minutes.

title: ham-potato bake
directions: Layer half the potatoes and half the carrots in a 2-quart casserole. Stir together cubed ham, mushroom soup, 1/2 cup shredded cheese, milk, onion and pepper. Pour half the ham mixture over potatoes and carrots in casserole. Repeat layers. Combine soft bread crumbs, the 1/2 cup shredded cheese and melted butter; sprinkle over casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° until heated through, about 45 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix soups and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Mix crushed crackers and melted margarine.
Spread over top of casserole. Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: knox perfection salad
directions: Mix gelatine, sugar and salt in pan; add 1 1/2 cups of water. Stir over low heat, stirring until gelatine is dissolved.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining water, vinegar and lemon.
Chill until unbeaten egg white consistency.
Fold in vegetables and turn into mold or Pyrex dish (2 x 7 x 9-inch).

title: coconut surprise cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Bake in an oblong pan until done.
Pierce the cake with a fork, then pour the condensed milk and cream of coconut on cake.
Allow the liquids to run through the cake.
When the cake is cool, spread on the pineapple, then the whipped topping.
Sprinkle the coconut on top and add the cherries and pecans.
Place the cake in the refrigerator.
The cake is better if cold.
Keep refrigerated.

title: brown sugar frosting
directions: Melt butter.
Add milk or cream and brown sugar.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add powdered sugar.
Beat well.
Cool slightly.
Add flavoring (vanilla).
Add powdered sugar and beat well.

title: free vegetables soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in large stock pot.
Start with 1/2 gallon of water.
Add herb to season (your choice).
Cook until it is almost tender.
It's better if veggies are crisp, not soft.

title: chicken-scalloped potatoes
directions: In casserole dish, mix potatoes, soup and milk until well coated. Bake at 350° for 1
1/2 hours.

title: au gratin potatoes(spicy)
directions: Scrub potatoes; leave skins on and slice in fairly thin slices.
Set aside in casserole dish.
Heat Mozzarella and American cheese in saucepan on stove.
When cheese begins to melt, add approximately 1/2 cup milk and stir until cheese is saucy. Add Cheddar and/or any other cheese, more milk and stir (adding more milk if necessary).
Stir in 1/2 stick butter and all seasonings.
Pour cheese sauce (fairly thin consistency) over potatoes and mix well.
Bake at 375° for one hour.

title: mini sausage biscuit sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Cut sausages lengthwise into quarters. Cut each quarter into 5 pieces. Remove biscuits from can and separate. Using fingers, flatten each biscuit to about 4 inches. Place small amount of honey, barbecue sauce or ketchup in center of biscuit. Top with 1 piece of sausage. Bring up edges of biscuit and pinch together to seal top of sausage. Place on baking sheet and bake 10 minutes until browned.

title: festive corn 'n broccoli dish
directions: In a heavy saucepan (2-quart), melt butter.
Add remaining ingredients; stir to blend.
Cover.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until crispy tender, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in casserole.
Pour uncooked macaroni into melted butter.
Stir until butter coats macaroni.
Cut cheese in small pieces.
Add salt, pepper, cheese and cold milk to macaroni. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not stir while baking.
When finished, it is golden brown and creamy.

title: tasty red apple salad(this is a great tasting apple salad.)
directions: Make syrup by boiling sugar and water.
Place diced apple pieces in baking dish and pour syrup over them.
Toss in red hots and bake until tender.
Leave the apples in the syrup until cold. Mix cheese, nuts and marshmallows and combine with the apples and a bit of syrup.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ellis and ruby's chocolate icing
directions: Boil Karo, cocoa, sugar and milk for 7 minutes in a heavy pot. Stir constantly.
After 7 minutes, add butter and vanilla. Remove from heat and beat by hand until creamy.
Spread on cake.

title: golden pumpkin pickle
directions: Tie spices in double thickness of cheese cloth.
Combine sugar and vinegar in large sauce pan
Add spice bag, bring to boiling. Add pumpkin, cook until tender.
Remove spice bag.
Spoon pumpkin into sterile jars.
Cover with syrup, seal at once.
Makes 5 pints.

title: trio cheese ball
directions: Beat the cheeses until fluffy.
Beat in onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in pecans.
Cover and chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Mold mixture into 1 large ball.
Roll in chopped nuts. Cover and chill.

title: magic biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast that has been dissolved in hot water.
Put in oiled bowl in refrigerator.
You don't have to wait for rising.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, Jell-O, lemon juice and water. Cook until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Wash and stem strawberries; dry.
Put strawberries in cooked pie shells and pour thickened mixture on top.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Serve with whipped topping and garnish with halved or whole berries.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt and nuts.
Mix sugar with strawberries to coat them.
Add eggs, vanilla and salad oil to strawberries and sugar, then add to dry ingredients.
Mix just until liquids coat the flour mixture.
Pour into greased loaf pan (9 x 5-inch) and bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: never fail kraut
directions: Chop cabbage; put in jar.
Heat remaining ingredients until salt and sugar are well dissolved.
Pour over chopped cabbage; seal.
Ready to eat in 4 to 6 weeks.

title: very simple herbed buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in the largest bowl you have and stir until well mixed and blended together.
Cut in the shortening until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and cool spaghetti.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss together.
Chill in covered dish 24 hours.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Cream oil and sugar, then add egg.
Mix dry ingredients with milk.
Beat well.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
You may add nuts, dates, apples, prunes or anything you want to add.
Makes one dozen.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine pumpkin, salt, sugar and spices.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix well and pour into shells.
Bake for 50 minutes until knife or toothpick can be removed clean after sticking in the middle of the pie.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Mix together eggs and sugar.
Add flour, cocoa and vanilla. Melt margarine and add to mixture.
Put in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; check occasionally.

title: apple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, cinnamon and soda together.
Mix sugar, eggs and oil together.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add apples (large chunks) and nuts or raisins last. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 50 minutes.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Make balls with ice cream scoop. Bake 45 minutes at 350°, covered.
Pour off excess fat.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and peanut butter.
Add vanilla and salt. Add eggs, soda, oats and chocolate chips.
Spoon drop.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields about 70 cookies.

title: corn bread quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into baking pan.
Add more cheese on top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in 400° oven.
Cut into squares.
Serve hot or cold.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Cream margarine
and
sugar;
mix all together (will be sticky).
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Stir and cook over medium heat to a soft ball stage, 234°.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Spread into a greased 9-inch pan.
Cool; cut.

title: crispy oven-fried mexican chicken
directions: In large shallow pan (not aluminum), combine V-8 juice and hot sauce.
Add chicken and marinate for 30 minutes.
Drain chicken. Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray a baking sheet with nonstick spray. In a large plastic bag, combine remaining ingredients.
Place chicken parts, a few at a time, in bag and shake to coat chicken. Transfer coated chicken pieces to baking sheet.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over chicken.
Bake until chicken is tender and crisp, about 1 hour.

title: peppermint cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill dough several hours.
Roll in balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Cookies will not brown and will still look doughy.

title: april showers punch
directions: In a punch bowl, combine punch and frozen lemonade.
Stir until blended.
Slowly stir in chilled club soda.
Makes ten 8 ounce cups.

title: liver pate
directions: Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Remove onion and add livers.
Saute slowly until just cooked through, but not brown. Remove livers from butter and cool.
Reserve butter.
Mash livers with fork or sturdy pastry blender.
Mash or grind egg.
Combine mashed livers, eggs, onion and butter.
Add just enough salad dressing to make a firm paste. Form into ball and refrigerate. Serve with miniature rye slices or crackers.

title: beef consomme rice
directions: Mix all of the ingredients into a microwavable bowl (do not dilute the soup).
Bake in microwave for 10 minutes or conventional oven for 30 minutes.
Times may vary from oven to oven.
Cook until done.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Cut tortillas into bite sized pieces and put half into 9 x 13 pan. Add layer of chicken, cheese, onion and half of the soup/milk mixture; repeat. Sprinkle cheese on top and refrigerate 24 hours. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus.
Add milk and mushroom soup.
Place in casserole dish.
Add sliced eggs on top.
Cover with grated cheese and bread crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Mix all the ingredients and add the browned hamburger meat.
Bring to a good boil and then cook on low for at least 1 hour.
We like a lot of garlic in this.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and saute onions.
Drain fat.
Add rest of ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with grated cheese, sour cream and corn chips.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread mix, corn, eggs and milk.
Grease a 13 x 10 x 2-inch pan.
Pour half of batter in pan.
Split peppers open, run under cold water.
Remove seeds.
Lay flat on top of batter. Spread cheese over peppers.
Cover cheese with remaining batter. Bake 40 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Prepare dressing as directed and pour over veggies, marinate overnight.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients with mixer, adding cocoa and flour last.
Beat well.
Pour into loaf or Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 or 50 minutes.

title: roast beef
directions: Place the roast in a baking pan. Cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 500° for 1 hour. Season according to your preference. Continue baking at 200° for 2 hours.

title: toasted almond party spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients. Spread onto a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 15 minutes, stirring after 8 minutes. Makes 2 1/2 cups spread.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Ingredients will be layered in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare pudding mix by package directions and set aside.
First Layer:
Mix nuts, flour and margarine, then pat into bottom of lightly oiled pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool.

title: raisin carrot jello salad
directions: Grate peeled carrots to make 1 1/2 cups.
Chop celery to make 1 1/2 cups; add drained pineapple, raisins and some nuts.
Add to lemon and lime jello, made as usual, only add drained pineapple juice to cold water.
Set jello until slightly firm, then add carrots and rest of ingredients.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add flour, stirring until smooth. Cool 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk and chicken broth; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt, garlic powder and basil.
Add broccoli and cover; cook over medium heat for 15 minutes or until broccoli is done.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Prepare topping by mixing fat, flour, cinnamon, sugar and nuts.
Next, mix fat and flour.
Beat together egg, sugar and milk.
Combine with flour by stirring until smooth for about 1/2 minute.
Then beat vigorously for 1/2 minute.
Spread in a lightly greased 8 x 8-inch deep cake pan.
Finally, sprinkle topping mixture on batter.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 22 minutes.

title: cheeseburger mac
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Over medium heat, heat through.
Makes 6 cups or 4 servings.

title: broccoli-buttermilk soup
directions: Combine the broccoli, onion, garlic and shallot in steamer basket and steam over boiling water until broccoli is tender, about 12 minutes.
Transfer vegetables to a food processor or blender and blend until pureed.
Then with the motor running, slowly pour in the buttermilk.
Don't overprocess the soup or it will be too frothy.

title: caramel fudge(use microwave)
directions: Cook butter until it melts.
Add brown sugar and milk.
Cook on Full power 2 to 3 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Gradually stir in powdered sugar and nuts.
Press mixture into a buttered 8-inch cake pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Yield:
5 dozen.

title: cloverleaf bran rolls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add remaining ingredients.
Use enough flour to make a soft dough (sticky).
Cover bowl and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Punch down and shape into balls.
Dip balls in butter and place 3 in each cup of a muffin pan that has been well greased. Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 16 to 18 rolls.

title: leo's stuffed peppers
directions: Brown beans and onions; add remaining ingredients (not pepper). Parboil peppers. Cook quickly to evaporate juice.
Stuff peppers with mixtures and bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6. May freeze.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package.
Cut up cheese in cubes. Save a few slices for top of bowl.
Mix cheese, tomato soup, noodles, parsley, salt and pepper together.
Put in buttered dish. Cover with foil.
Cook at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Uncover.
Layer leftover cheese on top and cook 10 minutes until cheese melts.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk. lemon juice, and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into graham cracker crust pie shell. Refrigerate for one hour.
Top with favorite pie filling.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour and 1/4 cup powdered sugar. Press in ungreased baking pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch, building up 1/2-inch sides.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: chicken almond salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water; dissolve over hot water.
Cool slightly and combine with mayonnaise, whipped cream and salt. Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill in individual molds until firm.
Unmold on crisp lettuce.
Yields 6-8 servings.

title: quick cheeseburger bake
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in soup, vegetables and milk.
Stir in Bisquick mix and water in bowl. Spread evenly in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread beef mixture over batter; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: butter chops
directions: Season chops with all the ingredients, except butter.
In large skillet brown chops on both sides, using very little oil if any.
Drain off fat.
Place chops in baking dish.
Add drained kraut over top with pats of butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender and brown.
Serve hot.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour in melted margarine and spread around so it covers the bottom of pan completely.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into small balls. Put on baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Crush cookies with rolling pin or in food processor.
Mix butter with crumbs and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 1/2 of Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Place over crust. Mix pudding with 3 cups milk.
Pour over above mixture.
Cover with remainder of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: country pork rib casserole
directions: Salt and pepper ribs. Dredge in flour. Brown in 1/4 cup of oil. Put in baking dish. Peel and quarter potatoes and carrots. Place between ribs. Add 1 can water to soup. Pour over. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, and vanilla.
Blend well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt gradually to creamed mixture.
Stir in oatmeal, nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonfuls on well-greased cookie sheet. Put in a 350° oven and bake for 10 minutes.

title: sedrie's casserole
directions: Saute 1 medium chopped onion in 3 tablespoons of butter.
Add, heating through, but not browning the ground beef, salt and pepper.
Spread in a 2-quart baking dish.
Add 3 cups coarsely shredded cabbage.
Cover with meat mixture.
Top with 3 more cups coarsely shredded cabbage.
Pour over the top the condensed tomato soup.
Bake covered at 350° in moderate oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Note:
Can use canned gravy instead of packaged gravy, but cut back on the water to 1/4 cup.

title: spiritual cake
directions: Season to taste with 1 Kings 10:12.
Follow Solomon's prescription for a good boy in Proverbs 23:14.
Good any day of the week.

title: aunt florence's moist chocolate cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into bowl.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Mix well, then add hot water and mix again.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Most ingredients are approximate, depending on how many guests are to be served.
This recipe can be altered to stuff the chicken breasts depending on what you have in the fridge. Some suggestions:
chopped cooked spinach, parmesan cheese, blue cheese, scallions, baby shrimp, asparagus, dried cranberries and sage, stuffing, herbs and whatever else inspires you.

title: veg-all casserole
