directions: Place Veg-All in small casserole dish with cheese and margarine; stir well.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot appetizer
directions: Blend together all ingredients except walnuts.
Pat in shallow baking dish.
Spread nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve hot.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all together with mixer on medium until well blended. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: spicy beef dip
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients in skillet until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender.
Stir in next 4 ingredients.
Cover and simmer gently for 10 minutes.
Spoon off excess fat.
Remove from heat.
Add cheeses.
Heat and stir until cheeses are melted and well combined.
Keep warm in chafing dish and serve with chips or crackers.

title: cape cod dip
directions: In bowl, stir cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in soup, garlic powder, Worcestershire and Tabasco sauce.
Cover; refrigerate until serving time, at least 2 hours.
Serve with crackers, chips or vegetables for dipping.

title: broccoli nut casserole
directions: Mix ingredients, chill and serve.
If doubling recipe, use only 1 1/2 amounts of spices (sugar, vinegar, mayonnaise and salt) or you'll have too much sauce.
Delicious!!

title: pralines
directions: In large boiler, stir sugar, syrup, baking soda and milk. Bring to a boil over medium heat until mixture turns a rich brown and reaches soft ball stage (stir constantly).
Remove from heat and add nuts, vanilla and margarine.
Continue to stir until mixture begins to cool and thicken.
Drop spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: black forest dump cake
directions: Drain pineapple and keep juice; spread pineapple in lightly greased baking dish. Add pie filling. Sprinkle cake mix on top of filling. Add pecans. Combine melted margarine and pineapple juice and pour over top of all. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Let cool and then spread on whipped topping.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Cook sausage until done.
Brown.
Drain well. Spoon over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, half and half cream.
Mix well and pour over cheese. Cover and chill overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking. Bake casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: golden apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg; toss with apples.
Toss together 1 cup cheese with 2 tablespoons flour; mix with apple mixture.
Place mixture in pie shell.
Combine 1/3 cup brown sugar, 1/3 cup flour and dash of nutmeg; cut in margarine until forms coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle over apple mixture.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle the rest of the shredded cheese over warm pie before serving.

title: milky way icing
directions: Melt butter and candy together in a heavy saucepan.
Stir constantly over low heat until mixture is fully melted and smooth. Beat in vanilla and sugar.
Spread on warm cake while icing is warm and pliable.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: mexican breakfast
directions: Shred the tortillas and fry in oil until crispy. Add onions, green pepper and tomato. Pour eggs over pan mixture. Cook until set. Serve with hot sauce.

title: easy enchiladas!
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef in 1 cup water.
Add taco seasoning and 1/2 jar of salsa.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Heat tortillas per package directions.
Spoon mixture into wraps and roll.
Put into baking pan, seam side down.
Pour leftover filling and other half of salsa over top.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese is slightly browned. Enjoy with lettuce, tomatoes and sour cream!

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Chop onion, chestnuts, pimientos; add balance of ingredients.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Be sure and use Hellmann's mayonnaise - no other. This can be divided and part frozen for later.
If you are going to freeze, do not cook.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Place pudding mix in 1 1/2-quart micro-proof bowl.
Stir in milk.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes; stir well.
Microwave until mixture boils, stirring at 1 minute intervals.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: strawberry cheesecake pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar. Add sour cream and vanilla. Fold in whipped topping. Spread layer of glaze over bottom of crust. Place sliced strawberries on glaze and cover with remaining glaze. Gently spread cream cheese mixture over berries. Cover and let chill for at least 4 hours before serving.

title: meringue
directions: For one (9-inch) pie:
Beat egg whites with vanilla and cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff and glossy peaks form and all sugar is dissolved. Spread meringue over hot filling, sealing to edge of pastry.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pizza bake
directions: Brown hamburg, onion and green peppers.
Drain grease off. Boil noodles and drain.
In 9 x 12-inch cake pan, mix hamburg mix, noodles, cheese soup and pizza sauce together.
Sprinkle top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Cut and serve hot.

title: strawberry cream filling
directions: Pour soda in small pan, sprinkle gelatin over to soften. Bring to boil.
Stir to dissolve.
Pour into blender.
Add lemon juice, salt and cottage cheese.
Blend until smooth.
Add sweetener to taste.
Refrigerate until thick.
Blend again for approximately 10 seconds.
Gently fold in berries.
Spoon into pie crust or serving dish.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: pizza dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with Fritos.

title: smoked sausage with black-eyed peas
directions: Soak peas overnight.
Add salt pork to peas; cover with water and cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Add the next 13 ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Add sausage.
Cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Serve over rice. Great with French bread and salad.

title: bo's potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins.
Chill.
Peel and grate in casserole. Over low heat, melt butter and cheese.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream, chives, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes and stir lightly.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: anise drop cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together several times. Beat eggs at low speed until frothy.
Turn mixer to medium; beat 10 minutes longer.
Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time; takes about 7 minutes.
Turn mixer to low speed.
Add dry ingredients slowly; beat 15 minutes longer.
Blend in anise.
Drop from teaspoon onto 5 to 6 greased cookie sheets.
Work quickly!
Allow to stand in a cool place for several hours or overnight.
Top of cookie should be dry to touch.
Bake at 325° for about 12 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook bacon; drain fat and break into small pieces. Mix salad dressing, sugar and vinegar. In a large bowl, add broccoli, raisins, celery, bacon and sunflower seeds. Pour dressing over mixture and serve.

title: pichin pig cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Oil and flour 3 round cake tins. Put batter in tins and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done. Remove from oven and cool.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil, debone and dice chicken.
Cook onion, celery and bell pepper in small amount of water.
Drain.
Combine with soups, garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce and dash of black pepper.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth; drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in dish.
Cover with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until thoroughly heated and cheese is melted.

title: busy day beef stew
directions: Place roast in a slow cooker; sprinkle with soup mix, browning sauce, if desired, salt and pepper.
Pour water over meat. Cover and cook on low for 8 hours.

title: large amount of lemonade
directions: Squeeze lemons on the sugar and let set for a while. Then add to water and stir, leaving the lemons in the water.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl in the order given.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8 inch layer pans.
Bake 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and remove from pans.
Best with a butter frosting.

title: fried alligator
directions: Soak meat in salt water overnight in refrigerator.
Drain and pat dry.
Sprinkle with lemon fish seasoning and pepper.
Roll in flour and fry in oil until brown.

title: sausage rice bake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put all in a covered, greased casserole. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: raccoon with red wine and garlic
directions: Clean raccoon well.
Cut into 8 sections.
Parboil in water to cover.
Add whole onion, 6 cloves garlic, bay leaves, 1 cup chopped celery and 1 teaspoon peppercorns.
Cover.
Cook over low heat for 2 hours.
Remove meat from kettle and drain.
Set aside.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into casserole and bake.
May add French fried onions on top the last 10 minutes. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: nutmeat
directions: Work peanut butter and water together; mix tomato juice and flour until smooth.
Combine with peanut butter mixture all remaining ingredients.
Steam in buttered double boiler for 5 1/2 hours.
Cool.
Turn onto plate.
Slice and serve cold or fry and serve with tomato gravy.

title: quick pork chops
directions: You will need foil.

title: minted potatoes and peas
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and cook on High for 5 to 9 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender, stirring once.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar, salt, flour and egg yolks well.
Gradually add milk and blend well.
Add butter and cook over medium heat until it thickens.
Set aside until you dissolve other 1/2 cup sugar in iron skillet over medium heat.
Gradually add this to other mixture, beating with mixer as you mix.
Pour this into a baked pie shell and set into the oven a few minutes to set up, then beat egg whites and sweeten to taste.
Put back into oven and brown.

title: squash delight
directions: Combine stuffing mix and melted butter in a medium bowl, stirring well. Spoon 2 cups stuffing mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Set baking dish and remaining stuffing mixture aside.

title: squash casserole #2
directions: Clean yellow squash well and cut into 1/2-inch slices and boil or steam until tender.
Cool slightly, drain and mash.
Add onion, pimentos, cheese, cracker crumbs, egg, butter, milk and salt to taste.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes in greased baking dish.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream the butter well.
Add sugar, a small amount at a time, beating until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Divide into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: beef and mozzarella bake
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook beef, basil, black pepper and garlic powder until browned, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, melted butter, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 2 eggs.
Spread in a greased and floured 15 x 10-inch or 13 x 9-inch pan. This mixture will be tacky.

title: delicious fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding with pineapple juice, instead of milk.
Cook pudding before adding fruits.

title: jiffy baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2 quart saucepan.
Cook on top burner, stirring constantly about 15 to 20 minutes until onion is cooked and juice is thick.

title: california chicken salad
directions: In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream, milk, green onion, vinegar, tarragon and salt until well mixed.
Add chicken, grapes and celery; toss gently until well combined.
Cover and refrigerate until well chilled.

title: graham cracker nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs well and add to creamed mixture.
Dust nuts with 2 tablespoons flour.
Then combine remaining flour and baking powder.
Add graham cracker crumbs and flour, alternately with milk, to batter, mixing well after each addition.
Add nuts and coconut last.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla; stir in zucchini, flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Serves 12.

title: ham-vegetable fettucini
directions: In a large pot, boil carrots, chopped broccoli and chopped cauliflower in water; boil until tender-crisp.
In saucepan, combine ham, onion, milk and cheeses.
Simmer until cheeses are melted.
If too thick, add additional milk.
Drain vegetables and place in mixing bowl.
Use large pot to boil 3 quarts of water and cook noodles 7 to 8 minutes.
Drain.
Add to mixing bowl; cover with meat mixture and stir thoroughly.
Serve.

title: quick turkey hash
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan on medium heat. Add mushrooms and onion. Saute about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in turkey, potatoes, parsley, salt and pepper.
Stir in evaporated milk. Reduce heat to low.
Heat mixture thoroughly (about 5 minutes). Makes 6 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: In large bowl toss cauliflower and lettuce together. Mix together mayo, sour cream, sugar and cheese; pour over top of lettuce and cauliflower. Top with bacon and refrigerate (toss before serving).

title: supermoist chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; put pieces of chicken in casserole dish.
Add soups, onions and celery (chopped).
Salt and pepper.
Place stuffing on top and pour 3 cups chicken broth over the top.
Place in oven and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: no cutting christmas cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then roll into 1-inch balls. Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: baked noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender (drain well).
Return noodles to pot and combine with remaining ingredients in order given.
Mix well. Bake in greased 9 x 12-inch baking pan at 350° for 1/2 hour or until lightly brown.
Let set 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut into squares. Good with ham or pork.

title: almond cake
directions: This cake flavors through if allowed to stand a day or so before serving.

title: ham rolls
directions: Combine thoroughly.
Use 1/2 cup to make individual rolls.

title: fish and corn soup
directions: Saute
onion
in
butter until soft in kettle; add potatoes, frozen
fish
and water and cover.
Simmer 30 minutes or until fish
flakes
easily
with fork and potatoes are tender. Stir in remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Serves 6.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Layer crumbled brownies in large deep glass bowl.
Layer chocolate mousse then whipped topping.
Crumble crushed candy bar of your choice.
Repeat layers and top all with chocolate chips.

title: seafood jambalaya
directions: Boil rice and set aside.
Saute onion over low heat in oil until almost brown.
Add shrimp and cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add parsley, shallots and bell pepper.
Saute 10 minutes, stirring.
Add smoked sausage and cook 10 minutes.
Add 3 cups water and cook 1/2 hour over medium heat.
Add onions and crab meat; cook 15 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add rice a little at a time, stirring steadily until all rice is in.
Heat over medium heat for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: taco dip
directions: Put together in layers in order given.
Microwave until warm. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: italian pizzelles
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add melted margarine.
Add anise or vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder to egg mixture; mix well. Drop by spoonful into pizzelle iron; heat iron first.
Pizzelles should cook in 2 or 3 minutes.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs. Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls on cookie sheet, 2-inches apart.
Sprinkle sugar on baked cookies.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Yields 100 cookies.

title: lasagna
directions: Ground beef can be substituted for the sausage.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain and mash.
Add onion, carrots, soup, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Mix well.

title: hazel's lasagna
directions: Melt butter or margarine in large skillet or Dutch oven.
Add onion and garlic and cook gently about 5 minutes.
Add ground beef.
Cook slowly, stirring frequently, until all red color disappears from meat.
Stir in tomato paste, tomatoes, salt, pepper, basil and oregano.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: kool-aid fruit punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid, water and sugar.
Mix well.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well and freeze overnight or until slushy. Serves 30 to 40.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In heavy skillet or Dutch oven, brown chicken in hot oil 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Add mushrooms, sweet peppers, onion and garlic to skillet drippings; cook until tender. Add wine and Serrano or crushed red pepper to vegetable mixture. Bring to a boiling point.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, until almost all the liquid is evaporated.
Add undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, lemon juice, basil, sugar, thyme, salt and pepper. Return chicken to pan.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes or until chicken is tender and is no longer pink.
Serve over pasta.

title: ice cream crunch
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Press mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save a little for sprinkles on top.
Slice ice cream about 1/2-inch thick.
Lay on top of mixture.
Add sprinkles on top.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: hermits
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar, molasses and egg together.
Stir in all dry ingredients.
Add raisins last and mix well.
Press evenly into ungreased 11 x 7-inch pan.
Sprinkle sugar over top.
Bake 9 minutes at 375°.
Take out of oven immediately.
Do not cook any longer.

title: freezer corn
directions: Boil
sugar
and
water.
Add
corn and cook 5 minutes. Keep stirred; let cool.	Pack in containers and freeze.	Cook in double boiler and add butter and salt.

title: pie crust
directions: Stir flour and salt into large bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry cutter or fork.
Beat together egg and vinegar; add to flour mixture.
Gradually add water and mix with hands.
Roll between waxed paper with rolling pin.

title: baked squash
directions: Wash squash.
Slice and cook in slightly salted water until tender.
Drain and mash; add all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix sugar, flour and oats together; sprinkle over sliced apples.
Slice 1 stick butter over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fat-free carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray eight jumbo muffin pan cups (3 x 1 1/2-inch) with nonstick cooking spray.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Arrange in greased 8 x 12-inch dish. Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with grated cheese. Blend crumbs with butter and sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine Ranch dressing mix, sour cream and mayo; set aside. Place half of cornbread in bottom of large bowl and top with half of beans.
Combine tomatoes, pepper and onion and put half over beans.
Layer half of the cheese, bacon, corn and salad dressing. Repeat layers, using all the ingredients, ending with dressing. Cover and chill well.

title: molasses taffy
directions: Cook sugar, molasses, vinegar and butter slowly until it forms a brittle string dropped into cold water or reaches 260°.
Stir in the soda.
Pour in buttered pan to cool.
When cool enough to handle, pull until cream colored.
Twist and cut with scissors.

title: blueberry buckle coffee cake
directions: Mix together sugar, margarine and eggs.
Stir in milk.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Stir into batter.
Mix well. Carefully blend in blueberries. Spread batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread the pineapple, juice included, in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Next, spoon the cherry pie filling on top of pineapple, then sprinkle the dry cake mix over the pineapple and pie filling. Spread the pecans over all and cut your margarine stick in slices and lay over top of pecans.
Do not stir any of the ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fat-free brownies
directions: Mix or sift dry ingredients together.
Cream sugar, egg whites, applesauce and vanilla together.
Add dry ingredients and mix together.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch nonstick pan or regular pan lightly sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp pizza
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on a pizza pan or platter.
Pour chili sauce over cream cheese. Scatter chopped green pepper and baby shrimp over chili sauce.
Chill.
Serve with a variety of snack crackers.

title: blond brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add sugar.
Stir in eggs, flour and baking powder.
Add vanilla, salt and pecans.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 minutes. Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: heavenly hamburger
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Mix sour cream and cream cheese (set aside.)
Brown meat and drain off the fat.
Put in the Prego sauce.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put a thin layer of noodles, sauce, meat, a thin layer of sour cream and cream cheese mixture, 1/2 package of each of the cheeses.
Repeat step until all ingredients are gone.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: taco soup ii
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook about 30 to 45 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: apple roll
directions: Mix flour and shortening together.
Add enough water to make dough.
Roll out thin as pie crust.
Sprinkle with chopped apples. Roll up like jelly roll and cut about 3/4-inch slices.
Lay in sheet cake pan.
Bring to a boil sugar, water, cinnamon and butter.
Pour over apple roll.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in large pot. Add onions and saute for 15 minutes over low heat, stirring occasionally. Cover pot and soak for 5 more minutes Add sugar, salt and pepper. Increase temperature to moderate and cook for 10 minutes. Add soup broth and water. Add flour or cornstarch mixed with a little broth to pot; stir until thickens. Add garlic and thyme. Bering to a boil, then simmer for 15 minutes until onions are tender. Add wine or sherry; stir. Transfer to ovenproof bowls. Place bread slice on top; sprinkle with cheeses. Put under broiler until bubbly. Add sprinkle of thyme and a splash of soup on top to serve. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix all together and let stand in refrigerator until set.

title: cedar creek seafood chowder
directions: Saute crabmeat and shrimp in small amount of butter for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve with boiled rice.
Serves 4.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Layer bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with single layer of ice cream sandwiches.
Gently press sandwiches together to form complete layer.
Follow with a layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat layers. Sprinkle pecans over top.
Now, drizzle back and forth over top with hot fudge sauce and caramel sauce.
Chill several hours. Great to make day before needed.
Enjoy!

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Boil potatoes until fork-tender. Melt cheese and soup in crock-pot. Pour in potatoes and milk; mix together. Salt and pepper to taste. Heat until warm; do not boil. Add some crumbled cooked bacon just before serving.

title: the ruby slipper cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sour cream, water and eggs in large bowl. Blend, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes until creamy. Spoon 1/3 of batter into well-greased and floured fluted tube pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 the gelatin.
Repeat layers.
Spread remaining batter over gelatin to cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until cake springs back when lightly pressed.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Remove from pan, cool on rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.
When cake is cut, it resembles a ruby slipper.

title: fresh fruit ice
directions: Soften the gelatin in the water and stir over low heat until dissolved.
Mix in the juice, sugar and sliced fruit.
Place in freezer until almost set.
Beat with an electric mixer until creamy and fluffy.
Return to freezer for a brief period.

title: goodie bar
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg. Press into a greased 9 x 13 baking pan. Mix sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese.
Sprinkle chips/nuts over cake mix then pour 2nd mixture over it. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, until golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stir all together and top with slivered almonds.
Let stand 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potatoes and herbs
directions: Combine all ingredients; put in plastic bag and shake well. Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes, turning occasionally.

title: strawberry shortcakes
directions: Mix strawberries with 1 cup sugar; let stand 1 hour.
Heat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, the baking powder and salt until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in milk just until blended.
Gently smooth dough into a ball on lightly floured cloth-covered board.
Knead 20 to 25 times.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with floured 3-inch cutter.
Place about 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Split crosswise while hot.
Spread with margarine; fill and top with cream and strawberries. Makes 6 servings.
Top with whipped cream.

title: salisbury steaks
directions: Mix 1/4 cup soup with all ingredients except water.
Shape into 6 patties.
Place in shallow dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Mix soup with water and pour over patties. Bake 10 more minutes.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix yeast and 1/2 cup lukewarm water in bowl; let stand.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, shortening and 1 cup hot water and let stand until lukewarm, then add yeast mixture to it.
Then add egg, 1/2 cup flour and beat, then add 1/2 teaspoon salt and enough flour to make a thick dough.

title: beef soup
directions: Simmer meat for a couple of hours in the 3 quarts of water with the onion, garlic, bay leaf, salt and pepper and tomatoes. Remove meat from soup; discard bones (or save for your dog if you have done).
Add vegetables of your choice (turnip, carrots, celery, potatoes) and a small head of cabbage the last half hour. Serve over noodles to make a hearty meat, or add a cup of rice the last half hour.

title: taco beef soup
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned and onion is soft.
Drain off fat.
Add water, kidney beans, tomatoes (including juices), tomato sauce and taco seasoning mix.
Simmer covered for 15 minutes.
Pass cheese, corn chips and sour cream to top each serving.
Serves 6.

title: reduced sodium beef stew
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven, over medium heat in hot oil, cook beef 1/2 at a time until browned on all sides.
In same Dutch oven over medium heat in drippings (remove meat after browning) cook onion, celery and garlic until browned, stirring occasionally.
Stir in tomatoes and next 7 ingredients.
Return meat to Dutch oven heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 1 hour stirring occasionally.
Add potatoes and carrots, cook 30 minutes longer or until meat and vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings 105 mg. sodium per serving.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda and sift. Alternate with sour cream, adding to egg mixture.
Beat about 5 minutes.
Put in cold oven; set temperature at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan bars
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour and margarine.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 15 to 20 minutes (until light tan).

title: christmas short bread
directions: Mix, drop and top with red and green cherries on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add taco seasoning, water and tomato sauce; simmer for 20 minutes.
Add hamburger mixture with lettuce, tomatoes, Cheddar cheese and onion.
Just before serving, add crushed taco chips.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: micro-cooked turkey
directions: Shake flour in large (14 x 20-inch) Reynolds oven cooking bag. For an 8 to 9-pound turkey, place bag in 13 x 9 x 2-inch microwave-safe baking dish.
Place onion and celery in bag.
Remove neck, giblets and excess fat from turkey.
Rinse, drain and pat dry.
Do not stuff and do not secure neck skin to back with skewer. Tie legs together with string.
Combine vegetable oil and browning and seasoning sauce; brush desired amount over turkey for color. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Place turkey in bag. Close bag with nylon tie; make 6 (1/2-inch) slits in top.
Insert microwave-safe meat thermometer through slit in bag into center of thigh, next to body, but not touching bone or use a quick register meat thermometer at end of cooking time.
Micro-cook on Medium (50%) power 7 to 9 minutes per pound, rotating dish every 15 minutes.
Turkey is done when thermometer registers 180°.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 5 to 8 servings.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Add brown sugar to melted oleo and cool.
Add all other ingredients and mix together.
Spread in well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: homemade chicken-noodle soup
directions: Bring broth with enough water to a boil and add egg noodles, onions, carrots and seasonings along with can of soup.
Reduce heat and simmer until vegetables are done.
You may use homemade noodles for better flavor.

title: savory jumbo shells
directions: Cook pasta using package directions; drain.
Combine next 9 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into shells.
Spread 1 cup Cheese Sauce in 9-inch baking dish.
Arrange stuffed shells in prepared dish; top with remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.
May broil for 3 to 5 minutes until brown.

title: jaw breaks
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil; cook until it comes to 325° (hard crack) on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; add coloring and flavoring.
Mix well without scraping sides of pan.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet.
Let harden enough to cut with scissors (approximately 3 minutes).

title: casserole of carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted boiling water until very tender; drain and mash.
Add onion and butter.
Separate eggs; beat yolks and add to the mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add crumbs and milk.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and pour into a buttered baking dish.
Bake in a moderate oven, 325° to 350°, for 45 to 60 minutes.
This recipe serves 8.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Stir dry ingredients to blend. Add other ingredients, stir don't beat. Bake in floured greased tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes. Test with toothpick.

title: powdered cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well and keep in an airtight container. When ready for a hot cup of chocolate, add 2 to 3 tablespoons to a cup of hot water.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. In large bowl, combine all ingredients except shell. Mix well. Pour into pastry shell. Bake 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350°. Bake 35 to 40 minutes longer. Cool. Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: pink non-alcoholic champagne
directions: Boil water and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Stir in cranberry, pineapple and orange juice.
Chill.
Add lemon-lime soda juice before serving.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Crumble bacon.
Brush individual gratin dish or casserole dish with bacon grease or butter.
Crack eggs into dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and chives.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon over eggs and then sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Pour milk over eggs.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes or until eggs are set.

title: leek dip
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Serve with fresh cut vegetables and/or crackers.

title: chocolate mint sticks
directions: Melt chocolate with oleo; set aside.
Beat eggs until frothy; add sugar and peppermint extract.
Add chocolate and oleo mixture. Add flour and salt; mix well.
Put in greased 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When cool, spread with frosting.

title: baked apples
directions: Core out middle of apples. Slice butter and stuff 1 teaspoon in apple. Fill apples with red hot candy. Bake until apples are done. I usually set my oven to 300 degrees and bake my apples for 30 minutes.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Cream together flour, margarine and sugar; then add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add buttermilk and all but 1/2 cup coconut. Pour into an unbaked pie shell and sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.
This should be a golden brown.

title: easy peanut butter chocolate fudge
directions: Melt peanut butter chips and 2 tablespoons margarine with 1 cup sweetened condensed
milk.
Remove from heat. Stir in peanuts. Spread in butter greased 8-inch square pan.
In small pan, melt chocolate chips and remaining sweetened condensed milk. Spread chocolate mixture on top of peanut butter mixture. Chill 2 hours. Cut into squares.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: gumbo new orleans style
directions: Make a roux (brown flour in cooking oil).
Saute onions.
Add all ingredients except shrimp; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 1 hour.
Add shrimp; simmer 1/2 hour.
Serve over rice; top with file gumbo.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown meat with spices and vegetables.
Add water, wine and soup; let
cook
for
a while.
Slowly add cooked rice and mix well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and pimento together.
Add chicken with soup mixture.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and mix with Ritz crackers. Add to casserole and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine breadcrumbs, 1/4 teaspoon basil, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken pieces in egg.
Dredge in breadcrumb mixture.
Coat skillet with cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot. Cook chicken until light brown.
Arrange chicken in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine tomato sauce, butter, Worcestershire sauce, oregano and garlic.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop 2 packages of beef and onions; add to cream cheese with remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Shape into ball and roll in remaining package of beef.
Serve on crackers.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter, shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended. Add egg and beat until well blended.

title: smoked sausage and black beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain water.
Add more for cooking. Slice sausage in large pieces and cook together with beans until tender.
Cook rice and set aside.
Serve sausage and beans on rice and garnish with pepper and sour cream.

title: heath bar candy
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Spread crackers over foil. Bring sugar and butter to a boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake 7 minutes at 400°.
Cool 2 minutes and spread chocolate chips over.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given and mix well.
Serve with lettuce or vegetable salad.

title: pumpkin roll cake
directions: Grease cookie sheet and line with wax paper, grease the paper, too.
Pour batter and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on a tea towel and turn cake on towel when baked.
Pull off waxed paper.
Roll cake together with towel while hot.
Cool for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, then unroll and spread with filling.

title: fried noodles(makes 6 servings)
directions: Marinate chicken breast halves in soy sauce and cornstarch for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles in boiling water until tender but firm to bite.
Drain well.
(Tip:
If not fried immediately, toss with 2 teaspoons sesame oil.)
Coat pan with vegetable oil over high heat.
Add vegetable oil; swirl to coat sides.
Add garlic; stir until fragrant, about 5 seconds.
Add chicken and stir-fry for 2 minutes or until opaque.
Add bell pepper and green onions and cook for 1 minute.
Stir in soy sauce, wine, brown bean sauce, vinegar, sesame oil and noodles.
Cook and gently toss until heated through.
Serve hot.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix together.
Store in airtight container.
Use 1/2 heaping teaspoonful per cup.
Add boiling water to each cup.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In bowl, mix thawed potatoes, onion and 1/2 of margarine.
Add cheese, sour cream, milk and soup.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Add remaining butter to coat cornflakes.
Put on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs together. Pour into a 10 X 6 baking dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: fiesta casserole
directions: Spread refried beans evenly over bottom of 2 quart, lightly greased shallow casserole dish.
Cook ground beef; drain and stir in taco seasoning mix.
Spread over beans.
Spread the soup over the meat and sprinkle the cheese over top.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 20 minutes.
This can also be heated in a microwave at medium power just until cheese melts.
Remove oven and garnish top with sour cream, olives and green onions.
Stand the tortilla chips around the edge of the dish and serve.

title: banana mallow pie
directions: Melt butter in skillet on top of stove.
Add coconut; stir until toasted.
Put in bottom of 9-inch pie plate, forming a crust.

title: sour cream
directions: Place warm water in bowl; add dry milk and mix well.
Add vinegar a few drops at a time, while stirring milk mixture.
Mix until smooth; set in fridge a few hours to thicken.

title: million dollar pies
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice together until well blended.
Add pecans, Cool Whip and strawberries; pour into shells.
Cover and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: aunt mibs zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add all ingredients.
Add nuts last.
Raisins are optional.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in a 9-inch greased loaf pan.

title: ham dish
directions: Cut ham into bite size pieces and set aside.
Cook noodles and set aside.
Saute onions and bell peppers in margarine until brown.
Add ham, milk and cream of chicken soup.
Let mixture come to a boil.
Pour mixture over cooked noodles.

title: choc-oat-wheat drops
directions: Cream butter and sugars, add egg and vanilla and beat until fluffy.
Mix flour with salt and soda.
Stir into creamed mixture, blending well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated 375° oven 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.
Remove at once from pan and cool on rack. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine ingredients and heat until butter and sugar dissolve. Cool and pour over chicken wings (20 to 30).
Marinate 2 hours, turning. Put in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn them over halfway.

title: potato casseroleroswell, new mexico
directions: Defrost hash browns.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Top with 2 cups crushed cornflakes mixed with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can add canned chicken or ham cut in pieces.

title: fresh lemonade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill and serve with ice.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and mix in sugar, corn syrup, melted margarine and vanilla. Stir well, then mix in pecans and pour into deep dish pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Fill coffee mugs one at a time with cider (one mug equals one serving).
Add 1 cinnamon stick, three whole cloves and 1 teaspoon sugar for each mug of cider.
Bring cider and spices to boil, then simmer.
Serve hot.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Set in a pan of water.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach and berry salad
directions: Bring medium pot of water to boil.
Add peaches and blanch 30 seconds; drain.
Transfer to bowl and cover with cool water until cooled; drain.
Peel peaches and slice.
Place in medium bowl.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix to blend.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini in boiling water until tender; drain and let stand to cool.
Add the remainder of ingredients and mix with creamy Italian dressing.
Cover and refrigerate for about 1 hour before serving.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix everything well, but cheese.
Pour 1/2 into greased pan. Cover with shredded cheese.
Pour remainder of batter over cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: white chocolate chip macadamia nut cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside. Combine butter, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and water.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: gazpacho
directions: Put veggies in food processor or blender and blend to desired chunkiness, not too fine.
Add juice, Tabasco and vinegar and mix. (I just pour veggies into pitcher/container and add liquid.) Chill very well.
Serves about 8.

title: mexican salad
directions: On a large tray (or platter) spread refried beans, avocado mixed with sour cream, a layer of cheese, black olives, lettuce and tomato.
Spread remainder of Cheddar cheese over top.
Place nacho chips on all sides.
Serves a large crowd, 10 to 20.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream the butter with sugar. Add beaten eggs. Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Add pineapple and adjust batter with more flour or juice until batter is firm but moist.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased pan. Watch carefully; the bottoms burn easily.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Frost.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy (eggs should be at room temperature before beating).
Gradually add sugar and continue beating until stiff.
Add salt and vanilla; mix well.
Add pecans and remaining ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop cookies by spoonful on ungreased foil-covered cookie sheet.
Place cookies in oven and immediately turn oven off.
Leave cookies in closed oven overnight.
Yields 2 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Whisk together last 3 ingredients.
Toss salad with dressing about one-half hour before serving.
Refrigerate.

title: crock-pot macaroni
directions: Mix together.
Put in crock-pot for 3 hours on low.

title: apple brownies
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Beat in dry ingredients. Fold in nuts and apples.
Put in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: jello poke cake(good light summer dessert!)
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool cake in pan for 15 minutes, then prick with fork at 1/2-inch intervals. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add orange juice (or water); pour carefully over warm cake.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Garnish as desired.
(Cool Whip for frosting is great!)

title: cornbread dressing casserole
directions: Take chicken off bones.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Mix with dressing or serve separate.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: chili and cheese roll-ups
directions: Take one egg roll wrap.
Place hot or mild green chilies and cheese of choice into egg roll.
Wrap mixture together and deep fat fry until golden brown.
Make sure to lightly moisten egg roll wraps when folding.

title: tasty short ribs
directions: In Dutch oven, brown meat in hot oil; add onions.
Blend together tomato sauce, 1 cup water, brown sugar, vinegar, salt, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over meat.
Cover and simmer 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Serve with noodles.

title: round steak with rich gravy
directions: Sprinkle meat with flour and pound into meat.
Cut meat into serving size pieces.
Brown meat in shortening, approximately 15 minutes.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over meat.
Mix water and soup. Pour over meat.
Cover tightly and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.
(Sometimes a little water must be added during cooking.)

title: soap flake finger paints
directions: Mix soap flakes and enough water to give the consistency of whipped cream.
Beat with a rotary beater until creamy.
Add food coloring for different colors.

title: spoon rolls(makes 24 to 30 rolls)
directions: Mix flour, sugar and yeast.
Add beaten egg, water and oil. Mix until it looks like paste.
Pour in muffin tins.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
(Batter can be stored in refrigerator for up to 5 days.)

title: 8-layer casserole
directions: One-half hour preparation, 15 minutes cooking.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: In a large kettle,
saute celery and onion in margarine 5 minutes.
Add bread
cubes, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning. Toss lightly.
Stir
in
chicken broth and chicken.
Mix well. Turn into
greased,
shallow
baking dish.
Over medium heat, brown bread crumbs in 2 tablespoons margarine;
sprinkle over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bachelor's buttons
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Stir in eggs and add vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Stir into mixture.
Mix thoroughly. Drop by teaspoons on greased baking sheet.
Place 1/2 cherry on each button.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: harry kellenberger baked beans(picnic size recipe)
directions: Combine all ingredients in large baking dish (2 to 2 1/2-quart).
Bake 6 to 7 hours or longer at 275°.
Stir occasionally.

title: oven kalua pork
directions: Rub rock salt and liquid smoke into pork surface. Wrap meat in ti leaves. Enclose in heavy aluminum foil. Bake, covered, at 375° about 4 hours or roast in crock-pot for 6 to 8 hours.
Shred meat into bite size pieces and serve with roasting liquid.
For a different flavor, substitute banana, taro or spinach leaves for ti leaves.

title: cavender's salad
directions: Mix all, except dressing, in a large bowl.
Add dressing and toss.

title: acini de pepe(macaroni fruit salad)
directions: Bring 6 quarts water to boil.
Add macaroni and cook 5 to 8 minutes or until tender.
Drain with a fine sieve and set aside in large bowl.
Drain juices from pineapple and oranges into the top of a double boiler pan so the "pudding" does not stick.
Add the drained fruit to the macaroni.
Add sugar, eggs and flour to the juices.
Over medium heat, stirring constantly, cook until the ingredients become the consistency of pudding.
Remove from heat and add the macaroni.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight. Before serving the next day, stir in the Cool Whip.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: peter pan cookies
directions: Combine shortening, salt and peanut butter, mixing well.
Add sugars and cream.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Mix flour with soda and add.
Make ridges with a fork dipped in water.
Bake at 325° in convection oven 12 minutes.
Yield: 400 (2 1/2-inch) cookies. Use #40 scoop.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix together; pour into shell and bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Sift all ingredients together and store in two 3 pound coffee cans.
For each serving, fill a cup 1/3 to 1/2 full with mix and add boiling water.
Stir and serve hot.

title: sesame breadsticks
directions: Shape each roll from package into a pencil-like rope 10 inches long.
Brush with water; sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sesame seed. Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes. Makes 10 breadsticks.

title: no sugar applesauce cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or spread in a 9 x 6-inch rectangular pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes for bar cookies.

title: sinful lemon cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Use 1 teaspoon of dough rounded into a ball and flattened for each cookie.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until very lightly brown.
Cool.
Put 2 cookies together with lemon filling and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: taco dip
directions: In a bowl, cream together sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning.
Spread mixture onto serving plate.
Pour salsa sauce over and spread evenly.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Combine melted butter with pecan sandies and press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix together cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Spread over the crust.
Top with blueberry pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: creamed beef
directions: Brown ground beef, garlic and onion.
Do not pour off fat. Add flour and 1/2 cup milk and stir.
Add seasoning.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: leftover meat pie
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add flour, stock and seasonings.
Cook until thick, then simmer about 5 minutes.
Add meat and vegetables.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon and set aside.
In same pan, brown hamburger meat and onion; drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: quick hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in the cooking oil.
Place potatoes in greased 2 to 3-quart baking dish.
Place carrots on top of potatoes. Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle rice over carrots.
Spread hamburger over rice; slice onion over meat.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
May be prepared and refrigerated until ready to bake.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain all beans well.
Rinse kidney beans.
Combine all ingredients and let marinate at least overnight in refrigerator. It is even better after 2 or 3 days.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: beef and cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburg and onion until onion is limp.
Drain and mix with Cheez Whiz.
Dip nacho or tortilla chips.

title: overnight chicken hot dish
directions: Combine all ingredients and put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight. Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans; place in casserole dish.
Mix milk, grated cheese, salt and pepper; pour over green beans.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 45 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle the onion rings over top.
Pour melted margarine over; bake 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: old england poppy seed cake
directions: Cream oil, eggs, milk and lemon juice together.
Add all dry ingredients.
Blend until smooth.
Fold in poppy seed.

title: perfect beef rib roast
directions: Preheat oven to 500° for 15 minutes.
Turn down oven to 375°. Put in roast 1 hour.
When hour is up, turn oven off.
Leave it off for 2 hours.
Do not open oven door.
This is the secret to this method of roasting.
If you open the door, roast will not turn out correctly.
Stop here for rare roast.
For medium and well down, turn the oven back to 375° for 20 to 30 minutes. Enjoy, 20 minutes for medium, 30 minutes for well done.

title: cucumber - green bean salad
directions: Bring first four ingredients to boil and pour over vegetables while mixture is still hot.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Pack firmly into vanilla wafer box.
Secure box with string.
Place in freezer for 7 days. Slice and serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, stir all ingredients together until well mixed.
Drop from teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until done.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter together.
Stir often or cheese will settle.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter to hot cheese mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Add 10x sugar and vanilla. Mix well and spread into a greased pan.
Chill, then cut.
May add nuts or any type of chocolate for variation.
Makes 6 pounds.

title: macaroni chicken salad
directions: Mix all or any of the ingredients or any others may be substituted for each person's own taste.
Combine and chill.
May be made the day before.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook diced potatoes in a Dutch oven in a small amount of water until soft.
Add broccoli that has been chopped and onions.
Season with pepper and Season-all.
Add water and boil 15 minutes.
Melt butter in a saucepan and add flour, this should look like thick paste.
Pour into soup a little at a time and stir with a wire whisk.
Cook until the soup is reduced to a semi-thick consistency.

title: irish potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and onion.
Chop in large pieces.
Cover with water in saucepan; boil until soft.
Cool slightly; put through food processor or blender.
Return to saucepan with milk; bring to boil.
Season to taste.
Add the butter.
Serves 6.
Serve sprinkled with parsley, if desired.

title: grilled red snapper
directions: Combine oil, salt and pepper (to taste) in a shallow dish. Add fish. Marinate for at least 1 hour. Turn once. Drain fish, reserving marinade. Put some garlic inside fish. Grill or broil on moderate heat, 6 to 8 minutes on each side. About three minutes before fish is cooked, spoon some marinade and bread crumbs over fish. Garnish with lemon wedges.

title: rosamarina salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package (do not overcook).
Drain and rinse well.
Drain juice from pineapple and oranges (not cherries).
Reserve juice.

title: shredded wheat bread
directions: Crumble biscuits; add oil, sugar and salt.
Cover with boiling water; cool.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add to wheat mixture.
Stir in part of flour and turn on floured board.
Knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl; grease top slightly.
Let stand until double in bulk.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp boats
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in frankfurter rolls.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix or beat all together and pour in 2 pie shells.
Bake 25 minutes at 300°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts and parsley.
Chill and shape into a ball.
Mix nuts and parsley and roll ball in the mixture. Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: mamo's shrimp bog
directions: Cook sausage and onion for 30 minutes.
In a large pot, boil potatoes until done.
Add sausage, onion and corn; cook for 10 minutes.
Add shrimp last and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple, cream cheese and sugar until cheese dissolves. Remove from heat and add jello and stir until dissolved.
Add ice water.
Mix well and place in refrigerator and let start to set. Then fold in prepared Dream Whip and nuts.
Return to refrigerator to let set.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients, but add beaten whites last.
Bake in small greased pan in hot water (water in lower pan) for 1/2 hour at 350°.
This makes a cake on top with sauce underneath.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cream of broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Cook celery, onion and broccoli in 2 1/2-quart casserole in microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Set aside.
Blend cottage cheese in blender until very smooth.
Slowly add milk and chicken soup. Continue to blend.
Add to undrained vegetables and heat through. Serve.

title: mushroom pastries
directions: Mix cream cheese and butter together thoroughly.
Add flour and mix well.
Will be soft and creamy feeling.
Chill well.
(Can make a day or two ahead of time for use, keep wrapped well.)
Roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness on lightly flattened surface, cut with 2-inch to 3-inch biscuit cutter.
Place approximately a teaspoon of filling in center and fold over the dough.
Press edges together with fork and prick top crusts to allow steam to escape.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake until lightly browned, 10 to 15 minutes.
(Pastry is good with preserve filling.)

title: buckeye candy
directions: Roll first 4 ingredients into balls and chill for 15 minutes. Dip balls into melted chocolate and paraffin.
Also squares for making candy can be substituted.

title: tea balls
directions: Mix butter, sugars and dates in heavy saucepan.
Boil for 6 minutes.
Pour this mixture over pecans and Rice Krispies in large baking pan.
Stir well to mix.
Roll into small balls and coat with confectioners sugar.

title: batter fried mushrooms
directions: Cover mushrooms with water and milk and let stand one hour or more.
Put 1 cup flour, salt, paprika, black pepper and cayenne pepper in a paper bag.
Drain mushrooms.
Retain about two-thirds of the liquid.
Put mushrooms in paper bag and shake until all mushrooms are covered with flour mixture.
Set mushrooms aside. Heat cooking oil to 400°.
Pour leftover flour and spices into milk-water mixture.
Add egg and enough flour to make fairly thick batter.
Beat.
Put mushrooms into batter.
Drop mushrooms individually into oil, 20 to 30 in standard deep fat fryer. After about two minutes, shake in basket and separate any mushrooms that have stuck together.
Fry until golden.
Drain and put on paper towel.
Sprinkle with cayenne pepper.
Serve with cocktail sauce (catsup, horseradish, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce and lemon juice to taste).

title: dressing for dandelion and warm lettuce
directions: Cook until thick; add lettuce or dandelion.
Bacon is optional.

title: chili - steak and shake
directions: Heat, but do not let boil.

title: easy german chocolate cake
directions: Spread nuts in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread coconut on top of this.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Spread this on top of coconut.
Mix cream cheese, butter or margarine and powdered sugar together.
Spread on top of batter.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven and 15 minutes at 200°.

title: hot italian dip
directions: Combine process cheese spread and Italian dressing in a 1-quart bowl.

title: fruited yogurt milkshake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container in order given. Blend at high speed for one minute.
Yields 8 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: mom's meat loaf and roasted veggies
directions: Rub bowl with garlic.
In same bowl, mix beef, eggs, breadcrumbs, milk, parsley, pepper, salt and onion.
Form into a loaf and place in greased roasting pan.
Place carrots and potatoes around meat loaf in pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 375 degrees for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake another 30 minutes.

title: easy jam cake
directions: Bake cake as usual.
Add nuts and jam last.
Bake at 350° until done; don't overcook.

title: traci's tuna casserole
directions: In a saucepan, heat milk. Add flour and milk mixture and stir well. Add salt, pepper, dill, tuna, and broccoli and let simmer to blend flavors.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients.
Use dip for fruit, strawberries, fresh pineapple, etc.

title: skinny shake(shake 'n bake)
directions: Put bread crumbs into a deep bowl and stir in vegetable oil with fork or pastry blender until evenly distributed.
Add seasonings and blend.
This stores well in tightly covered container on shelf.

title: miss kay's fresh peach pie
directions: Combine water, cornstarch and sugar.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Remove from stove and add peach jello.
Mix well. While
still warm, stir in peaches.
Pour into baked pie shells. Chill and top with Cool Whip.

title: shortcake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Stir in butter to sugar and flour. Then add milk.
Mix well with fork.
Pour into 8-inch round cake pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and slice in half.
Add strawberries and serve.

title: scotchy peanut bars
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup. Bring to a boil; remove and add peanut butter and butterscotch chips. Stir until melted. Add corn flakes and spread over crust. Cool and spread Topping.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Drain off all fat.
Line a dish with the refried beans.
Add hamburger and taco seasoning mix sauce.
Cool.
When
cooled
spread
sour
cream
over it. Cover with grated
cheese
and bake for 30 minutes.
Let set 5 minutes. Cut in squares.
Serve with a tossed salad.

title: spaghetti and pizza sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot and simmer for 1 hour. Put into jars and seal.
Yields 3 quarts.

title: italian supper casserole
directions: Brown meat and sprinkle Sloppy Joe mix over it; stir.
Add tomatoes and mix well, breaking up tomatoes.
In separate bowl, whip cream cheese with whisk or hand beater.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Mix first three ingredients to make crust.
Chill.
Roll crust into little balls and press into small tart pans.
Make filling from brown sugar, egg, butter and nuts.
Mix and put into each crust.
Put whole pecan on top.
Bake 400 degrees for 10 minutes, then turn to 350 degrees until done.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: navetta's chicken and rice
directions: Cut chicken into pieces, rinse and put aside.
Heat oil in large skillet, add half the sliced onion and minced garlic.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice and water; cook until water is absorbed.
Add milk and sugar; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture starts to thicken (about 1 hour).

title: sausage potato pizza
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage until browned; drain off excess fat.
Separate rolls of dough into triangles.
Place in an ungreased 12-inch pan, points toward the center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form a crust.
Spoon sausage over crust. Sprinkle potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over all.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over the top. Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: patti's french toast
directions: Mix egg and milk together well.
Add your spices; mix well. Dip bread in mixture; put in pan.
Cook to a golden or light brown in color.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: christmas punch
directions: *Two quarts of cranapple juice may be substituted for cranberry juice and apple juice.

title: jim's cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Beat in eggs, then sour cream and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until lightly browned around edges (center will be slightly soft).
Cool.
Chill.
Top with cherry or other fruit topping.
Refrigerate leftover.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage and break into small pieces.
Drain well.	Break bread into 9x13 baking dish.
Add layer of sausage and a layer of cheese until all is used.
Beat eggs and add seasonings and milk. Pour over mixture and cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake one hour covered at 350°.
Great for brunch.
Serves 8.

title: bannocks(little oatcakes from scotland)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a baking sheet.
In a bowl, stir oats, flour and salt with a fork to blend.
Cut cold butter into small pieces and add to mixture.
Rub butter and mixture together until coarse bits form.
Stir in water and mix.
Gather rough dough together and place on a board that is lightly dusted with oat flour.
Knead dough about 6 times.
Divide dough in half and pat each half into a circle about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut each circle into 4 wedges.
Place wedges on baking sheet 1/2 inch apart.
Bake for about 20 minutes or until lightly colored.
Makes 8.

title: amaretto-almond sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a small saucepan.
Stir in water.
Place over medium heat. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Stir in Amaretto and lemon juice. Heat just until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat.
Stir in Grape-Nuts and almond extract.
Serve warm over frozen yogurt, angel food cake, fresh fruit or baked apples.
Yields 3/4 cup (12 tablespoons).

title: basic chicken stock
directions: Place all ingredients in a large soup pot and bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer until chicken is tender, about 40 minutes.
Remove chicken from pot and bone it.
Return bones to soup pot and cook for another hour.
Strain and cool broth. Remove fat so that chicken stock is fat-free and all ingredients are removed.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar well. Add dry ingredients; mix. Stir in zucchini and nuts. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: meatless chili for 4
directions: In large, heavy skillet saute the first 5 ingredients in olive oil.
Cook until vegetables are almost tender.
Add sesame seed and saute lightly.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Sometimes I cook this in my crock-pot.
After sauteing the vegetables and sesame seed I just transfer to the crock-pot, add everything else and cook at low for 3 to 4 hours.
Make sure you rinse the kidney beans before adding to the vegetables.
I also add extra beans to stretch, if needed.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan with cream; add sugars.
Bring this mixture to boil, stirring constantly boiling for about 12 minutes.
Once you reach soft boil stage, remove from heat; add vanilla, peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool before cutting.

title: tasty wings
directions: Place cleaned, disjointed wings in a foil-lined 9 x 13-inch pan.
Salt and pepper wings to taste.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Pour over wings.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, turning and basting with sauce every 15 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Mix and cook over medium heat for 2 hours or more until thick. Put into jars and seal.

title: peanut butter sensations
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream Crisco, peanut butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla in large bowl at medium speed on electric mixer for 1
minute, scraping sides of bowl frequently. Add egg and milk.
Beat until well blended.
Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter each biscuit.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Put biscuits in greased Bundt pan.
Melt 1 stick of butter and combine with brown sugar.
Pour over top of biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Very sweet and very fattening!
Yum!

title: stuffed fajitas
directions: If butterflied fajitas are not available, cut fajitas into very thin, 5 to 6-inch slices.
Cook mushrooms; set aside.
Saute bell pepper, onion and 1/2 hot pepper in butter until tender. Spoon onion mixture on fajita slice.
Roll up fajita and wrap 1 slice of bacon around it, securing with toothpick.
When coals are ready, place on grill; cook well done.
Turn very slowly and in small turns.
Fajitas have to cook all the way through from one side.
Top with mushrooms and butter.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Saute onions and butter until transparent.
Beat eggs well, then add other ingredients.
Add onions to top.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: pasta italian
directions: Cook, rinse and drain spaghetti.
Roll around your hand to make individual servings.
Put in single layer in large covered container.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: glazed fresh apple cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sift flour with soda.
Mix shortening, brown sugar, salt, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and egg until well blended.
Stir in half flour mixture, then nuts, apples and raisins.
Blend in apple juice, then remaining flour mixture. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 11 to 14 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.
Spread Vanilla Glaze on top; top with pecans.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Press out crescent rolls on baking sheet.
Press flat.
Pinch seams together and bake for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs i
directions: Mix jelly and chili sauce together.
Mix meat, egg and bread crumbs to form small balls.
In saucepan cook in chili-jelly mixture until cooked, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot in sauce.

title: lime mousse
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: p.j.'s cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into ball; roll in chopped pecans. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: marion's meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients, except bacon.
Mix well.
Put in ungreased loaf pan or form into loaf in regular pan.
Put bacon strips on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until center is shaky.

title: oreo cake
directions: Melt ice cream just enough to mix.
Mix ice cream and Cool Whip together.
Smash up cookies.
Mix 1/2 together with ice cream.
Put in a 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle rest of cookies.
Put in freezer overnight.

title: s'more clusters
directions: In a large microwave bowl, toss chocolate and oil.
Microwave, uncovered at medium for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until chocolate is melted.
Stir only once.
Stir in marshmallows and graham crackers. Spoon into muffin cups and refrigerate for 1 hour or until firm.

title: egg bread for dressing
directions: Heat a 10-inch skillet in a 450° oven for 5 minutes.
Combine all dry ingredients and mix.
Gradually add all liquids; mix well with spoon or hand.
Remove skillet from oven and coat with cooking spray.
Pour batter into skillet.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Let cool.
Yields 8 cups crumbled bread crumbs.

title: egg noodles
directions: On clean counter surface shape flour into a well.
Add in salt and eggs.
Slowly add in water.
Knead until a firm ball. Roll out 1/8 inch and let dry.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place in boiling water for 3-6 minutes until al dente.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with Twinkies, cut in half lengthwise, filling side up making 2 layers (5 Twinkies per layer).
Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Spread half of pudding over Twinkies.
Crush candy and sprinkle half over pudding.
Spread with half of topping; repeat layers.
Sprinkle top with candy. Chill at least 2 hours.

title: yummy bars
directions: Cream together first 2 ingredients. Combine this with the syrup, vanilla and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Pat in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and mix in the peanut butter. Spread over hot bars.

title: frankfurter puff
directions: Remove crust from bread and cut in 1-inch squares.
Thinly slice franks on the diagonal.
Arrange half bread cubes in a well-buttered pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Place 1/2 franks, onions and cheese over bread.
Repeat these layers.
Beat together egg, milk and seasoning.
Pour mixture evenly over cheese and dust with paprika.
Add more milk if cheese is not covered.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: lizzies
directions: Mix fruit with 1/2 cup flour. Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and other ingredients.
Mix well and drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until light brown (about 16 to 20 minutes).
Good at holidays!

title: apple cheese crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place in a greased baking dish.
Pour water and lemon juice on top.
Combine sugar, cinnamon, flour, margarine and cheese until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sweet and sour cucumber salad
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar except cucumbers and onions. Shake well to mix.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Chill. Serves 6 as a side dish.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients;
mix well.
Combine next 3 ingredients; mix well.
Do not add to first mix until ready to serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand, then peanut butter until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream.
Turn into prepared crust.
Drizzle topping over pie.
Freeze for 4 hours or until firm.
Return leftovers to freezer.

title: easy coconut cake (delicious)
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box.
While still warm, poke holes in cake.
Pour cream of coconut in holes; cool.
Prepare frosting (Cool Whip with a cup of coconut mixed in).
Now frost your cake and sprinkle remaining coconut on top.
Makes a beautiful cake.
Very moist.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in microwave.
Heat for 2 minutes on High, then stir.
(If more time is needed, stir morsels every 30 seconds.)
Add nuts and noodles.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by large tablespoon onto wax paper, making clusters.

title: erwin's shrimp
directions: Simmer all ingredients except shrimp for 20 to 30 minutes, then heat to high.
Add shrimp and cook until shrimp turn pink (2 to 4 minutes, according to size).
Do not overcook.
Immediately serve hot butter sauce with shrimp in soup bowls and sourdough bread (muffins or small loaves), cooked on low heat until very hard.
Sop sauce with bread.

title: macaroons
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful on well-greased baking sheet about 1-inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan at once.

title: wassetta
directions: Brown hamburger meat and sausage on top of stove with salt and pepper to taste.
Heat onion in grease from hamburger until clear. Cook noodles in salted water until tender, about 12 to 15 minutes; drain.
Mix soups with 1/2 can water each.
Mix all together and heat thoroughly in 350° oven for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Let stand until nearly cool and cover with Reynolds Wrap.

title: easy cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, put the pie filling and pineapple. Sprinkle the cake mix over the top.
Melt the margarine and pour over the cake mix. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: joyce m.'s baked beans
directions: Drain beans and discard liquid.
Cut up bacon in small pieces and chop onion.
Brown bacon in pan with onion.
Do not drain grease.
When bacon is brown, add brown sugar, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Cook over medium-low heat until sugar is melted.
Put sauce mixture and drained beans in a large casserole dish and bake for 50 minutes at 400°.
Excellent for fellowship or a picnic.
Feeds a crowd.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Make 1/2 cup size balls.
Place in baking dish or pan.

title: sand tarts(wedding cookies)
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add vanilla and flour (a little at a time).
Then stir in nuts.
Measure 1/2 teaspoon into little balls. Bake at 325° for around 30 minutes.
Cool, then dust with powdered sugar.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoonful into deep, hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: polish sausage and potatoes
directions: Cook diced potatoes in oil until halfway done.
Slice sausage in thin slices and add with onions to potatoes.
Cover and cook until potatoes are done.

title: chicken or turkey enchiladas
directions: This is the perfect answer for leftover turkey after Thanksgiving!

title: baked brie
directions: Roll the pastry to make 1 round crust.
Wrap around the cheese, pinching to seal.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Let cool a few minutes.
Serve warm with Wheat Thins or sliced baguettes.

title: pizza quiche
directions: Beat together half and half, oregano, garlic powder and eggs. In pie shell, place minced salami and 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella.
Pour egg mixture over cheese and salami.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Spoon hot pizza sauce over each serving.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a greased dish at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: jezebel sauce(use with ham)
directions: Beat apple jelly well; add preserves, mustard, horseradish, salt and pepper. Beat well.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip first.
Add other ingredients.
Let chill overnight.

title: seven up pound cake
directions: Cream together softened
butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flavoring.
mix well.
Add flour, sifted together with salt, alternating with Seven Up.
Bake at 325° 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: uncooked pickles
directions: Mix sugar, white vinegar, celery seed or flakes and pickling salt until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil.
Cool.
Slice pickles fine in a large container; add chopped onions.
Pour juice over pickles and stir a few times.
Put into jars and refrigerate.
Will keep for 3 months or more.
(Can also put in stalks of fresh celery; I also put in fresh dill.)

title: jiffy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix dry ingredients and pour over top of melted margarine; do not mix.
Pour fruit and juice on top; do not mix.
(To sweeten fruit, let it stand until juice comes up on fruit.)
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Top with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: pecan pie
directions: Makes one 9-inch pie.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: brown sugar pecans
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla. Beat well after each addition.
Add pecans.
Drop by teaspoons on baking sheet. Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Store in airtight containers.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in slow cooker.
Spread soup over chops. Turn on low for 8 hours or on high for 5 to 6 hours.
Serve with mashed potatoes.
To stop the cooker from heating up the house, place cooker in the garage or on the patio.

title: crisco pie crust
directions: Add 1/2 cup flour at first, rest of flour as needed.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter in heavy bottomed saucepan. Stir over low heat until cheese is soft and butter is melted, and the mixture is thoroughly blended.
Add the powdered sugar and stir until well combined.
Add your choice of food coloring and flavorings.

title: graham cracker preserves cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Crush graham crackers and mix with milk.
Separate eggs.
Add egg yolks, then nuts, raisins, dates, crushed pineapple and preserves.
Add baking powder.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into tube pan or 9 x 13-inch pan and cook in moderate to slow oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: florida pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1 cup sugar and beat again until stiff.
Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla and set mixture aside. Combine crackers, chopped nuts and 1 cup sugar.
Mix well.
