Fold into the beaten egg whites.
Put this mixture into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cool for 45 minutes.

title: vidalia onion supreme sandwiches
directions: Spread mayonnaise on bread.
Spread peanut butter on one slice and top with onion slices and other slice of bread.
Slice and serve.

title: george bush's chicken
directions: Saute chicken in butter and sprinkle with dry Italian dressing mix while turning chicken. Do the sauteing slowly, because it may burn easily.

title: peach tart
directions: Mix together the graham cracker crumbs, sugar and 1/4 pound butter.
Beat the Dream Whip, sugar, cream cheese and milk until thick; then put in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Take graham cracker mix and press firmly in bottom of pan or dish.
Pour Dream Whip mixture over graham cracker mix and top with your choice of pie filling.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to a boil; let cool.
Pour into gallon jar and add cucumbers and onions.
Garlic and hot peppers may be added if desired.
Put into refrigerator.
Add new cucumbers as needed.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Place cabbage in large pot of salted, boiling water and break apart with forks.
Roll mixture inside of cabbage leaves.
Add tomato paste and sauce with enough water to fill pot 2/3 full.
Cook 1
1/2 hours over medium heat.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, then 250° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Chill all ingredients 1 hour.
Grease baking sheet.
Dip out by teaspoon.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 325°.

title: salisbury steak with mushroom gravy
directions: Combine meat, egg, bread crumbs, onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Shape into 6 patties.
Preheat skillet to 325°.
Brown patties well on both sides.
In small bowl, combine mushroom soup, milk and gravy.
Pour over patties.
Reduce heat to 200° and simmer, covered, 15 to 20 minutes or until well done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in a large pot; whisk in flour and cook over medium heat 5 minutes, whisking constantly.
Gradually add warm stock, whisking constantly.
Stir and simmer 20 minutes until it has thickened.
Add seasonings.
Add chicken and vegetable and simmer until chicken is heated through.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat Bisquick and milk, adding more Bisquick if necessary to make a manageable dough.
Turn onto a floured board.
Knead until smooth, about 30 seconds.
Roll out until large enough to cover casserole.
Bake until golden brown on top, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: country dinner rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; cool.
Add oil, yeast (softened in 1/3 cup water), molasses, brown sugar, egg and salt.
Beat in 1/2 flour to make soft dough.
Add bacon and onion pieces.
Add remaining flour; knead until smooth.
Cover bowl with foil.
Let dough rise until double in bulk.
Punch down; let rise again.

title: susan's shortcakes(for strawberries)
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Beat egg in measuring cup with milk.
Stir into flour mixture.
Drop in mounds on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Split while still hot and spread with butter.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Cook giblets in salted water.
Save 1 1/2 cups broth.
Mix dry ingredients in a paper sack.
Beat egg and 1/2 cup milk together. Shake chicken in flour, then egg, then flour.
Melt margarine in pan in oven.
Place chicken, skin side down, in pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 30 minutes.
Turn and bake 25 minutes more. Remove chicken from pan.
Add remaining flour mixture and chopped giblets to drippings in pan.
Stir over medium heat until blended. Combine 1 1/2 cups broth and remaining milk.
Slowly add to flour mixture.
Cook until thickened.

title: lemon-broiled chicken(lulu's only dish)
directions: Rub chicken halves on both sides with lemon; brush with butter. Mix salt, pepper, paprika and sugar together and sprinkle over chicken.
Place in broiler pan, skin side down.
Turn every 20 minutes.
Baste to ensure browning.
Broil for 25 to 40 minutes, until pink color disappears from bone.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add remaining.
Stir until well mixed. Very good and healthy.

title: waffles deluxe
directions: Use 3 mixing bowls.
In the large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
In another bowl, combine beaten egg yolks, milk and melted margarine.
In a small bowl, beat egg whites until stiff. Blend flour mixture with wet mixture, then fold in egg whites. Bake in a hot waffle iron.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix oleo, confectioners sugar, salt and flour.
Add nuts; roll in balls the size of a marble.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 400° oven for 15 to 17 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while warm.
When cool, roll in confectioners sugar again.

title: layered cole slaw
directions: Shred vegetables in order listed.
Do not stir.
Pour sugar over this.
Do not stir.
Combine remainder of ingredients and bring to boiling point.
Pour over cabbage while hot.
Do not stir.
Refrigerate.
Serves 10.

title: wendy's chili
directions: In a large skillet, brown hamburger meat.
Add 1 tablespoon oil, French onion soup, chili powder, 3 or 4 drops Tabasco sauce, both cans of tomato sauce.
Let simmer on medium heat for 30 minutes.
Then enjoy.

title: scallop potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thin.
Slice onions.
Cut garlic in half.
Beat eggs and mix with half and half milk.
In oblong dish, rub bottom of dish with garlic cloves and margarine.
Make layer of thin sliced potatoes, layer of onions, layer of grated cheese and repeat until they are all used. Pour egg and half and half mixture over layers.
Part with margarine.
Cook in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barb's chili chicken
directions: Mix together soups, broth, green chilies, chili and onion.
In large casserole, layer tortillas, chicken, soup mixture and cheese.
Repeat tortillas, chicken, soup mixture and cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove top and cook another 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Place pie filling and pineapple in a 9 1/2 x 11-inch pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over top of fruit.
Pour liquid Butter Buds on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Serves 16 to 18.

title: girl scouts' herbed biscuits
directions: Put biscuits in pan.
Baste tops of biscuits with melted margarine.
Then add to taste remaining ingredients.
Bake as normal.
Delicious with Italian dishes such as spaghetti or lasagne.

title: date and nut pudding
directions: Bake in 350°
oven.
When ready to serve, break
up in pieces in a big dish and put whipped cream over it.

title: caesar salad
directions: Mix liquid ingredients, plus garlic, together in jar.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Rub wood bowl with garlic half. Lettuce into bowl (romaine).
Dry ingredients and mix.
Liquid ingredients and mix.
Raw egg, beaten, and mix (if desired). Croutons (homemade are best).
More grated Parmesan cheese (if desired).

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, lard, salt, baking powder and sugar until crumbly. Mix together water, egg or egg yolk and vinegar; add to first mixture.
Thoroughly combine and roll out for pie shell.
(I use 1/4 cup water and 1 egg yolk.)
Freezes well.

title: chili relleno bake
directions: In a large skillet, crumble together the beef and chorizo or sausage.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until meat is browned. Add onion and garlic; cook until onion is soft.
Drain.
Line a 9 x 9 x 2-inch greased baking dish with half of the chilies; top with 1 1/2 cups of the cheese.
Add the meat mixture and top with remaining chilies, set aside.
Beat together eggs and flour until smooth; add milk, salt and hot pepper sauce.
Blend well.
Pour egg mixture over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes or until knife inserted off center comes out clean. Sprinkle with remaining cheese on top.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: auntie's coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after.
Sift flour, salt, and baking powder together.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Beat in coconut.
Pour into tube pan which has been well greased and floured.
Bake in 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
After cooling a few minutes, remove from pan and pour glaze over cake.

title: orange juice drink(like you buy from the mall)
directions: Blend with 12 ice cubes. Makes about 4 cups.

title: no meat chili pasta
directions: Spray large skillet or pot with nonstick cooking spray.
Cook onion 2 minutes.
Add undrained tomatoes, drained beans, spices and tomato paste.
Bring to a boil, simmer 15 minutes.
Toss with elbows.
Serve with sour cream and cilantro.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs, milk and mustard together.
Add bread; mix.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 8 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Uncover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except nuts.
Form a ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate 2 hours at least before serving with crackers or apple slices.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Thoroughly mix ingredients together and chill about 1 hour. Makes about 6 servings.

title: sugar-free chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix everything together and put in ice cream maker.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Boil and cool.
Pour over sliced onions and cucumbers.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: hamburger bundles
directions: Add a little milk to hamburger meat.
Prepare Stove Top dressing.
Place about 1/4 cup of the dressing in hamburger patty, flattened, for each bundle.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Beat shortening at medium speed.
Gradually add sugar, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in coconut.
Pour in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Remove from pan, cool on wire rack.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter until tender.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Bake in casserole with crumbs on top at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Add sauerkraut and onions.
Pour the tomatoes and tomato sauce over the top.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 6 hours.

title: overnight easy coffee cake
directions: Combine pudding mix (dry) with brown sugar and nuts.
Place pieces of frozen dough in a well-greased Bundt pan.
Pour melted butter over frozen dough and sprinkle with pudding mixture.
Leave pan out overnight; dough rises beautifully by A.M.
(I usually put a piece of wax paper lightly over top as it rises.)
Bake at 350°. Invert on serving plate and eat!

title: beef tenderloin
directions: Cover meat with bacon grease.
Bake at 500° on a rack for 7 to 10 minutes, depending on size.
Reduce oven to 400°.
Bake 10 to 20 minutes, again depending on size and degree of wellness desired.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 to 15 minutes before slicing/serving.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix crumb and margarine and press into 8 x 8 or 9 x 9 dish or pan.
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and milk until smooth and spread over crust.
Top with pecans.
Fold sugar and marshmallows into whipped topping.
Spoon over pecans.
Combine cherry pie filling and vanilla.
Pour over top and chill.

title: sweet potato turnovers
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until soft.
Peel and mash.
Add butter, sugar and spices.
Mix well.
Unroll the crescent roll dough into squares.
On each square, put some sweet potato filling.
Fold edges together.
Bring oil to a boil and then turn off heat. Carefully drop the turnovers into oil, one by one, and deep fry to a golden brown or until crisp.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef in large heavy kettle; drain and add onion.
Cook until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese; simmer for 15 minutes.
Ladle into bowls, top with grated cheese. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Stir jello until dissolved in the boiling water.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Add bananas.
Let set until firm.
Mix sugar, flour, egg yolk, pineapple juice and butter and cook until thick.
Let cool and beat in one small Cool Whip. Spread on jello.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: chocolate gloss
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch; add chocolate, salt and 1/2 cup water.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly and chocolate melts.
Remove from heat; add oleo and vanilla.
While hot, frost cake.

title: grilled pork tenderloin
directions: Blend orange juice, white wine, soy sauce and garlic.
Pour over tenderloin in glass dish or plastic bag, covered in refrigerator for 8 to 24 hours.
Prepare grill.
If using charcoal, use indirect method.
Remove pork from marinade.
Pour marinade into saucepan and add butter, marmalade and honey.
Bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Roast tenderloin in covered grill about 30 to 45 minutes.
Baste often with glaze.

title: glorified pork chops
directions: In a skillet in hot oil, cook half of the chops 10 minutes or until brown.
Remove.
Set aside. Repeat with remaining chops. Spoon off fat.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes, using only a small amount of water; cool and drain.
Combine eggs, mayonnaise, soup, onion, 3/4 cup cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix in broccoli.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: strawberry delight
directions: In a mixing bowl or blender, beat the eggs with the sliced strawberries, sugar and vanilla.
Gradually add milk, mixing until all ingredients are thoroughly blended.
Serve immediately.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Add vegetables to liquid mixture.
Bring to a boil and can.

title: frankfurter goulash
directions: Cook frankfurters in water; when cooked, cut into penny slices.
In medium pan, start with 2 cups milk or cold water; add tomato soup, stirring until smooth.
When soup reaches boiling point, add frankfurter penny slices.
Stir until blended.
Add peas, potatoes and onions; return mixture to boiling point.

title: cajun shrimp stew
directions: Saute celery, onion and garlic in butter until soft.
Stir in flour, salt, thyme and pepper; cook, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Stir in tomatoes, chicken broth, clams and liquid and red pepper seasoning.
Continue cooking and stirring until mixture thickens and boils 1 minute.
Add okra and shrimp; heat to boiling.
Ladle into a shallow serving bowl; spoon rice around edge.

title: wild rice
directions: Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid. Combine mushroom liquid and beef broth. Add water to make 2 cups.

title: nutmeg tea cakes
directions: Add
lemon
juice
to Milnot; set aside.
Cream together sugar and
shortening;
add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add
vanilla.
Sift
together dry ingredients; add
dry ingredients alternately with the Milnot to the creamed mixture. Drop
by rounded teaspoons onto floured cookie sheet. Bake
for
8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Frost if desired. Store plain, then frost.

title: sausage-potato casserole
directions: Parboil chunked potatoes.
Layer smoke sausages (in slanted pieces) in bottom of casserole.
Add drained potatoes on top.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix kidney beans, celery, pickles, onion, eggs, salt and pepper.
Mix lightly with mayonnaise or sour cream. Chill thoroughly. Serves 6.

title: creme brulee
directions: In a large, heavy saucepan, combine the cream, milk and 1/2 cup of the sugar. Place the pan over high heat and bring to a boil, watching carefully to prevent a boil-over, then remove from the heat. Add 2 teaspoons vanilla extract, or, if using a vanilla bean, cut the vanilla bean on a cutting board in half lengthwise and scrape the seeds out with the tip of a sharp knife. Add the seeds and the pod to the pan. Let the cream mixture stand for 30 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil mixture until crackles (290° to 300°) when dropped in cold water.
Add 1/4 teaspoon soda.
While foaming, pour mixture over corn.
Form into balls while warm.
Makes 12 (3-inch) balls.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat. Add onion, salt and pepper.
Add vegetable soup, tomato soup and water.
Cut the potatoes up in cubes and add to the meat and soup mixture.
Put in greased casserole. Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are done.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Bake in oblong baking dish.
When done, punch a few holes in cake with fork.

title: linguini salad
directions: Prepare linguini according to package directions.
Drain and toss well with Salad Supreme.
Add dressing and allow to cool. Chop tomatoes, cucumber, green pepper, onion and celery.
Add to linguini.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Stir occasionally and just before serving.
Keeps well.

title: baklava
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease baking dish.
Mix walnuts, sugar and cinnamon in a bowl and set aside.
Place 2 sheets of phyllo in bottom of greased pan and brush with melted butter.
Add 2 more sheets of phyllo and brush with butter.
Continue until a total of 8 sheets is on bottom of pan.
Be sure to brush each layer with butter.
Sprinkle 2/3 to 1 cup of the walnut mixture evenly over phyllo.
Cut remaining phyllo in half and place 6 layers of phyllo (2 each and butter), then walnut mixture.
Repeat another 6 layers with butter and add walnut mixture, etc.
Trim phyllo away from edges with scissors.
With a sharp knife, cut halfway through the layers to form a diamond pattern.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours until golden brown.
Heat the honey and water together until hot and pour evenly over baked baklava.
Cut all the way through and enjoy.

title: apple pie without apples
directions: Take first three and boil for 1 minute.
Put 20 Ritz crackers in a pie crust.
Pour the ingredients over the crackers slowly. Put butter and cinnamon on top like apple pie.
Bake for 15 minutes in oven (500°).
The last 3 minutes, turn down to 450°.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 5 to 6 mini bread pans.
Mix all ingredients together.
Fill bread pans about half full.
Bake until done, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Let cool to touch; remove from pan.
Store in refrigerator.

title: classic cole slaw
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and chill. Serves 6.

title: fried spinach stuffed chicken breast
directions: Place breast between heavy plastic wrap and flatten to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place 1/2 teaspoon of spinach mixture on each flattened breast.
Fold in sides and ends and secure with toothpicks. Combine egg and milk, mix well.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture, then dip in egg mixture, and dredge in flour mixture.
Pour oil to 1 inch in skillet and fry chicken in hot oil about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
May also dip in egg wash and roll in cornflake crumbs (with seasonings) and bake.

title: raspberry-apple salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with boiling water; add cider or juice, then add raspberries.
Chill until firm; may want to stir during chilling so raspberries do not float to top.

title: cranberry-mandarin glazed pork roast
directions: In a small saucepan stir together all ingredients except pork. Cook stirring over medium heat until the sauce is thickened, set aside.
Place roast in a shallow baking dish, brush with thickened sauce.
Roast at 325° for 30 minutes.

Spoon 1/2 cup of the prepared glaze over the roast, continue roasting for 30 to 45 minutes more until internal temperature of roast is 155° to 160°. Let the roast stand 10 to 15 minutes before slicing.
Slice and serve with the remaining sauce.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken.
Cook spaghetti in broth. After spaghetti is done, take out about half of the water and add the soups, tomatoes and cheese and the deboned chicken.
Simmer and stir until cheese is melted.
Ready then to serve.

title: green goddess dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender or food processor.
Be careful not to over grind parsley.
Serve with vegetables.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Let come to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil one minute; remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter, nuts and vanilla.
Mix and drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Allow to cool.

title: uncooked relish
directions: Put each vegetable through food chopper using coarse blade. Drain off juice; discard.
Measure each vegetable after chopped. Mix vegetables with salt; let set overnight.
Next morning, drain off as much liquid as possible.
Add spices, sugar and vinegar to vegetables; mix well and pack in jars to within 1/2 inch of top. Put on cap; screw firmly.
Process in boiling water for 15 minutes.

title: creamed celery with pecans
directions: Boil celery in water to cover in saucepan until tender; drain. Blend flour into melted butter in skillet.
Add milk slowly. Simmer until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Add salt and celery; mix well.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with pecans; cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken and brown rice(low-fat)
directions: *Turkey or tuna may be substituted.

title: apple cauliflower salad
directions: Thinly slice unpeeled apples.
Mix with sliced cauliflower and enough poppy seed dressing to coat each piece.
Serve over a bed of lettuce or prepare individual servings on small salad plates. Excellent served with pork or poultry.

title: spring daffodil pie
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Combine milk, sugar, salt and egg yolks in small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to boil.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Stir in orange juice, lemon juice and orange rind.
Chill mixture until slightly thickened.
Fold whipped cream into gelatin mixture.
Pour into crust.
Chill for several hours or until set.
Garnish with whipped cream or Cool Whip and crushed candy mints.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for at least 1 hour.

title: creole flounder
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix first 4 ingredients in saucepan and simmer about 15 minutes or until tender.
Place fish in shallow buttered baking dish in single layer.
Pour sauce over and bake for 25 minutes.
Add salt and pepper as desired prior to baking.

title: beef chowder
directions: Cook the rice in the beef stock for 2 hours.
Fry the noodles in the oil for a few seconds, then remove.
Finely chop the ginger and add with the meat to the rice.
Cook for about 15 minutes. Stir sesame oil, soy sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Put some noodles and a little egg in each soup bowl.
Pour the chowder over and garnish with chopped scallions.

title: potatoes a la good
directions: Parboil peeled potatoes.
When cool, slice.
Season soup with onion, cheese, salt and pepper.
Put layer of potatoes in casserole.
Cover with soup mixture.
Repeat potatoes and soup mixture.
Be sure to end with soup mixture.
Dot top with butter and sprinkle with some grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: good peanut brittle
directions: Bring 1/2 cup water to a boil then add: sugar and syrup. Stir until dissolved and boil until it spins a thread.
Add peanuts and cook slowly over a low fire until it turns golden brown.
Remove from fire and add butter, vanilla and soda.
Stir quickly and pour on a buttered cookie sheet.
Let it get cold then break into pieces and store in well covered container.

title: fruit cake
directions: Butter a 9-inch tube pan.
Line bottom of pan with waxed paper. Butter the waxed paper.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix flour and baking soda and sift.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine the eggs, mincemeat, mixed fruit and the nuts.
Mix well.
Add the dry ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour into the prepared pan and bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Invert the pan and cool cake for an hour. Remove from pan and peel off the waxed paper.
Use the small jar of cherries as a garnish for the top of the cake.

title: potato halushki
directions: Cook potatoes in their jackets; skin and mash.
Mix eggs and flour together with mashed potatoes.
Make the Halushki by cooking in simmering salted water for 6 to 8 minutes.
Drain.
Serve with sauteed onion if desired or plain butter, melted.

title: hamburger hot pot
directions: In skillet, lightly brown ground beef and drain well.
Add garlic powder, salt and pepper; set aside.
Place half the potatoes and half the onions in greased crock-pot.
Add browned beef.
Top with remaining potatoes and onions.
Combine mushroom soup and water; spread over top, being sure to moisten and cover evenly. Cover and cook on low setting for 8 to 10 hours (on high setting for 3 to 4 hours).
Makes 4 to 6 servings (about 2 1/2 quarts).

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, Miracle Whip and chili powder.
In a 2-quart casserole, layer meat, half of chips and half of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Top with shredded lettuce and tomato.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Rinse shrimp in cold water and drain.
Peel carrots.
Slice celery and carrots.
Saute carrots and celery in butter.
Add soup and milk.
Blend mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Add cooked spaghetti and shrimp.
Heat thoroughly and serve.

title: peach crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Slice peaches in dish.
Sift together flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Cut margarine into flour mixture until it resembles cornmeal.
Spoon this over peaches.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with cream.
Serves 6.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine onions, potatoes and water in pan.
Bring to boil. Add bouillon cubes, parsley, pepper and salt.
Combine 1 cup of milk and flour; add to soup.
Simmer until thick, stirring constantly.
Add remaining milk; heat until hot.
Crumble bacon over top and serve.
Yields 6 servings.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients through food chopper.
Add sugar, vinegar and spices.
Cook in oven until thick, about 3 1/2 hours. Put into jars; process and seal.

title: celebrity broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well. Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Melt the 1/2 stick butter and cheese over low heat.
Spread over broccoli.
Mix 3/4 cup butter with cracker crumbs.
Spread over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Add shortening, egg and milk. Stir well. Place in greased muffin pan. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: chicken pockets
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fill crescent rolls (2 cans). Bake until a golden brown.
Serve with a chicken-like gravy.

title: neapolitan cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for colored, fluted tube pan).
Use solid shortening to grease and flour pan, 12-cup size.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream margarine and 2 cups sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add alternately with sour cream, beating just enough after each addition to keep batter smooth.
Spoon 1/3 of batter into a greased 10-inch pan.
Combine cinnamon, nuts and remaining sugar. Sprinkle 1/3 over batter in pan.
Repeat 2 more times.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes or until done.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water to a thread.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into egg whites, other half, cook until brittle.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Beat until it loses its shine.
Drop by the spoonful onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together; make meatballs.
Fry in olive oil.
On pound hamburg makes about 16 meatballs.

title: esther's holiday coconut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, butter and powdered sugar until smooth.
Spread with fingers in 8-inch square pan.
Bake about 35 minutes. (Watch and don't let it get too brown.)

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, baking soda and salt.
Add water and mix well.
Add flour a little at a time.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in egg whites, stiffly beaten.
Bake at 350° until done.
Makes 3 layers.

title: sauce for fresh fruit
directions: Mix and pour over fruit.

title: herb harvest vegetable casserole
directions: Grease a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish and arrange half of the potato slices in overlapping rows.
Dot with half of the butter. Sprinkle with half of the sage, tarragon, peppers, onion, rice and zucchini.
Dot with remaining butter and repeat layering.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender. Remove cover and top with tomato slices and cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes or until tomatoes are warm and cheese has melted.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: boiled shrimp
directions: Get a big, deep pot, fill half full of water.
Bring to a boil.
Add shrimp boil, onions, lemons, salt and pepper.
Boil together 5 minutes.
Add unpeeled shrimp; boil 5 minutes.
Drain and pour over a bed of ice.
Chill; peel and dip in butter or other sauce.
Eat.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Make a roux of margarine and flour.
Add chicken broth and mix until smooth.
Add evaporated milk; stir until smooth and thick over medium heat.
Add herbs last.
Just before serving, add dry sherry, if desired.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Place breasts in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together soup, sour cream and mushrooms.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: papago tepary bean soup
directions: Drain soaked beans and bring to boil in big pot.
When tender, fry bacon until limp.
Remove bacon; add onion, carrots, celery and garlic and saute.
Add bacon, tomatoes and juice and spices. Cook 10 minutes; add beans.
Cook
another hour until beans are mealy-tender.
Serves 6.
Serve with flour tortillas or fresh frybread.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
While still real hot, add frozen red raspberries.
When dissolved, stir in applesauce and put in refrigerator to set.

title: grandpa bisbee's fudge
directions: Bring to a boil: sugar, milk and butter.
Boil for 5 minutes. Add Hershey bars and chocolate chips.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: bodacious baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown sausage in a skillet.
Remove sausage and set aside.
Add beef and onion to skillet and cook until browned; drain fat.
Combine beef mixture, sausage, beans, molasses, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, ketchup and bacon in a large casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake cake in round pans; let cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool completely.
Place cake layers top side up, back into clean pans.
Prick each layer with a utility fork, 1/2-inch intervals.
Mix 1 cup boiling water with red jello, then spoon over 1 layer and then repeat with lime jello.
Put in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours.
Dip 1 layer in pan, in warm water for 10 seconds. Invert on plate, then spread with Cool Whip.
Then do the same with second layer.
Frost with rest of topping.
Refrigerate.
Garnish with gumdrops.
Cut to resemble holly.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Line bottom of loaf pan with 1/4 jar of sauce.
Mix hamburger, eggs, seasoning, 1/2 jar sauce, onion and crackers. Form together and put into pan. Top with remaining sauce. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. The last 15 minutes, top with Mozzarella cheese.

title: golden skillet cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In cast iron skillet, melt shortening in oven. Combine dry ingredients. Add milk and egg.
Mix until blended.

title: sweet potato sonker
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Put half of potatoes in 9 x 13 inch casserole dish.
Cover with half of sugar and margarine.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with strips of pastry.
Add another layer of potatoes, sugar, margarine and cinnamon.
Mix flavoring with milk or water and pour over all.
Cover with pastry.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
This recipe can easily be cut in half and made in an 8 inch square dish.

title: vegetable rice
directions: In 10-inch frypan, combine ingredients.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes or until tender.

title: toasted nuts
directions: Spread pecans on cookie sheet and roast at 275° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Beat egg whites.
Melt butter in oven in a 9 x 12-inch loaf pan.
To foamy egg whites, add sugar, vanilla and salt.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into pan with butter and spread evenly in pan.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes until butter is absorbed and nuts are brown. Dump onto waxed paper to cool.
Break up and put in airtight container to store.

title: bacon custards
directions: Separate eggs.
In a bowl, mix together yolks, butter, milk, either ham or bacon and seasonings.
Set aside.
In another bowl, beat egg whites until stiff, about 2 minutes.
Gently fold into yolk mixture.
Pour mixture into 6-ounce custard cups.
Place in oblong pan that has been filled with 1-inch hot water.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 cups.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pick, wash, trim and dry cukes.

title: savory beef mushroom burgers
directions: Combine
chuck,
cereal, onions, coarsely ground pepper, garlic
and
milk in a medium bowl;
stir well.
Divide mixture into
equal
portions,
shaping
each
into a 3/4-inch thick patty.
Set
patties aside.
Combine cornstarch and 2 teaspoons water,
stirring until cornstarch dissolves; set mixture aside. Coat
a small nonstick skillet with vegetable spray; place over medium
heat
until
hot.
Add sliced mushrooms and saute until tender.
Remove
mushrooms
from
skillet
and
set aside.
Add cornstarch
mixture, remaining 1/2 cup water, bouillon granules and
1/8 teaspoon pepper to skillet; cook over medium high heat until
thick and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Return mushrooms to skillet
and
stir
well.
Remove
from heat and keep warm. Broil patties 7 inches from heat for 3 minutes on each side or to desired
degree
of
doneness.
Spoon
sauce
over patties, sprinkle
with parsley.
Yield:
4 servings, about 267 calories per patty and 3 tablespoons sauce.

title: cheezee potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on them until about half done. Peel potatoes
and
shred
into	large bowl. Add butter. Stir well. Add
remaining
ingredients and put into greased baking dish.
Top with
crushed regular or cheese potato chips. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 4.

title: savory green beans
directions: Cook beans and onions in a saucepan according to package directions for the beans.
Drain.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce. Sprinkle each serving with bacon pieces.
Makes 2 servings.

title: dutch meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, onions, green pepper, eggs, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Press into 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Unmold loaf on rack of broiler pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Combine 1/2 cup tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard in pan.
Cook over medium heat until heated. Spoon sauce over meat loaf.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Mix all together and cook 5 hours in 250° oven or cook in crock-pot all day.
Thicken sauce and serve over noodles.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Cut chicken into desired pieces and place in skillet.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour barbecue sauce and 7-Up over chicken.
Simmer on top of stove for 1 hour.

title: german potato soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter until onion is golden.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Add potatoes and cook for 2 minutes.
Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth.
Add ham or bacon; salt and pepper to taste.
Add beaten egg yolk, stirring until creamy and soup is heated through.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and sugar; set aside.
Mix together bran flakes and milk; let stand until soft, 1 to 2 minutes, then add egg and oil.
Beat well, then add dry ingredients to cereal mixture; stir until combined.
Grease muffin tins.
Makes 12 muffins.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: betty's apple pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon and lemon juice in a bowl.
Add to apples.
Put apples and mixture in pie crust.
Dot on top with butter.
Put pie crust on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Pour water over dates and add 1 teaspoon soda.
Let cool. Cream together shortening, 1 cup sugar and eggs.
Add date mixture and mix well.
Add flour, salt and 3/4 teaspoon soda.
Mix well and put batter in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Top with chocolate chips, 1/2 cup sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together well.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Drop by spoonfuls in 375° deep fry.
When done, they will float.
Drain on paper towels.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add milk slowly and stir until smooth. Add slightly beaten egg yolks slowly and mix well.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly (be careful not to scorch) until mixture comes to a boil and thickens. Serve with vanilla wafers and Cool Whip.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Mix chicken, sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning. Layer refried beans, guacamole, chicken mixture, cheese, tomatoes and green onions. Top
with olives.
Chill for about 1 to 2 hours. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: ham noodle skillet
directions: Saute onion in oil until tender.
Add thinly sliced cabbage, stirring now and then.
Add brown sugar and vinegar.
Add cooked noodles, ham, butter, salt and pepper.
Blend all together. Simmer on low for about 1 hour.

title: chicken and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in 1 cup boiling water.
Combine cornstarch and 1/3 cup water, stirring well; stir into bouillon mixture and set aside.
Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces; set aside. Pour 2 tablespoons oil around top of wok.
Allow to heat at medium heat (325°) for 2 minutes.
Add vegetables, salt and ginger; stir-fry 4 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Remove from wok and set aside.
Pour 1 tablespoon oil around top of wok and heat to medium-high for 2 minutes.
Add chicken and stir-fry for one or two minutes or until chicken is light brown. Return vegetables to wok.
Pour bouillon mixture over chicken and vegetables, stirring well.
Reduce heat to 225° and simmer 2 or 3 minutes.
Serve over chow mein noodles.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Thinly coat the fillets with mayonnaise, dredge them in bread crumbs and arrange in baking pan.
Sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper.
Bake at 450° for about 15 minutes.
Serve with lemon wedges as garnish.

title: oriental steak
directions: Combine soy sauce, honey, vinegar, oil, ginger and minced garlic to make marinade.
Put steak into a plastic bag; pour in marinade.
Tie bag and place in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Take steak out of bag and brush with browning sauce. Broil to desired degree of doneness.
Serve.

title: granny white's tea cakes
directions: If shortening is used, add 1/2 teaspoon of salt.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar together in a separate bowl.
Grease Bundt pan and sprinkle bottom of pan with chopped nuts.
Cut first pan of biscuits into fourths and lay on top of the nuts.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of cinnamon sugar mixture over biscuits.
Repeat with remaining 2 cans of biscuits.
Melt margarine.
Stir in brown sugar and cinnamon.
Simmer for 2 minutes.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
When done, remove from oven and invert onto a large plate.
Excellent for breakfast or brunch.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skin until tender.
Drain and cool before slicing.
Add onions, oil, salt and pepper.
Chop bacon into small pieces and fry until done.
Drain bacon.
Mix vinegar, water and sugar.
Pour over bacon and heat to boiling.
Pour hot mixture over potatoes.
Stir gently.
Best when served warm.

title: chocolate roll
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch jelly roll pan; line with wax paper.
Grease and lightly flour paper.
Beat yolks until thick (set aside).
Sift sugar and cocoa together. Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add salt; beat until egg whites form stiff peaks and fold sugar and egg whites into cocoa.
Fold 1/3 egg white mixture into yolks.
Fold in rest of egg white mixture. Spread evenly into pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Turn cake onto clean kitchen towel; roll with towel and let set a few minutes.
Unroll; let set and re-roll and let cool.
Unroll; spread with sweetened whipped cream.
Roll up again without towel.
Dust top with powdered sugar.
Add strawberries or favorite fruit.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add the vanilla.

title: white chocolate pretzels
directions: Melt white chocolate in microwave or double boiler.
With tongs, dip pretzels, one at a time, in chocolate.
Let chocolate run off back into pan.
Place dipped pretzels on wax paper to cool. Melt the semi-sweet chocolate.
Cool several minutes.
Use a plastic bag with the tip snipped off or a large spoon. Drizzle chocolate over coated pretzels.
Chill.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine
flour	and sugar.
Heat butter, cocoa and Coke until it	boils.	Pour over sugar and flour mixture. Mix.
Add buttermilk,
eggs, soda, vanilla and marshmallows.	Beat well. Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Ice while hot.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into pie shell (unbaked). Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes, then turn back to 350° for about 30 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: pecan roll
directions: Butter Bundt pan or angel food cake pan.
Sprinkle nuts evenly in
pan and between biscuits.
Cut biscuits into quarters and shake
in
sugar and cinnamon.
Drop into pan.
Take rest of cinnamon, sugar, margarine and corn syrup and combine in a saucepan;
bring to a boil.
Pour over biscuits and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes; turn out on plate.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound meat to 1/4-inch thickness.
In paper or plastic bag, mix flour, salt and pepper.
Shake meat in bag until coated. Place meat in 2-quart square casserole.
Mix tomatoes, onion, dressing and rosemary; pour over meat.
Place green pepper rings on top of meat and cover.
Microwave at 50% (Medium) for 25 minutes.
Turn meat over; spoon sauce over meat and microwave, covered, at 50% (Medium) for 15 to 25 minutes or until meat is tender.
Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Cook mixed vegetables until tender.
Drain; place in a large bowl.
Add kidney beans, celery, onion and green pepper.

title: carbonara
directions: Cut bacon into cubes.
Separate eggs.
Use whites for another recipe.
Slightly beat yolks.
Whisk in cream.
Add grated cheese and salt.
Put bacon and grease into pan and saute until crisp at edges.
Pepper it.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix well.
Cover and let stand 24 hours.

title: cheese cake
directions: Chill Pet milk and whip with sugar.
Dissolve lemon jello in boiling water; chill.
Add jello to whipped milk and whip again. Add vanilla.
Take graham crackers and crush.
Add oleo and mix. Put 3/4 of graham cracker mixture in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Put remainder of cracker mixture on top.
Refrigerate.
This freezes well.

title: cheesy fish fillets
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Grease/spray a 9-inch square baking pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Arrange fish in pan.
Sprinkle with pepper and butter.
Pour soup over all.
Top with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: teeny fruit muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients together and pour batter into mini muffin pans. Bake for about 30 minutes.

title: 6 cans casserole
directions: Bake long time at low temperature or shorter time at higher temperature.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: chocolate-peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: In processor or blender, process cookies and peanuts to fine crumbs.
Add margarine; process to mix thoroughly.
Press mixture firmly over bottom and up sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Place crust in freezer 15 minutes.

title: toll house chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
In another bowl, thoroughly stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add flour mixture to cream mixture and beat well.
Stir in morsels, walnuts and one teaspoon hot water.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Makes 6 dozen 2 1/4-inch cookies.

title: easy chocolate delight pie
directions: Heat all but 3 squares chocolate with 1/4 cup milk in heavy saucepan over very low heat.
Stir until completely melted.

title: hershey chocolate bar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, brown sugar, egg, flour and vanilla.
Press on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (or until lightly browned). After removing from oven, and while still warm, top with chocolate bars to melt.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: pumpkin cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar.
Add spices and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in pumpkin, milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Chill and serve with whipped cream.

title: refrigerator (potato) rolls
directions: Cream the Crisco, sugar and mashed potatoes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add potato water, cooled to room temperature.
Add yeast mixture and stir well.
Cover with a damp cloth and let stand one hour.
After the hour, add flour and salt, stirring well (1 or 2 cups at a time).
Keep adding flour until you have a stiff dough.
Turn dough onto floured board and knead well.
Place in refrigerator in a covered container.
Make rolls as needed.
Place in well-greased pan and let rise until double in size.
Brush tops with melted butter and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: tea cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and flour a little at a time.
Bake at 350° until light and brown.

title: lasagna
directions: In a larger pan, boil lasagna noodles until they start to turn white.
In a large frying pan, brown hamburger; drain grease and add both jars of spaghetti sauce.
Simmer on low heat.

title: plain pastry pie dough
directions: Sift the flour and salt together.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender.
Sprinkle water a tablespoon at a time and mix with a fork.
Form into a ball, put on lightly floured board and roll very thin.
Roll onto rolling pin and unroll over pie pan. Even edges and flute.
(Save some of the dough for lattice on fruit pies.)

title: baked beans
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight.
Rinse beans again and place in a baking dish, covering with water.
Stir in sugar, salt and pepper.
Cut salt pork into 4 pieces and place on top of beans. Bake beans at 350°
for approximately 4 hours.
Check beans periodically, stirring and adding water as needed.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Pour sugar onto cranberries. Let stand overnight. Mix with pineapple, Cool Whip and marshmallows. Chill before serving.

title: potato and ham soup
directions: Cook potatoes covered with water. Cook until tender. Add cheese, cream of chicken soup and milk.
Mix. Bring to a boil. Salt and pepper.

title: old fashioned walnut sour cream cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, grated rind and lemon juice. Continue beating until light and fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream. Blend well.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar and top with walnut halves. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: artichoke, green chile dip
directions: Chop artichokes.
Mix with mayo, Parmesan and chiles.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly and cheese melts.
Serve hot with crackers or corn chips.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Mix the cake mix, margarine and 1 egg; pat into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix the cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar; pour over first mixture in pan.
Sprinkle with the pecans, if desired. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Mix well and pour over slaw.
Also good on potato salad.

title: choco-crispies
directions: Melt
together
first
3 ingredients in microwave.
Add and mix
powdered sugar and vanilla.
In 13 x 9-inch buttered pan
mix ingredients
and add 4 cups Rice Krispies.
Let cool and then cut into squares.

title: pork chops with apples
directions: Trim the fat from 6 thick loin pork chops and season them lightly with a mixture of salt, freshly ground pepper and powdered rosemary.
In a skillet, brown the chops well on both sides in 1 tablespoon butter.
Place them in one layer in a shallow baking dish and cover them with 3 tart apples, peeled, cored and sliced.

title: tootie bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Slice bread into 16 slices, but not all the way through to the bottom. Cut cheese diagonally into halves. Place cheese between slices of bread. Place bread on a foil-covered baking sheet. Mix margarine, onion, mustard and poppy seeds. Spread mixture over the top and sides. Sprinkle with bacon. Bake 20 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes.
Mash with a fork.
Add mashed eggs, minced onion, relish, mustard and pepper.
Mix with mayonnaise. Refrigerate until served.

title: chicken rice-a-roni
directions: Brown rice from box in butter; add hot water and flavor packet from box.
When rice is done, add chicken.
Cook on low until moisture absorbs.

title: marge's cole slaw
directions: Cut green pepper and onion into thin rings.
Combine with shredded cabbage.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over mixture.

title: white pie
directions: Cook all ingredients except egg white mixture until thickened. Fold in egg whites.
Pour into cooled pie shells.
Chill and top with Cool Whip and chopped pecans.

title: salsa, spaghetti soup
directions: Optional:
Small chunks of cooked beef, pork or chicken; red kidney beans or green lima beans or string beans.

title: sherry chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken breasts; dip in melted butter and place in shallow baking dish.
Pour sherry over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Mix well the soup, parsley, paprika, mayonnaise and sour cream.
Add juice from chicken and mix well.
Remove chicken from bone and cut into bite size pieces.
Pour 1/2 of liquid into rice in 13 x 9-inch baking dish; stir well.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Pour remaining liquid over chicken.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: wagoner's chinese egg soup
directions: Heat broth to simmer.
While waiting, whip 4 eggs in a bowl, also whip starch with 2 spoons cold water.
Pour eggs into hot broth slowly, stirring often.
When heat returns, pour in starch. Mix in corned beef; stir a few times.
When hot and mixed, stir in green onions (optional).
Serve.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut the Crisco into the flour, salt and sugar.
Stir well the egg, water and vinegar and cut this mixture into flour.
Roll out dough in usual fashion for pie crust.

title: fiesta chicken
directions: Boil whole chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bones.
Mix in saucepan the soup, taco sauce, milk, grated onion, chili powder and cumin to taste.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Cut up chicken and mix through sauce; heat through.

title: cinnamon-raisin coffee cake
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until blended.
Combine egg, milk and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture, stirring until blended. Set batter aside.
Combine brown sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, cinnamon and raisins.
Stir in melted oleo. Set brown sugar mixture aside.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon and onion in skillet until crispy.
Stir in flour. Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain and mash about 1/2 cup potatoes against pot.
Add bacon, onion and flour mixture.
Put in water and liquid for clams.
Stir in clams and half and half.
Season; cook on low heat until bubbly.

title: stir-n-roll pastry
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix together flour and salt.
Pour into a measuring cup (but don't stir) vegetable oil and cold milk, then pour all at once into flour.
Stir lightly until mixed.
Round up dough.
Divide in halves.
Flatten each half slightly.
Roll between waxed paper.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook and drain carrots.
Mix ingredients, cook until thick. Pour sauce over carrots and let stand a short time.
Serve hot.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except last 4 ingredients and cook on low heat in a large skillet or electric skillet 2 hours.
Last 15 minutes, thicken with cornstarch and add green pepper and sliced olives.
Add mandarin oranges just before serving.

title: adrienne's delight(ms.  thermon smith, little rock, arkansas)
directions: Let cream cheese, butter and sour cream come to room temperature.
Cream well and add sugar.
Soften gelatin in cold water, dissolve over hot water and add to cream cheese mixture. Then add raisins, almonds and lemon rind.
Put in quart mold, refrigerate.
When firm, unmold and serve with saltine crackers. (This may be frozen after unmolding.)

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine hamburger, rice, seasonings and onion.
Roll into balls.
Drop into hot tomato soup and water in a pot.
Cook slowly for 1 hour.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: topsy-turvey coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in vanilla and orange rind.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.

title: triple good bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In medium saucepan, combine raisins, condensed milk, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture starts to bubble.
Remove from heat; cool slightly and set aside.
Beat margarine, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients; blend until evenly mixed and crumbly. Reserve 2 cups.
Press remaining mixture onto bottom of prepared pan.
Spread raisin mixture to within 1/2-inch of edge of pan. Sprinkle with remaining oat mixture; pat lightly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all of the ingredients together. Pour into greased and floured baking pan/pans.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Allow cake to cool completely and frost with your favorite icing.

title: pickled cauliflower
directions: Cut cauliflower, onions and carrots in small sections, and cook until tender, but not mushy; drain.
In a large pan, add vegetables and equal parts of sugar and vinegar to almost cover. Add turmeric, bring to a boil and spoon into clean jars.
Seal while hot.

title: mock hollandaise sauce
directions: In top of a double boiler blend together the cottage cheese, water and lemon juice.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Add beaten egg yolks and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir constantly over simmering water until the sauce is thick.
Serve hot.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers, onions, peppers and garlic with salt poured over ice water for 3 hours; drain.
Heat cucumber mixture, sugar, vinegar and spices to boiling.
They will turn yellow.
Seal in jars.

title: squash cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients last, then add chocolate bits.

title: apricot jello
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil (including the juice). Add jello and dissolve. Let cool completely.
Add buttermilk and stir well. Whisk in Cool Whip until smooth and pour into a mold.

title: microwave breakfast oatmeal(heart healthy)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in microwave-safe dish.
Add rest of ingredients.
Microwave in covered dish for about 8 minutes. Serve with milk.

title: old fashioned peanut brittle
directions: Cook and stir sugar, corn syrup and water in heavy bottomed 2-quart saucepan over high heat until sugar dissolves. Cook, without stirring, until mixture reaches 300° (hard-crack stage), about 5 minutes. Stir in peanuts, margarine, vanilla and baking soda. Quickly spread in thin layer on greased baking sheet; cool. Break into pieces; store in airtight container for up to 2 weeks. Makes 1 pound.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Will need a 15 x 10 x 2-inch cookie sheet.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients except beef and bread. Now mix in well the ground beef.
Add bread cubes.
Mix.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Place on rack in pan and bake at 350° about 1 hour until brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, milk and butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until soft ball is formed when tested in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow.
Stir until well combined.
Pour into buttered pan. Cool and cut into blocks.
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend with electric mixer cream cheese, cottage cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread on serving platter and cover with shredded lettuce, then layer of chopped tomatoes and last of shredded cheese.
More cheese can be added.

title: rhubarb-pineapple jam
directions: Cut rhubarb into small pieces.
Combine rhubarb, pineapple and sugar.
Cook over low heat until thick and rhubarb is tender.
Add jello and simmer a few more minutes.

title: mom's christmas cookies
directions: Mix together with your hands until right consistency.
Roll out very thin and cut with cookie cutters.

title: favorite fruit cups
directions: Mix first five fruits in a bowl.
Spoon into paper cups.
Top with shredded coconut.
Clean up.
Serve and enjoy.
Makes enough for 5.

title: swedish pork cutlets
directions: Cook as much rice as you need to serve your family.
(We cook 1 cup of raw rice for our family of three).

title: spicy baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Mix all ingredients together and bake at 300° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: trash
directions: Melt oleo, chocolate chips and peanut butter in double boiler (or over low heat) just until melted and mixed together.
Pour over Crispix in large bowl (looks terrible).
Gently fold until all the cereal is covered.
Take white kitchen garbage bag and put half of the powdered sugar in the bottom of the bag.
Put cereal mixture into bag and put remainder of powdered sugar on top.
Tie bag shut and gently shake bag until cereal separates and the pieces are coated with the powdered sugar.
After cooling, store in airtight container.
Lasts several weeks.
Delicious.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery, onion and salt in 2 cups water about 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Lightly mash potatoes and continue to cook, stirring constantly, until soup is hot and thickened.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Put ingredients in baking dish.
Salt and pepper to desire.
Cook 1 hour at 400°.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Leave butter out all night in a covered bowl.
When it is nice and creamy, add sugar.
Beat a few minutes, then add 1 cup flour at a time.
It gets lumpy, so put it on a cookie sheet and pat it smooth with your hands.
Then cut in squares and bake in a slow oven until golden brown.
Remove from oven and with knife, go over the lines again.
(I use a cookie sheet with sides.)

title: chicken scampi
directions: In saucepan with salted water, place broccoli and steam 4 minutes.
Boil linguine and drain.
In large frypan, place butter and olive oil over medium heat.
Add onion and pepper and saute 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and reserve.
To frypan, add chicken. Continue to cook, stirring about 5 minutes.
Return onion and pepper to frypan.
Add cooked broccoli and saute for 5 more minutes.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Place linguine in serving dish, top with chicken vegetable mixture and sprinkle with cheese.

title: corn pudding
directions: Place butter in casserole to melt.
In blender, mix eggs, dry ingredients and 1 cup milk.
Blend, add corn.
Turn on-off to chop corn slightly.
Pour in buttered casserole.
Add other cup of milk.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Stir 3 times at 10 minute intervals the first 30 minutes.

title: chili con carne
directions: Cook ground beef and onion and drain.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add kidney beans, tomato or tomato sauce, ketchup, garlic powder, chili powder, paprika, oregano, cumin and cayenne pepper. Simmer approximately 30 minutes.

title: low-fat pancakes or waffles
directions: Mix all ingredients together; beat for 2 minutes.
Cook in nonstick pan, using a no-stick cooking spray.
Cook until golden brown.
Makes approximately 12 pancakes or waffles.

title: five cup fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruits.
Mix together and refrigerate overnight. Add marshmallows last.
Refrigerate.

title: morning glorious muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt in a mixing bowl.
In a second bowl, combine carrots, apples, coconut, dates and pecans.
Stir in eggs, oil and vanilla. Add to dry ingredients until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins which will freeze nicely.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti, not completely cooked.
Drain.
Mix butter and Parmesan cheese to form spaghetti into pie shell.
Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Alternate with hamburger mixture, cottage cheese and sauce.
Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375°.
Use 1 small cake pan (9 x 13-inch) or 2 (9-inch) pie pans.

title: 100 year old german slaw dressing
directions: Cook together water and sugar until it spins thread.
Remove from heat and add vinegar, onion juice or grated onion, salt and celery seed.
This dressing will keep a month or more in the refrigerator.
Toss with shredded cabbage to serve.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in coconut.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat the daylights out of them! Drop onto ungreased cookie sheets and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: puffy chile rellenos
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Cut chilies lengthwise to make 10 pieces.
Remove seeds and ribs.
Rinse and drain.
Cut cheese into ten 3 x 1/2 x 1/2-inch pieces.
Wrap each piece of cheese with a chili.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits; press or roll each to a 5-inch circle.
Place 1 chile-wrapped cheese piece on each biscuit.
Fold dough over piece of cheese; pinch to seal.
Form each into a finger-shaped roll; place seam-side up on prepared sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bring to a boil, water and margarine; stir in flour until it forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs one at a time; beat with electric mixer.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Beat cream cheese until smooth; add French vanilla pudding and milk.
Spread pudding mixture over top of cake.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into prepared 10-inch pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake at 425° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: creamy hash brown casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine the soups, sour cream, margarine, onion and salt.
Add potatoes; mix well.
Pour into a greased 13x9x2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with potato chips.
Bake, uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven, sprinkle with cheese, if desired.
Return to oven and resume baking for another 10 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: jim's honey barbecued chicken
directions: Mix honey and oil well in a small bowl; set aside.
Season cleaned chicken with salt, pepper and Old Bay seasoning.
Place chicken, skin side up, on grill 5 to 7-inches from medium-hot coals.
Grill 30 to 40 minutes.
Turn about every 10 minutes and baste with honey mixture.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients; roll or pat out to 1-inch thickness.
Cut into biscuits.
Let rise for 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: fish cakes
directions: Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper.

Add the potatoes, parsley, butter and egg. Shape into flat round cakes. Roll in fine bread crumbs, then the egg mixed with 1 tablespoon milk, then again in bread crumbs. Fry both sides in deep oil until brown. Serve hot with lemon slices.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in a pan and bring to a boil.
Let simmer 30 minutes.
Enough for 4 whole chickens or 8 halves.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes (no longer).

title: poppy seed ham roll
directions: Combine butter and next 4 ingredients. Without separating the rolls, slice the rolls in half so there is a top and a bottom. Brush butter mixture on the cut sides of bread.
On bottom half, layer ham, cheese and remaining ham.
Replace top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cut into small sandwiches and serve hot.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add liquids.
Beat all together. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: roulade of beef fenelon
directions: Flatten steak by pounding.
Brown sausage and onion in frying pan.
Reserve 2 tablespoons fat for browning the steak.
Add bread crumbs to sausage and brown slightly.
Add water and mix.
Spread seasonings and sausage mixture over the surface of the flattened steak; then roll up and fasten with toothpicks or string.
Brown the steak roll on all sides in iron skillet in the 2 tablespoons reserved fat and bake in moderate oven until tender, about 2 hours.

title: kay's jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add orange juice (don't dilute).
Add in crushed pineapple along with the juice.
Add cut up apples, pecans and cranberries.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Heat milk.
In separate pan, melt 3 tablespoons butter then add flour and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Add heated milk; whip until lumps are mostly gone.
Simmer 3 minutes until thickened, stir occasionally.
Add Parmesan cheese; mix well.
Add pepper and remaining butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine soup and cheese.
Cook until melted.
Add sour cream. Pour over cooked and sliced potato slices.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: dolly parton crumb cake
directions: Follow directions on the box except add one extra egg.
Bake in a cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: giant pizzazz cookie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour and baking soda; set aside.
Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture just blending.
Dough will be crumbly. Pat dough evenly into greased 12-inch round pizza pan (or 9 x 13-inch pan).
Prick crust with fork.
Bake 15 to 16 minutes or until firm.
Combine M&M's mini baking bits, coconut and peanuts. Spread warm crust evenly with caramel topping.
Sprinkle evenly with combined chocolate, coconut and nut mixture.
Pat lightly. Bake 5 minutes or until coconut begins to turn golden; cool completely.
Cut into wedges; makes 16 wedges.

title: vera's "more" casserole
directions: Prepare and mix first 6 ingredients.
Place in large baking dish (or two medium).
Bake at 350° to 400° until hot through. Top with Fritos and then sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake until hot and cheese melts.

title: pudding in a cloud
directions: Spoon 1/2 cup of whipped topping into each of 6 dessert glasses.
Using back of spoon, make depressions in center and spread topping up sides of glasses.
Prepare pudding mix with milk as directed on package.
Spoon pudding mixture into glasses; chill.

title: delicious banana cake
directions: Mash bananas and mix with baking soda.
Mix in cake mix, water, eggs and oil.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add nuts.
Grease a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 - 35 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.

title: gay's elegant mushroom soup
directions: Saute green onions and mushrooms in butter in Dutch oven until onions are tender. Stir in flour. Gradually add milk and water to mushroom mixture, stirring well. Add bouillon granules and cook over low heat 10 minutes or just until thoroughly heated, stirring frequently.
Yields 4 cups.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour in buttered casserole.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Have the coconut ready in a bowl.
Add the vanilla or almond extract and salt.
Combine these with the sweetened condensed milk.
Make a thick paste.
These are much improved by folding into the batter the stiffly beaten egg whites. Roll into balls, or drop by teaspoon onto a well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned around edges.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Beat margarine and sugar.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks.
Add pecans and fruit with part of flour.
Add soda to warm water. Beat into mixture of margarine and sugar.
Add lemon extract. Add fruit and flour mixture.
Beat egg whites.
Mix in egg whites, alternating with rest of flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ice cream frosting
directions: Mix all together in mixer and beat for 5 minutes or thickness to frost cake.

title: apple bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add apples, nuts and coconut; blend.
Add in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done when tested.

title: lamboll street shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bread crumbs and 1/4 cup margarine.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with bead crumbs and remaining margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: the world's best cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add egg; mix well.
Add salad oil and vanilla, mixing well.
Add oats, cornflakes, coconut and nuts, stirring well.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheets. Flatten with a fork dipped in water.
Bake for 12 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheets for a few minutes before removing.
Makes 8 dozen. They stay moist and keep beautifully.

title: divinity
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan stir together sugar, corn syrup, water and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stir constantly until mix boils.
Reduce heat and cook without stirring until temperature reaches 248° on candy thermometer or until it forms a firm ball when you drop in some cold water.
Just before temperature reaches 248°, beat egg whites in large bowl until soft but not dry.
Beat constantly on high speed, slowly pour about 1/2 of the hot syrup over egg whites.
Cook remaining syrup to 272°, until mixture dropped in very cold water separates into threads which are hard, but not brittle.
Beating constantly, pour syrup over first mixture, about 1 teaspoon at a time.
Beat well after addition. Beat until mixture looks like it is glossy.
Serves 8.

title: cheese roll
directions: Grate cheese.
Blend in seasoning and onions.
Add ground nuts last.
Knead like bread; form in rolls in wax paper.
Sprinkle paper with paprika; roll to coat.
Reroll in wax paper; store in refrigerator.
Serve with crackers.

title: meringue topped yams
directions: Mix yams and beaten egg yolk until smooth.
Blend in butter, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Place in a dish sprayed with Pam.
Top with meringue of beaten egg white and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together the margarine, 1 egg and cake mix.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Combine eggs and cherries.
Blend with spoon.
Stir in dry cake mix.
When mixed well the batter should be similar to brownie batter.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.
Check with a toothpick.
Cool.
Then frost with milk chocolate frosting.
This is a very moist cake.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, cool and remove desired meat.
In 9 x 11-inch casserole dish, combine chicken (cooked), rice, soup and drained Veg-All.
Smooth mixture and unroll crescent rolls on top.
Bake according to directions of crescent roll can.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls in a jelly roll pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until brown. Cool. Blend cream cheese, dressing and mayonnaise.
Spread on crust.
Top with diced raw vegetables. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, sour cream, soup and onions.
Pour into casserole dish (about 9 x 13-inch).
Sprinkle with cheese. Combine margarine and corn flakes.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mother's jelly pie
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, egg yolks, jelly and milk.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in 325° oven until firm.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix together Raisin Bran, sugar, flour, salt and baking soda. Add eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full (or use paper baking cups).
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mixture will keep in refrigerator for 6 weeks.
Muffins are better if mixture sets in refrigerator overnight.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, cottage cheese and Cool Whip; fold in drained canned fruit.
(Refrigerate.)

title: mozzarella chicken(over sauce)
directions: Cut chicken into serving size pieces.
Dip into eggs; coat with crumbs.
Heat butter in skillet.
Cook chicken over medium heat until brown.
Stir in tomato sauce and basil.
Reduce heat; cover and cook over low heat for about 30 minutes, turning chicken every 10 minutes.
Prepare sauce.
Put noodles in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange chicken on top.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese and paprika.
Broil 6 to 7 inches from broiler until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: georgia pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add salt, beaten eggs, syrup and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into uncooked pastry shell.
Pecans will float to surface.
Spread these with grated orange rind.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until done.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Saute onion, green onion tops and bell pepper.
Melt cream cheese.
Mix in crabmeat.

title: daddy's favorite spanish rice
directions: Melt fat in skillet.
Add onion, pepper, beef and rice.
Stir over high heat until lightly brown.
Add tomato sauce.
Stir.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Bring quickly to a boil. Reduce heat and cover lightly.
Simmer 25 minutes.
For precooked rice, simmer 10 minutes.

title: easy hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Drain any fat.
Add tomato soup and green beans (with liquid).
Mix together and pour into baking dish.
Top with potatoes.
Spread to cover meat mixture.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: quick classy casserole
directions: Crumble the ground beef into a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with rice and soup mix. Combine soup, water and green peas; pour over rice. Spread onion tops over mixture; cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Chop green pepper and onion into small pieces and put in frypan with 1/4 stick oleo for saute.
Put tomatoes and paste (with 1 can water to paste) in large pot and heat.
Add salt and pepper to tomato mix.
Add green pepper and onion mix to tomatoes and enough chili powder to taste.
Cook 2 hours.
Brown hamburger, drain and add to tomatoes.
Cook 1 hour or so.
Cook spaghetti and add to mix.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.
(Does not have to be refrozen, but may be kept in the refrigerator.)

title: breakfast sundaes(healthier than boxed cereal!)
directions: Layer ingredients in sundae glasses alternating layers.
Top with broken walnuts.
Serve immediately.

title: beef brisket
directions: Sprinkle last 5 seasonings on both sides of brisket.
Place brisket in cake pan.
Pour liquid smoke over meat and let set overnight.
Seal with Saran Wrap.
Pour off but a little liquid and wrap in foil and save liquid.
Bake at 350° for 4 hours.
The last 30 minutes add barbecue sauce and leave off foil.

title: sweet n' sour meatballs
directions: Soak white bread in bouillon.
Mash bread into meat.
Pour both kinds of sauce into frying pan and mix well.
Form meat into 1-inch balls and dip into cold sauce.
Heat sauce on low heat and cook meatballs, turning until all sides are cooked.
Simmer in sauce for about 2 hours or until sauce is thick, dark and glazed.
Stir occasionally.
Drain off fat.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Blend dry ingredients.
Add oil and remaining ingredients. Blend well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not too dry, adding sugar and salt as you beat.
Fold in chips and nuts.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Place in oven.
Turn heat off and leave overnight or for several hours.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Place cheese, zucchini and onion in a large bowl.
Mix the remaining ingredients in a separate bowl and add to the zucchini. Blend well.
Lightly grease an 8 x 11 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add the mixture and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pot roast for diabetics
directions: Dredge meat well in flour, salt and pepper. Brown in oil in skillet. Add remaining ingredients, cover and simmer about 4 hours over low heat.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly add sugar.
Combine with nuts, baking powder, crackers, and vanilla.
Mix well.
Grease pie pan.
Pour mixture in pie pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Let cool completely.
Top with Cool Whip.
Serve.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In a medium bowl, combine sugar, mustard, salt, vinegar and onion juice. Beat in oil until thick and smooth. Stir in poppy seed.

title: cucumber salad with buttermilk dressing
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together the buttermilk, yogurt, dill, cider vinegar and honey.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until blended.
Chill.

title: mustard chicken
directions: Combine milk and mustard.
Set aside.
Combine bread crumbs and spices on wax paper.
Set aside.
Rinse chicken breasts and dry.
Dip into milk/ mustard mixture, allowing excess to drip off. Roll in bread crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet sprayed with no stick spray; skin side up.
Spray chicken again with no stick spray.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes until chicken juices run clear at 350°.

title: marvelous minis(for kids)
