directions: Place 18 of the waffles or cookies on your work surface. Spread 1 tablespoon of softened ice cream on top of the mini cookie or waffle and place another cookie or waffle on top of the ice cream. Smooth the edges of sandwich and place on a tray in the freezer.
Repeat with remaining cookies and freeze.
Makes 18 mini snacks.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Mix flour, crumbs, oleo and nuts; press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°, then cool.
Cream the cheese with sugar and fold into the prepared Cool Whip.
Pour into cooled crust and chill.
Top with pie filling.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mom's chocolate candy 2
directions: Melt chocolate chips and milk over low heat. Remove from heat and add nuts and vanilla. Pour in a 8x8 inch pan. Chill until firm.

title: fiesta corn chowder
directions: Brown bacon; put aside.
Lightly brown onion, celery and green pepper.
Cook potatoes and broth for 10 minutes.
Add corn and milk; then add bacon, onion, celery and green pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Season with black pepper. Then garnish.

title: baked seashells marinara
directions: In nonstick skillet, saute onion and garlic in oil 5 minutes. Stir in parsley, basil and pepper; saute 2 minutes.
In small saucepan, combine half of onion mixture, tomato sauce and water. Set aside.
Add spinach to remaining onion mixture in skillet. Stir over medium heat just until spinach is thawed and warmed through.
Remove from heat.
Mix in Ricotta, 1 tablespoon grated cheese and salt.
Fill shell with Ricotta mixture.
Simmer tomato sauce mixture 5 minutes.
Spoon half into shallow 1-quart baking dish.
Arrange shells in dish.
Spoon remaining tomato sauce over shells; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover loosely with foil and bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix cheese, sugar, vanilla, juice and egg yolk.
Spread 1 package rolls on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread cheese mixture over.
Lay other package of rolls on top.
Brush with egg white. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes; cover with foil.
Bake 10 more minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cream all ingredients except nuts.
Add nuts and form into large roll.
Chill.
Slice and bake 10-20 minutes at 350°.

title: date balls
directions: Cook butter, dates, coconut and sugar over low heat.
Let come to a bubble and cook 6 minutes.
Add the Rice Krispies and chopped pecans.
Make small balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: flan (custard)
directions: Bring
milk to boil and set aside to
cool.
Beat
eggs until frothy.
Add sugar, salt, nutmeg,
anise
and
vanilla extracts, then add milk that is cool.
Place
a
half teaspoon of brown sugar in each custard cup.
Pour milk and egg mixture into
each cup.
Place on a rack on top of
a
pan
of
water. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until firm.

title: raisin cookie bars
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and shortening.
Add raisins and the dry ingredients and the boiling water.
When cool, I spread a light glaze over.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut hot potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out potatoes, leaving skins intact for re-stuffing.
With wire whisk, beat potatoes with cottage cheese, milk and onion.
Spoon mixture back into skins.
Sprinkle with paprika, parsley flakes and black pepper.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Cut slice from tops of green or red apples; scoop out the inside pulp, leaving just enough to hold the skin in place.
Fill the shells with salad mixture and serve on lettuce leaves.
A little salad dressing may be put on top of each.
The apple, cut in cubes, celery and nut mixture may be served on lettuce with salad dressing.

title: pudding salad
directions: Mix all fruit together.
Stir into pudding.
Stir vigorously and chill.

title: dressed up chicken
directions: Place chicken (seasoned) in a casserole dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Sprinkle mushrooms over chicken.
Combine soup, sherry and sour cream; spread over chicken and mushrooms.
Cover; cook in a 350° oven until tender.
You can remove cover and brown chicken, if desired.
This makes a delicious recipe to serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into balls.
Cook on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: ham and potato soup
directions: In a 4-quart container, assemble all ingredients (except salt), taking care not to heat milk beyond scalding.
Cook for 90 minutes over a low to medium fire, stirring occasionally, since the potatoes take the longest to cook.
Add salt gradually until it suits your taste.
Adjust other seasonings, if desired.
Fresh vegetables and the leanest ham are recommended.

title: quick apple cake(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray 8-inch square pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In medium bowl, beat margarine and sugar until well blended.
Add egg; beat well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon, allspice and milk; beat just until moistened.
Stir in apple. Spread batter evenly in spray-coated pan.
Sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm cake squares with Light Caramel Sauce.
Makes 9 servings.
Calories:
6 grams.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Heat water and margarine to 120°.
In a large bowl combine 3 cups of flour, yeast, sugar, salt, dry milk, eggs and warm water mixture.
Mix well.

Gradually add enough remaining flour to form a moderately stiff dough. Turn out onto floured board and knead for about 10 minutes until "blisters" form on dough, adding only enough flour to keep dough from sticking to board.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 30 minutes.
Punch dough down and make into cinnamon rolls.

title: island style party mix
directions: Mix ingredients in large brown bag.

title: stir-fry sauce no. 1
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Combine last 4 ingredients and let stand for 10 minutes.
Blend mixtures and add to wok.

title: chili con carne
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add chopped pepper.
Add ground beef and cook until browned, breaking up lumps.
Add herbs and spices; mix well.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste.
If chili gets too thick, add some water.
Best served the next day with Italian or garlic bread.

title: delicious cheese cake
directions: Put cheese in bowl; mix until soft.
Add sugar, a little at a time; blend on low.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Add 2 eggs at a time while you are still beating batter.
Grease a spring-form pan. Pour thin batter into it.
Fill another larger pan with cold water. Put spring-form pan into larger pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Shut off oven.
Gently open oven door; leave in another 1/2 hour.
Refrigerate for a few hours.
Top with cherries or blueberries.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Put crackers in milk. Combine beef with crackers, salt, pepper, egg and onion. Shape in oval patties and brown in butter. Place in baking pan or dish. Stir 1/4 cup skillet drippings with flour. Dissolve cubes in water and add slowly until mixture thickens. Pour over steak. Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 325°.

title: boneless pork with gravy
directions: Get a piece of boneless pork shoulder, 3/4 inch thick, that will roll up to be about 4 inches in diameter and about 1 foot long.
Before rolling, combine nutmeg, caraway seed, salt and pepper.
Rub the side that will be on the inside of the roll.
Roll up meat and tie in 3 places with twine.
Mix together the same amount of seasonings as before but adding the paprika.
Rub the outside of the pork roll.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Place roast in a roasting pan with the 1/2 cup water. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes per pound of meat.
Turn roast to brown on all sides, adding water if needed.
Meat will be done when a meat thermometer inserted in roast reads 185°.
Make gravy from drippings in pan.

title: best cookie cutter sugar cookies
directions: In a large bowl mix the first 4 ingredients.
Then blend in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Roll out and cut as desired.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: aunt polly's candy
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, syrup, salt and milk.
Cook on low heat until Crisco melts.
Turn on high heat after it starts to boil, then boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and nuts. Place pan in cold water and beat until it thickens.
Drop on wax paper by spoonfuls.
Makes 2 or 3 dozen depending on their size.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: Mix all together and pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: short cut chili sauce
directions: Combine tomatoes, celery, onions, pepper and salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain in colander, but do not press.
Place vegetable mixture in large kettle.
Add sugar, brown sugar, pepper and spices (tied in a cheese bag) and vinegar.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 15 minutes.
Ladle into jars and seal; process in boiling water bath 15 minutes.
Makes 5 1/2 pints.

title: exotic peach salad
directions: Mix marshmallows, pineapple, coconut and sour cream together. Spoon into peach halves to serve.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix well.
Pour over cabbage, let set overnight.
Pour off liquid and it's ready to serve.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Boil pepperoni 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Saute onion in 1 1/3 tablespoons of oleo.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour rest of oleo into 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Toss spaghetti in oleo and add one can tomato sauce.
Toss again.
Add in order:
1/2 grated cheese, 1/2 pepperoni, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese, all mushrooms and all onion. Then sprinkle with oregano and basil.
Add rest of sauce, grated cheese, pepperoni and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

In a large bowl, beat eggs at high speed until foamy (about 3 minutes). Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until well blended. Beat in softened butter. Stir in nuts and chocolate chips. Pour into unbaked shell. Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between edge and center comes out clean and
top is golden brown. Cool on wire rack. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: basil pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine flour and garlic salt in bag; add chops and toss lightly until they are thoroughly coated. Brown chops in heavy skillet using just enough oil to cover bottom of the skillet.
Arrange chops in shallow ungreased baking dish without letting them overlap.
Sprinkle with basil.
Cover closely with foil.
Bake until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Skim off all fat.
Add wine or fruit juice.
Remove cover and continue to cook until liquid bubbles.

title: marinated carrot-onion salad
directions: Drain the chilled carrots and place in a flat dish.
Add the onion rings and mix.
Pour enough dressing to cover.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Serves 4 to 5 persons.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt 1 stick butter or margarine in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Layer the following ingredients in order listed over butter:
graham crackers, chocolate chips, coconut, butterscotch chips, chopped pecans and condensed milk.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool, then cut into squares.

title: fig cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour; mix. Add pecans and figs; mix.
Add coconut.
Mix.
Add soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: breakaway vegetable bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Dip each piece into melted butter and layer 1/3 in a lightly greased 6 cup Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of bacon, cheese, onion and green pepper mix.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used, ending with the biscuit layer. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: golden carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender.
Drain; reserve liquid.
Add water to make 1 cup.
Make a sauce from margarine, cornstarch, 1 cup water and pineapple juice.
Add salt and nutmeg. Fold in carrots and pineapple.
Serve hot.
(Works well to put in casserole and warm up next day in oven.)
Serves 8 to 10.

title: "crab" casserole
directions: Place bread cubes in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour beaten eggs and milk over them.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Mix together "crab," celery, onion, sliced mushrooms and mayonnaise.
Spread mixture over hot bread cubes, then spread the two cans of undiluted soup over "crab" mixture.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 275°.

title: cheesecake #1
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and butter; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 10 minutes.

title: roast beef au jus
directions: Let roast stand at room temperature for at least 1 hour. Preheat oven to 375°.
Place meat in shallow pan.
Do not cover or add water; cook 1 hour.
Turn off heat but do not open oven at any time until ready to serve.
Regardless of how long meat has been in oven, turn oven to 375° 40 minutes before serving.
Do not preheat.
Always medium-rare regardless of size of roast.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onion, green pepper and peas.
Top with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon bits on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: pizza cups
directions: Cook and drain hamburger with onion and pepper.
Season to taste.
Mix 1 1/2 cups of your favorite spaghetti sauce and 1 cup of shredded pizza cheese with cooked and drained hamburger.
Place 1 biscuit in each muffin cup and mold around the cup.
Place a full tablespoon of meat mixture in each cup and top with a teaspoon of sauce and a sprinkle of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Very good snack or for dinner with a salad.
Can be frozen and reheated in microwave.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together, then add butter and rest of liquids.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: june layer salad
directions: Cut lettuce enough to cover bottom of casserole.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar together.
Layer lettuce, celery, pepper, onion and peas.
Spread mayonnaise over the peas.
Cover with cheese.
Sprinkle bacon bits on top.
Cover with Glad Wrap and let set overnight.
Beat if made a day ahead.
Enjoy.

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, buttermilk, salt and butter in a saucepan. Cook until soft ball forms in cold water.
Take off of stove and let cool.
Beat until creamy.
Add nuts and vanilla; beat until consistency and easy to spread.
Pour into a buttered platter. Cut into squares when firm.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Cube cake to cover the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish. Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add strawberries to this mixture almost immediately.
Keep turning berries until thawed.
Pour mixture over cubed cake.
Chill until set.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump cherry pie filling in bottom of baking dish.
Dump crushed pineapple on the top of cherry pie filling.
Dump cake mix and crumble over top of pineapple and cherry.
Then cut up margarine into little pats and scatter them on top of cake mix. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cool, cut and serve.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well and pour into pie crust and bake at 425° for 15 minutes and then 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Stick a sharp pointed knife in center to see if done.

title: poor man's soup
directions: Fry pork until crisp.
Brown onion in fat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook slowly 1 to 2 hours.

title: lucky red
directions: Remove the stems and slice the strawberries.
Pour the soda into a glass; add the ice cream and add the strawberry slices. Serve with maraschino cherries speared on a toothpick.
Serves one.

title: apple cake with nuts
directions: Combine and bring to a boil.
Pour over cake while still warm.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Wash whole mushrooms and slice.
Add butter, onion and celery seed; simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Add bouillon cubes and boiling water and simmer uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Use jello dry.
Good with any fruit or lime jello and pineapple.

title: apricot jello mold
directions: Boil apricot Jell-O and pineapple; place in refrigerator and cool.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions; set aside.
(You can use Cool Whip.)
Whip the cream cheese, baby food apricots and sugar until fluffy.
Add pineapple mixture when cool.
Add Dream Whip and nuts.
Chill.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer all of these.
Let set for 3 hours.
Mix up and serve.

title: bavarian potatoes(non-dairy)
directions: Add salt and garlic to taste.
You may brown hot dogs in oil first if you wish.
Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creamy chicken enchiladas
directions: In a skillet or saucepan coated with nonstick cooking spray, saut onion until tender. Remove from the heat. Add soup, tomatoes, sour cream, 3/4 cup Cheddar cheese and 3/4 cup Mozzarella cheese and chicken; mix well. Place approximately 3 tablespoons on each tortilla. Roll up tightly. Place seam side down in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray. Top with remaining soup mixture; sprinkle with remaining cheeses. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.

title: coconut pie
directions: Soak coconut in milk and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, mix sugar, salt, flour, eggs and butter; mix well.
Add milk and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: best meat loaves
directions: Thoroughly mix meats.
Stir in onion, celery and seasonings, mixing well.
Soak bread cubes in milk, adding eggs to the milk and bread; beat with a rotary mixer.
Combine meat with egg, milk and bread mixture.
Form in two loaves.
Roll in dry bread crumbs. Place in greased shallow pans (2 pans) or one large one.
Score tops with knife.
Spread 1/2 cup chili sauce over each loaf.
Pour boiling water into pan, around the two loaves.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.
Serve hot, with favorite vegetables and salad or chill, slice and serve with mustard, etc., as sandwich material. Serves about 4 to 6, maybe 8 to 10, depending on servings.

title: date nut bars
directions: Cook sugar, egg and margarine until thick.
Pour over nuts

title: country stew
directions: Sprinkle flour over meat (water).
Bake steak in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, or until almost done.
Add potatoes; cook 10 minutes, then add green pepper and onions.
Cover until done.

title: blueberry nut bread
directions: Cream sugar, butter, eggs and honey.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Add nuts and blueberries.
Mix well and pour into 3 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until tests done.
Serve with cream cheese, butter or cream cheese mixed with chopped dates and nuts.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown onion and ground beef.
Drain.
Put half cabbage in 2-quart casserole, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Layer half meat mixture, remaining cabbage and then remaining meat.
Mix water and soup and pour over top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cover the last 30 minutes to steam cabbage.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Bake potatoes, peel and mash.
Add beaten eggs and sugar. Cream melted butter and all ingredients.
Put in pie shell and bake at 375°
for 1 hour.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in refrigerator.
These pickles may be kept in the refrigerator all winter.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Drain.
Take mixture, tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
Stir well.
Place 1/2 mixture in lightly greased casserole.
Top with half beans.
Sprinkle with 1/2 corn chips.
Repeat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Uncover and bake 5 minutes longer.
To serve, sprinkle with lettuce.

title: thelma's mud cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Sift flour and cocoa and add to mixture.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Mix these ingredients together and pour into a greased and floured pan and bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: oxtail soup
directions: Put first eight ingredients in large pot.
Bring to a boil then reduce heat to simmer for 1 to 2 hours.
When oxtails are cooked add the barley and or pasta to the soup and cook until they are cooked (about 30 to 45 minutes). Remove bay leaf.

title: pink beans and hamburger casserole
directions: Saute hamburger, onion and bell pepper until brown. Add rest of ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: spinach stuffed mushrooms
directions: Have the cream cheese at room temperature.
Cut stems and saute with garlic.
Mix all ingredients well and stuff caps.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: aunt millie's brownies
directions: Melt margarine in square pan.
In a bowl, mix sugar, cocoa, eggs, flour and salt. Add melted margarine and nuts.
Stir well and pour back into square pan. Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix together Kool-Aid, water, sugar and juice, then add ginger ale and lime sherbet last.

title: hot rolls and cinnamon rolls
directions: Scald milk, mix yeast in warm water with 1 teaspoon sugar. Pour milk over oleo, shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and salt; let cool. Add yeast mixture.
Slightly beat eggs.
Add to all.
Stir in flour (may use part wheat flour).
Put dough on floured surface and knead until smooth, not sticky.
Put into greased bowl and cover with cloth or Saran Wrap.
Let rise for an hour.
Make into rolls or loaves.
Let rise another hour.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: vegetable sunburst
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium sauce pan, cook carrots in boiling water to cover just until tender crisp.
Place hot carrots under cold running water until cool enough to handle.
Drain.
In 1 1/2 quart casserole dish, arrange half of the carrots around the edge of dish.
Place half of the zucchini in center.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can Durkee onions over vegetables.
In small bowl, combine soup, milk and seasonings.
Pour half of soup mixture over onions.
Arrange remaining zucchini around edge of casserole and remaining carrots in center.	Pour remaining soup mixture over vegetables.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Serves 4-6.

title: warm taco salad
directions: For Sauce:
In bowl stir together tomatoes, sugar, oregano, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Using edge of spoon, break up large tomato pieces.
Stir in green pepper and onion.
Set taco sauce aside.

title: seven layer mexican dip
directions: Mix beans
and
chilies
and
spread
in a pizza pan or something similar
in
size.
Mix
sour
cream
and
taco mix. Spread on top of beans.
Mix avocados and salsa (to taste) and spread.
Combine shredded cheeses and sprinkle over top of the mixture.
Slice
olives, chop onions and tomatoes and sprinkle over
cheeses.
Place
tortilla
chips around edges as garnish and serve with lots of chips.

title: southern style creamed corn
directions: Remove husks and silks from corn. Cut corn from cob, scraping cob to remove pulp; set aside. Combine flour, sugar and salt in a small bowl; gradually stir in milk until mixture is smooth. Melt butter in a heavy skillet; add corn, mixing well. Gradually stir in flour mixture; cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes, stirring often. Stir in whipping cream; serve immediately.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Dissolve baking soda in sour cream.
Add to mixture and beat well.
Add bananas, flour, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg, salad oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Blend well.
Make into a ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Smash with fork or glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 375° oven.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix macaroni, peas, onions, pickles, bell pepper and pimento together.
Add 4 boiled eggs, chopped, mayonnaise and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over the salad.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook chopped onion and ground beef together; drain.
Add rest of ingredients; simmer for 30 minutes.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Cream and mix well the butter, margarine, brown sugar, white sugar, egg, oil, vanilla and orange rind. Combine and add flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Mix and stir in oatmeal, coconut, pecans and Rice Krispies. Drop walnut size on cookie sheet. Pat down slightly.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Cool on wire rack. Makes 70 to 80 cookies.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar, cornstarch and syrup until clear.
Add jello.
Cool until it starts to set.
Put fresh strawberries (cut in half) in baked, cooled pie shell.
Pour mixture over berries. Chill.
Top with whipped cream.

title: salad dressing
directions: Put into an electric blender.
Blend for 20 seconds.
Chill and pour over salad.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients just until blended.
Drop by teaspoon into hot chicken broth or sauerkraut and pork broth.
Cover with a tight fitting lid; do not open.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Good eating!

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions, omitting salt.
Drain well.
Place in large bowl.
Combine butter and whipping cream in small saucepan.
Cook over low heat until butter melts.
Stir in cheese, pepper and parsley.
Pour mixture over hot fettuccine; toss until fettuccine is coated.

title: the thing!
directions: Soften the cream cheese; add the Monterey Jack cheese, chilies, tomato, green pepper, onions and seasonings to taste.
Mix well. Scoop out the center of the loaf of bread and fill the cavity with the cheese mixture.
Bake in 350° oven, stirring cheese occasionally until completely melted (about 25 to 30 minutes).
Do not overcook.
Serve with crackers or small chunks of bread.

title: cheesy sausage biscuits
directions: Crumble sausage into skillet.
Add onion and cook over medium heat until sausage is browned.
Drain well on paper towels.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Soak pecans for 30 minutes.
Drain on towel for 2 hours and bake at 300° until done.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling water for 4 minutes; thoroughly drain.
Combine soup and sour cream and mix by hand until
smooth.
Add carrot and mix lightly.
Combine stuffing mix and melted butter together.
Spread half of stuffing mix over bottom of greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture over top of dressing, then cover the vegetable mixture with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: stir and go salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Be sure to drain the juice from the fruit before using.

title: microwave spanish chicken
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer olives, mushrooms and chicken breasts.
Set aside.
Place bacon in a 2-cup measure. Microwave on High 1 1/2 to 3 minutes, or until crisp.
Remove bacon with slotted spoon.
Blend flour into bacon drippings.
Stir in wine and salt.
Microwave at High for 1 to 3 minutes or until thickened.
Add bacon.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with wax paper. Microwave at High 8 to 11 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, rearranging chicken once.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese cake
directions: In a bowl, combine crumbs, butter and 1/4 cup sugar.
Mix together.
Pat into the bottom and sides of pan.
Chill.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces. Combine chicken, consomme, soup, garlic, onion and cloves in saucepan. Add mushrooms. Cook over moderate heat 10 minutes. Season with salt. Add spaghetti. Boil gently for 10 minutes or until spaghetti is tender. Serve hot. Makes 6 servings. (Can substitute pork.)

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter, powdered sugar and water together. Roll into about 24 balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
With toothpick, dip balls into chocolate and set on buttered plate.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and then take up and fry hamburger with onion until brown.
Drain grease.
Put all together and cook for 3 hours in crock-pot.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain both cans of green beans.
Mix with the mushroom soup. Place onion rings on top.
Heat in oven or microwave and serve.

title: christmas candy
directions: Peel potato.
Boil until done.
Mash while hot.
Add powdered sugar, a little at a time, until you have a dough-like mixture. Roll out on waxed paper.
Dough should be about 1/2-inch thick. Spread enough peanut butter to evenly cover dough.
Roll up.
Chill overnight.
Slice into pieces.

title: corn relish
directions: Put together in pot
and boil for 15 minutes. Put in hot jars and can.

title: gingerbread muffins
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add egg; beat well.
Add molasses.
Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Add water; beat until smooth.
Fill small greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 20.

title: shrimp asparagus salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and beat well.
Pour 1/2 mixture over shrimp in bowl.
Pour remainder on greens.
Chill both at least 1 hour.

title: delicious apple cake
directions: In a mixer, beat margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Slowly add flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg. Then add apples and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar on top.

title: easy cheesy potatoes
directions: Peel and cube potatoes and place in pan. Cover with water. Chop onion and put in with potatoes. Cook over medium heat until done. Salt and pepper to taste. Stir in cheese and sour cream.

title: snap beans and new potatoes
directions: In heavy pot, fry bacon over medium heat until done.
Remove bacon.
Add butter and all seasonings.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Add all ingredients except potatoes and boil, covered, for 45 minutes. Add potatoes; season to taste and cook 30 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: marty's shrimp casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to directions on box.
Saute onion and green pepper in 1/2 stick margarine until onion and pepper are soft.
Add mushrooms.
Combine rice, shrimp, onion, pepper and mushrooms with 1 3/4 cans of cream of chicken soup.
Add 1 tablespoon of Worcestershire sauce and 6 drops of Tabasco.
Mix cracker crumbs with remaining melted margarine.
Place rice and shrimp mixture in a buttered 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: theresa's coffee
directions: Place 1 tablespoon Drambuie and 1 teaspoon brown sugar in each of 8 serving cups.
Fill with hot coffee.
Scoop 1 tablespoon ice cream in, then whipped cream for each.
Stir when you are ready to drink.

title: hearty meat filling
directions: Combine all ingredients together with enough mayonnaise or Miracle Whip for easy spreading.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dredge meat in flour, salt and pepper; brown in hot fat.
Add onions, garlic, mushrooms, Worcestershire sauce and bouillon. Simmer 30 minutes or until meat is tender.
Add soup and mix well. Fold in sour cream.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: blueberry syrup
directions: Simmer together about 10 minutes. Top your favorite pancakes with this syrup. Yummy! Yields about 2 1/2 c.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: First butter plate.
Put peanut butter and marshmallow cream on plate.
Cook sugar, milk and butter.
Cook slow until more than soft ball.
Stir into peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Have pan ready to pour into before starting.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt margarine and oil together; add to brown sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, and blend well.
Add flour, a small amount at a time.
Add vanilla, nuts, coconut and chips; stir well.
Bake at 350° in a greased pan for 30 minutes.

title: apple bars
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt and cut in shortening.
Mix like pie crust.
Put egg in measuring cup and fill to 2/3 cup with milk. Mix well.
Divide into 2 parts.
Rolls better if you chill for awhile.
Roll 1/2 of dough and put into a pan, 10 x 15-inch. Sprinkle Rice Krispies on dough.
Top with apples, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, flour and lemon juice.
Beat egg white and pour over crust with a pastry brush.

title: saucy beef over rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in Reynolds oven bag (large size, 14 x 20-inch).
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add undrained tomatoes, soup mix, water and pepper in bag.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
Add beef strips to bag.
Turn bag to coat beef with sauce.
Arrange ingredients in an even layer.
Close bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top.
Bake until beef is tender, 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Cream sugar and margarine. Add egg yolks.
Mix in all other ingredients. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Make into small balls.
Chill. Melt chips and paraffin together.
Use toothpicks to dip balls into melted chips and paraffin.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake 2 cans of crescent rolls on cookie sheet at 375° until brown, then cool.
Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing mix.
Spread over cool crescent rolls crust.
Add any vegetables you like.
Top with cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion added. Cream together the sour cream, chicken soup and chiles.
Roll hamburger meat inside tortillas.
Place in pan and pour cream sauce over top of enchiladas.
Top with grated cheese. Cook, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Serve when cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: green grape salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix grapes, pineapple and pecans. Set aside. Melt oleo; add flour. Stir until smooth. Add milk slowly, stirring and adding 6 marshmallows. Cook on medium, heating until marshmallows are melted, continuing to stir. Add remaining marshmallows until all the mixture is melted and smooth. Remove from heat and let cool. Pour over grape mixture and toss. Chill for several hours before serving.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix egg, mustard and old bay together.
Then add mayonnaise. Fold ingredients into crab meat.

title: mounds balls
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream together the butter and confectioners sugar.
Add coconut, milk, almonds and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Roll into walnut size balls (may have to refrigerate first).
Insert a toothpick in each ball.
Place on cookie sheet. Refrigerate or freeze firm.

title: french peach tart
directions: Prepare pie crust and bake in hot oven at 425° for 12 minutes or until golden.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Combine pudding mix with milk, sour cream and almond extract in a medium bowl. Prepare following directions on package.
Pour into cooled crust. Let stand at room temperature for 5 minutes or until set.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in hot tap water.
Let cool, not jelled. Add cake mix, eggs and oil.
Mix well, 5 minutes on medium speed. Bake 1 hour at 350° in greased and floured spring-form pan.
When cake is done, leave in pan. Combine lemonade and sugar.
Mix well. Pour over cake at once.
Refrigerate about 8 hours.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour in a casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hot water gingerbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan. Sift together first 6 ingredients.
Work shortening until smooth and creamy.
Slowly add sugar until light and creamy.
Add beaten egg and molasses.
Add flour mixture and hot water alternately, beating after each addition.
Turn into pan and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 40 to 55 minutes or until done.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and separate onion slices into rings.
Arrange layers of cabbage and onion in a bowl or plastic container, sprinkling sugar as you layer.
Place all other ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage and onions. Cool.
Cover and refrigerate.
Best if made at least one day prior to serving.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together in baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or cook on low in a crock-pot for 3 hours.

title: amanda's hot sauce
directions: Cook until it boils. Turn heat down and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add butter and cream.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake until set.

title: fudge cookies(unbaked)
directions: Bring to a boil in saucepan the sugar, milk, butter and cocoa. Cool 5 minutes.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add oatmeal and vanilla. Drop in desired size on waxed paper or cookie sheet.

title: crab meat cheese ball
directions: Mix together cream cheese, garlic powder, salt and chives. Fold in crab meat.
Form into a ball or log and roll in pecans. Serve with your favorite cracker.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Mix all of the ingredients. Stuff in decored peppers and wrap in foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: frozen pineapple slush
directions: Bring water and sugar to boil.
Then add the juices.
Freeze for 12 to 24 hours.
When ready to serve, put some of the slush in a glass and pour ginger ale over it.

title: spicy macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni; add tomato juice.
Gradually stir in black pepper, green pepper and onion.
After you have added these ingredients, let simmer.
Add salt to taste.

title: chop suey
directions: In a large saucepan, brown cubed beef in oil.
Add garlic, onion, water, soy sauce and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil over medium for 15 minutes.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.
Add chopped celery and water.
Cook for 5 more minutes.
Have cooked rice prepared to serve with.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, bananas and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well. Stir in pecans.
Pour into greased 15 x 10 loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely and frost.

title: honey gingerbread cake
directions: Beat butter, eggs, sugar and lemon rind.
Sift together flour, nutmeg, baking powder, salt and ginger.
In separate bowl, combine honey, molasses and water.
Add alternately to butter mixture with flour mixture.
Bake in buttered dish, 350° for 40 minutes; don't overbake.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until meat begins to fall off bone (I cover the chicken with water and add 1 small onion and a stalk of celery for extra flavor).
Remove chicken and let cool.
Save broth for later.
Once chicken is cool, pull from bone and cut into small pieces.
Set aside.

title: onion meat loaf
directions: Break eggs
in
a bowl, heat slightly.
Stir in catsup, water and envelope
of
soup mix.
Add bread crumbs and ground beef. Bake in oven at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers or use as filling for sandwiches.

title: peach jello dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups hot water.
Let cool.
Blend in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Drain fruit and add to Jell-O.
Add chopped bananas and pecans.
Chill overnight.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Mix all together.
Mix on medium speed for 3 to 5 minutes. Add chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased and floured (use cocoa to dust pan) tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Cool on rack for 30 minutes.
Turn out on rack and cool.
